obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (17125)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17125&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Cantonments Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 18th December, 2006, vide notification No. S.R.O. 15(E), dated 18th December, 2006, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (17126)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17126&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `.In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Assistant Health Officer" means the medical officer appointed by the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, to be the Assistant Health Officer for a cantonment;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means a Cantonment Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "boundary wall" means a wall which abuts on a street and which does not exceed two and a`
  line `half metres in height;`
  line
  line `(d) "building" means a house, outhouse, stable, latrine, shed, hut or other roofed structure`
  line `whether of masonry, brick, wood, mud, metal or other material, and any part thereof, and includes a`
  line `well and a wall other than a boundary wall but does not include a tent or other portable and temporary`
  line shelter;
  line
  line `(e) "casual election" means an election held to fill a casual vacancy;`
  line
  line `(f) "casual vacancy" means a vacancy occurring otherwise than by efflux of time in the office of`
  line `an elected member of a Board and includes a vacancy in such office, arising under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(g) "Chief Executive Officer" means the person appointed under this Act to be the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer of a cantonment;`
  line
  line `(h) "civil area" means an area declared to be a civil area by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(i) "civil area committee" means a committee appointed under section 47;`
  line
  line `(j) "Command" means one of the Commands into which India is for military purposes for the`
  line `time being divided, and includes any area which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare to be a Command for all or any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "dairy" includes any farm, cattle-shed, milk-store, milk-shop or other place from which milk`
  line `is supplied or in which milk is kept for purposes of sale or is manufactured for the sale into butter,`
  line `ghee, cheese or curds, and, in relation to a dairyman who does not occupy any premises for the sale of`
  line `milk, includes any place in which he keeps the vessels used by him for the storage or sale of milk;`
  line
  line `(l) "dairyman" includes the keeper of a cow, buffalo, goat, ass or other animal, the milk of which`
  line `is offered or is intended to be offered for sale for human consumption, and any supplier of milk and`
  line `any occupier of a dairy;`
  line
  line `(m) "dangerous disease" means cholera, leprosy, enteric fever, smallpox, tuberculosis, diphtheria,`
  line `plague, influenza, venereal disease, hepatitis, Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome and any other`
  line `epidemic, endemic, infectious or communicable disease which the Board may by public notice,`
  line `declare to be, an infectious, contagious or communicable disease for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "Defence Estates Circle" means one of the circles into which India is, for the purposes of`
  line `defence estates management, for the time being divided, and includes any area which the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a Defence Estates Circle for all`
  line `or any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "Defence Estates Officer" means the officer appointed by the Central Government to perform`
  line `the duties of the Defence Estates Officer for the purpose of this Act and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(p) "Director General" means an officer of the Indian Defence Estates Service (IDES) appointed`
  line `by the Central Government to perform the duties of the Director General, Defence Estates for the`
  line `purpose of this Act and includes Senior Additional Director General and Additional Director General;`
  line
  line `(q) "Director" means the officer appointed by the Central Government to perform the duties of`
  line `the Director, Defence Estates, the Command, for the purposes of this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(r) "entitled consumer" means a person in a cantonment who is paid from the Defence Service`
  line `Estimates and is authorised by general or special order of the Central Government to receive a supply`
  line `of water for domestic purposes from the Military Engineer Services or the Public Works Department`
  line `on such terms and conditions as may be specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(s) "Executive Engineer" means the officer of the Military Engineer Services of that grade,`
  line `having charge of the military works in a cantonment or where more than one such officer has charge`
  line `of the military works in a cantonment such one of those officers as the Officer Commanding the`
  line `station may designate in this behalf, and includes the officer of whatever grade in immediate`
  line `executive engineering charge of a cantonment;`
  line
  line `(t) "factory" means a factory as defined in clause (m) of section 2 of the Factories Act, 1948`
  line `(63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(u) "Forces" means the regular Army, Navy and Air Force or any part of any one or more of`
  line them;
  line
  line `(v) "General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command (GOC-in-C, Command)" means the`
  line `Officer Commanding any of the Commands;`
  line
  line `(w) "General Officer Commanding the Area" means the Officer Commanding any one of the`
  line `areas into which India is for military purposes for the time being divided, or any sub-area which does`
  line `not form part of any such area, or any area which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare to be an area for all or any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "Group Housing" means a group of houses for dwelling purposes and may comprise all or any`
  line `of the following: namely, (a) a dwelling unit, (b) open spaces intended for recreation and`
  line `ventilation, (c) roads, paths, sewers, drains, water supply and ancillary installations, street lighting`
  line `and other amenities, (d) convenient shopping place, schools, community hall or other amenities for`
  line `common use;`
  line
  line `(y) "Government" in relation to this Act means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(z) "Health Officer" means the senior executive medical officer in military employ on duty in a`
  line cantonment;
  line
  line `(za) "hospital" includes family welfare centre, child welfare centre, maternity centre and health`
  line centre;
  line
  line `(zb) "hut" means any building, no material portion of which above the plinth level is constructed`
  line `of masonry or of squared timber framing or of iron framing;`
  line
  line `(zc) "inhabitant", in relation to a cantonment, or local area means any person ordinarily residing`
  line `or carrying on business or owning or occupying immovable property therein, or declared as such by`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer and in case of a dispute, as decided by the District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(zd) "intoxicating drug" includes a narcotic drug and psychotropic substance as defined in the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985) as modified from time to time;`
  line
  line `(ze) "market" includes any place where persons assemble for the sale of, or for the purpose of`
  line `exposing for sales, meat, fish, fruits, vegetables, animals intended for human food or any other`
  line `articles of human food whatsoever, with or without the consent of the owner of such place`
  line `notwithstanding that there may be no common regulation for the concourse of buyers and sellers and`
  line `whether or not any control is exercised over the business of, or the persons frequenting, the market by`
  line `the owner of the place or by any other person, but shall not include a single shop or group of shops`
  line `not being more than six in number and shops within unit lines;`
  line
  line `(zf) "military" includes Air Force, Navy and other defence related establishments;`
  line
  line `(zg) "military officer" means a person who, being an officer within the meaning of the Army Act,`
  line `1950 (46 of 1950), the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) or the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), is`
  line `commissioned, gazetted or in pay as an officer doing army, naval or air force duty with the army,`
  line `navy or air force, or is an officer doing such duty in any arm, branch or part of any of those forces;`
  line
  line `(zh) "nuisance" includes any act, omission, place, animal or thing which causes or is likely to`
  line `cause injury, danger, annoyance or offence to the sense of sight, smell or hearing or disturbance to`
  line `rest or sleep, or which is or may be dangerous to life or injurious to health or property;`
  line
  line `(zi) "occupier" includes an owner in occupation of, or otherwise using his own land or building;`
  line `(zj) "Officer Commanding the station or Station Commander" means the military officer for the`
  line `time being in command of the forces in a cantonment and if such officer is likely to be absent for`
  line `more than thirty days, the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command may nominate, by`
  line `an order, another military officer as "Officer Commanding the station or Station Commander";`
  line
  line `(zk) "ordinary election" means an election held to fill a vacancy in the office of an elected`
  line `member of a Board arising by efflux of time;`
  line
  line `(zl) "owner" includes any person who is receiving or is entitled to receive the rent of any`
  line `building or land whether on his own account or on behalf of himself and others or an agent or trustee,`
  line `or who would so receive the rent or be entitled to receive it if the building or land were let to a tenant;`
  line
  line `(zm) "party wall" means a wall forming part of a building and used or constructed to be used for`
  line `the support or separation of adjoining buildings belonging to different owners, or constructed or`
  line `adapted to be occupied by different persons;`
  line
  line `(zn) "Principal Director" means the Officer appointed by the Central Government to perform the`
  line `duties of the Principal Director, Defence Estates, the Command for the purpose of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(zo) "private market" means a market which is not maintained by a Board and which is licensed`
  line `by a Board under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(zp) "private slaughter-house" means a slaughter-house which is not maintained by a Board and`
  line `which is licensed by a Board under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(zq) "public market" means a market maintained by a Board;`
  line
  line `(zr) "public place" means any place which is open to the use and enjoyment of the public,`
  line `whether it is actually used or enjoyed by the public or not;`
  line
  line `(zs) "public slaughter-house" means a slaughter-house maintained by a Board;`
  line
  line `(zt) "resident", in relation to a cantonment, means a person who maintains therein a house or a`
  line `portion of a house which is at all times available for occupation by himself or his family even though`
  line `he may himself reside elsewhere, provided that he has not abandoned all intention of again occupying`
  line `such house either by himself or his family;`
  line
  line `(zu) "regulation" means a regulation made by a Cantonment Board under this Act by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(zv) "rule" means a rule made by the Central Government under this Act by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(zw) "shed" means a slight or temporary structure for shade or shelter;`
  line
  line `(zx) "slaughter-house" means any place ordinarily used for the slaughter of animals for the`
  line `purpose of selling the flesh thereof for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(zy) "soldier" means any person who is a soldier or sailor or an airman subject to the Army Act,`
  line `1950 (46 of 1950), the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) or the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), as the`
  line `case may be, and who is not a military officer;`
  line
  line `(zz) "spirituous liquor" means any fermented liquor, any wine, or any alcoholic liquid obtained by`
  line `distillation or the sap of any kind of palm tree, and includes any other liquid containing alcohol which`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a spirituous liquor`
  line
  line `(zza) "street" includes any way, road, lane, square, court, alley or passage in a cantonment,`
  line `whether a thoroughfare or not and whether built upon or not, over which the public have a right of`
  line `way and also the road-way or foot-way over any bridge or cause way;`
  line
  line `(zzb) "sub-area" means one of the sub-areas into which India is for military purposes for the time`
  line `being divided and includes, for all or any of the purposes of this Act, any territory which the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a sub-area for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(zzc) "trade or commercial premises" means any premises used or intended to be used for`
  line `carrying on any trade, commerce or industry;`
  line
  line `(zzd) "vehicle" means a wheeled conveyance of any description which is capable of being used`
  line `on a street, and includes a motor-car, motor lorry, motor omnibus, cart, locomotive, tram-car,`
  line `handcart, truck, motor-cycle, bicycle, tricycle and rickshaw;`
  line
  line `(zze) "water-works" includes all lakes, tanks, streams, cisterns, springs, pumps, wells, reservoirs,`
  line `aqueducts, water-trucks, sluices mains, pipes, culverts, hydrants, stand-pipes, and conduits and all`
  line `machinery, lands, buildings, bridges and things used for, or intended for the purpose of supplying`
  line `water to a cantonment; and`
  line
  line `(zzf) "year" means the year commencing on the first day of April.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (17127)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Definition of cantonments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17127&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, declare any place or places along with boundaries in which any part of the Forces is quartered or`
  line `which, being in the vicinity of any such place or places, is or are required for the service of such forces to`
  line `be a cantonment for the purposes of this Act and of all other enactments for the time being in force, and`
  line `may, by a like notification, declare that any cantonment shall cease to be a cantonment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by a like notification, define the limits of any cantonment for the`
  line `aforesaid purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) When any place is declared a cantonment under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a Board within a period of one year in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the said`
  line `period of one year for a further period of six months at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, until a Board is constituted, by order make`
  line `necessary provisions for the efficient administration of the cantonment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that in any place`
  line `declared a cantonment under sub-section (1) the provisions of any enactment relating to local`
  line `self-government other than this Act shall have effect only to such extent or subject to such modifications,`
  line `or that any authority constituted under any such enactment shall exercise authority only to such extent, as`
  line `may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (17128)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Alteration of limits of cantonments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17128&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may after consulting the State`
  line `Government and the Board concerned, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare its intention to`
  line `include within the cantonment any local area situated in the vicinity thereof or to exclude from the`
  line `cantonment any local area comprised therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Any inhabitant of a cantonment or local area in respect of which notification has been published`
  line `under sub-section (1) may, within eight weeks from the date of notification, submit in writing to the`
  line `Central Government through the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, an objection to`
  line `the notification, and the Central Government shall take such objection into consideration.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of eight weeks from the date of the notification, the Central Government may after`
  line `considering the objections, if any, which have been submitted under sub-section (2), by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, include the local area in respect of which the notification was published under`
  line `sub-section (1), or any part thereof, in the cantonment or, as the case may be, exclude such area or any`
  line `part thereof from the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (17129)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `The effect of including area in cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17129&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `When, by a notification under section 4, any local`
  line `area is included in a cantonment, such area shall there upon become subject to this Act and to all other`
  line `enactments for the time being in force throughout the cantonment and to all notifications, rules,`
  line `regulations, bye-laws, orders and directions issued or made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (17130)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Disposal of cantonment fund and cantonment development fund when area ceases to be a cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17130&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) When, by a notification under section 3, any cantonment ceases to be a cantonment`
  line `and the local area comprised therein is immediately placed under the control of a local authority, the`
  line `balance of the cantonment fund or the cantonment development fund and other property vesting in the`
  line `Board shall vest in such local authority, and the liabilities of the Board shall be transferred to such local`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(2) When, in like manner, any cantonment ceases to be a cantonment and the local area comprised`
  line `therein is not immediately placed under the control of a local authority, the balance of the cantonment`
  line `fund or the cantonment development fund and other property vesting in the Board shall vest in the Central`
  line `Government, and the liabilities of the Board shall be transferred to that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (17131)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Disposal of cantonment fund and cantonment development fund when area ceases to be included in a cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17131&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) When, by a notification under section 4, any local area forming part of a`
  line `cantonment ceases to be under the control of a particular Board and is immediately placed under the`
  line `control of some other local authority, such portion of the cantonment fund or the cantonment development`
  line `fund and other property vesting in the Board and such portion of the liabilities of the Board, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by general or special order, direct, shall be transferred to that other local authority.`
  line
  line `(2)When, in like manner, any local area forming part of a cantonment ceases to be under the control`
  line `of a particular Board and is not immediately placed under the control of some other local authority; such`
  line `portion of the cantonment fund or the cantonment development fund and other property vesting in the`
  line `Board shall vest in the Central Government, and such portion of the liabilities of the Board shall be`
  line `transferred to that Government, as the Central Government may, by general or special order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (17132)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Application of funds and property transferred under sections 6 and 7.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17132&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Any cantonment fund`
  line `or a cantonment development fund or a portion thereof or other property of a Board vesting in the Central`
  line `Government under the provisions of section 6 or section 7 shall be applied in the first place to satisfy any`
  line `liabilities of the Board transferred under such provisions to that Government, and in the second place for the benefit of the inhabitants of the local area which has ceased to be a cantonment or, as the case may be,`
  line `part of a cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (17133)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Limitation of operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17133&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, exclude from the operation of any part of this Act the whole or any part of a cantonment, or`
  line `direct that any provision of this Act shall, in the case of any cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) situated within the limits of a metropolitan area; or`
  line
  line `(b) in which the Board is superseded under section 60, apply with such modification as may be`
  line `so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (17134)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Cantonment Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17134&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every cantonment there shall be a Cantonment Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Board shall be deemed to be a municipality under clause (e) of article 243P of the`
  line `Constitution for the purposes of--`
  line
  line `(a) receiving grants and allocations; or`
  line
  line `(b) implementing the Central Government schemes of social welfare, public health, hygiene,`
  line `safety, water supply, sanitation, urban renewal and education.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (17135)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Incorporation of Cantonment Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17135&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every Board shall, by the name of the place by`
  line `reference to which the cantonment is known, be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power to acquire and hold property both movable and immovable and to contract and`
  line `shall by the said name, sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (17136)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Constitution of Cantonment of Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17136&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Cantonments shall be divided into four categories,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) Category I Cantonments, in which the population exceeds fifty thousand;`
  line
  line `(ii) Category II Cantonments, in which the population exceeds ten thousand, but does not exceed`
  line `fifty thousand;`
  line
  line `(iii) Category III Cantonments, in which the population exceeds two thousand five hundred, but`
  line `does not exceed ten thousand; and`
  line
  line `(iv) Category IV Cantonments, in which the population does not exceed two thousand five`
  line hundred.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the population shall be calculated in accordance with the latest`
  line `official census, or, if the Central Government, by general or special order, so directs, in accordance with a`
  line `special census taken for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) In Category I Cantonments, the Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the station as ex officio or, if the Central Government so directs in`
  line `respect of any cantonment, such other military officer as may be nominated in his place by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command;`
  line
  line `(b) the District Magistrate or an Executive Magistrate not below the rank of Additional District`
  line `Magistrate nominated by him;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(d) the Health Officer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Executive Engineer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) three military officers nominated by name by the Officer Commanding the station by order in`
  line writing;
  line
  line `(g) eight members elected under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) In Category II Cantonments, the Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the station as ex officio or, if the Central Government so directs in`
  line `respect of any cantonment, such other military officer as may be nominated in his place by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command;`
  line
  line `(b) the District Magistrate or an Executive Magistrate not below the rank of Additional District`
  line `Magistrate nominated by him;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(d) the Health Officer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Executive Engineer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) two military officers nominated by name by the Officer Commanding the station by order in`
  line writing;
  line
  line `(g) seven members elected under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) In Category III Cantonments, the Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the station as ex officio or, if the Central Government so directs in`
  line `respect of any cantonment, such other military officer, as may be nominated in his place by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command;`
  line
  line `(b) the District Magistrate or an Executive Magistrate nominated by him;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(d) the Health Officer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Executive Engineer ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) one military officer nominated by name by the Officer Commanding the station by order in`
  line writing;
  line
  line `(g) six members elected under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) In Category IV Cantonments, the Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the station ex officio or, if the Central Government so directs in`
  line `respect of any cantonment, such other military officer as may be nominated in his place by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(c) two members elected under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) The Officer Commanding the station may, if he thinks fit, with the sanction of the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, nominate in place of any military officer whom he is empowered`
  line `to nominate under clause (f) of sub-section (3), clause (f) of sub-section (4) or clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (5), any person, whether in the service of the Government or not, who is ordinarily resident in`
  line `the cantonment or in the vicinity thereof.`
  line
  line `(8) Every election or nomination of a member of a Board and every vacancy in the elected`
  line `membership thereof shall be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(9) The Member of Parliament and Member of Legislative Assembly representing constituencies`
  line `which comprises wholly or partly the cantonment area, shall be special invitees for the meetings of the`
  line `Board but without a right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (17137)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to vary constitution of Boards in special circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17137&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 12, if the Central Government is satisfied,--`
  line
  line `(a) that by reason of military operations, it is necessary, or`
  line
  line `(b) that, for the administration of the cantonment, it is desirable, to vary the constitution of the`
  line `Board in any cantonment under this section, the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make a declaration to that effect.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the making of a declaration under sub-section (1), the Board in the cantonment shall consist`
  line `of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the station,`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Executive Officer, and`
  line
  line `(c) one member, not being a person in the service of the Government, nominated by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command.`
  line
  line `(3) The nomination of a member of a Board constituted under this section, and the vacancy in the`
  line `membership thereof shall be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of a Board constituted by a declaration under sub-section (1) shall not`
  line `ordinarily extend beyond one year:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may from time to time, by a like declaration, extend the term`
  line `of office of such a Board by any period not exceeding one year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government shall forthwith direct that the term of office of such a`
  line `Board shall cease if, in the opinion of the Central Government, the reasons stated in the declaration`
  line `whereby such Board was constituted or its term of office was extended, have ceased to exist.`
  line
  line `(5) When the term of office of a Board constituted under this section has expired or ceased, the Board`
  line `shall be replaced by the former Board which, but for the declaration under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (4), would have continued to hold office, or, if the term of office of such former Board has`
  line `expired, by a Board constituted under section 12.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (17138)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Term of office of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17138&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of`
  line `a member of a Board shall be five years and shall commence--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of an elected member, from the date of notification of his election under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 12, or from the date on which the vacancy has occurred to which he is`
  line `elected, whichever is later; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of a nominated member, from the date of nomination under clauses (b) and (f) of`
  line `sub-section (3), clauses (b) and (f) of sub-section (4) and clauses (b) and (f) of sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 12, or the date of vacancy under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 18, whichever is later,`
  line `and the member so nominated shall be able to take part in the proceedings of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, when satisfied that it is necessary in order to avoid`
  line `administrative difficulty, extend the term of office of all the elected members of a Board by such period`
  line `not exceeding one year, as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a member whose term of office has been so extended, shall cease to hold office`
  line `on the date of the notification of the election of his successor under sub-section (8) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member of a Board shall continue so long as he holds the`
  line `office by virtue of which he is such a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member elected to fill a casual vacancy shall commence from the date of`
  line `the notification of his election, and shall continue so long only as the member in whose place he is elected`
  line `would have been entitled to hold office if the vacancy had not occurred.`
  line
  line `(4) An outgoing member shall, unless the Central Government otherwise directs, continue in office`
  line `until the election of his successor is notified under sub-section (8) of section 12 or the nomination of his`
  line `successor, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Any outgoing member may, if qualified, be re-elected or re-nominated.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (17139)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Filling of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17139&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Vacancies arising by efflux of time in the office of an elected member`
  line `of a Board shall be filled by an ordinary election to be held on such date as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) A casual vacancy shall be filled by a casual election the date of which shall be fixed by the`
  line `Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, and shall be, as soon as may be, after the`
  line `occurrence of the vacancy:`
  line
  line `Provided that no casual election shall be held to fill a vacancy occurring within six months of any`
  line `date on which the vacancy will occur by efflux of time, but such vacancy shall be filled at the next`
  line `ordinary election.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (17140)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Vacancies in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17140&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If for any cause at an election no member is elected, or if the`
  line `elected member is unwelling to serve on the Board, fresh election shall be held to fill up such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person is elected to more than one seat in a Board, then, unless he resigns all but one of the`
  line `seats within fourteen days from the date on which he is declared elected, or where the dates on which he`
  line `is declared elected are different in respect of different seats, from the last of such dates, all the seats shall`
  line `become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) Vacancies arising in any of the following cases shall be filled by nomination by the Central`
  line `Government after consultation with the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where at a casual election no member is elected;`
  line
  line `(b) where at an election held when a Board is constituted for the first time no member or an`
  line `insufficient number of members is elected or an elected member is unwilling to serve on the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-section (2) of section 15, a member nominated in pursuance of`
  line `sub-section (3) of this section shall where there has been a division of the cantonment into wards, be`
  line `deemed to have been elected by such ward as the Central Government may at the time of making the`
  line `nomination or at any time thereafter declare.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of a member nominated under this section shall expire at the time at which it`
  line `would have expired if he had been elected at the casual election.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (17141)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Oath or affirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17141&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every person who is by virtue of his office, or who is nominated or elected to be, a member of the Board shall, before taking his seat, make and subscribe at a meeting of the Board an oath or affirmation of his allegiance to the Constitution of India in the following form, namely:--`
  line
  line become
  line
  line `"I, A.B., havingbeen elected`
  line `a member of this Board, do`
  line
  line `been nominated`
  line
  line `swear in the name of God`
  line
  line `that I will bear true faith and allegiance to the Constitution of`
  line `solemnly affirm`
  line
  line `India as by law established and that I will faithfully discharge the duty upon which I am about to enter.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (17142)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17142&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) Any elected member of a Board who wishes to resign his office may give`
  line `his resignation in writing to the President of the Board who shall forward it for acceptance and`
  line `notification to the Central Government under intimation to the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief,`
  line `the Command.`
  line
  line `(b) Any nominated member of a Board who wishes to resign his office may forward his resignation in`
  line `writing through the President of the Board to the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command`
  line `for orders.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government or the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, as the`
  line `case may be, accepts the resignation, such acceptance shall be communicated to the Board, and thereupon`
  line `the seat of the member resigning shall become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the resignation of any person elected to`
  line `more than one seat in a Board from all but one of the seats in pursuance of sub-section (2) of section 16`
  line `shall take effect when such resignation is received by the President of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (17143)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `President and Vice-President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17143&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Officer commanding the station if a member of the`
  line `Board shall be the President of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a military officer holding the office of the President ceases to be the Officer`
  line `commanding the station merely by reason of a temporary absence from the station for a period not`
  line `exceeding thirty consecutive days, he shall not vacate the office of President.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Officer commanding the station is not a member of the Board, the military officer`
  line `nominated in his place under clause (a) of sub-section (3), sub-section (4), sub-section (5) or`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 12 shall be the President of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) In every Board except in case of a Board falling under Category IV Cantonment there shall be a`
  line `Vice-President elected by the elected members only from amongst them in accordance with such`
  line `procedure as the Central Government may by rule prescribe.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of a Board falling under Category IV Cantonment, the Vice-President shall be elected by`
  line `draw of lot under the supervision of the President of the Board in such manner as he may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (17144)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Term of office of Vice-President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17144&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of a Vice-President shall be five years`
  line `or his residual term of office as a member, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(2) A Vice-President may resign his office by notice in writing to the President and, on the`
  line `resignation being accepted by the Board, the office shall become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) A Vice-President may be removed from his office, at a special meeting convened for the purpose`
  line `on a requisition for the same by not less than one-half of the elected members of the Board holding office,`
  line `by a resolution passed by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the total number of elected members`
  line `then holding office and attending and no member, other than an elected member, shall have the right to`
  line `vote on the resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of Category IV Cantonments, the Vice-President may be removed if a resolution`
  line `to this effect is passed by the Board and the other elected member shall become the Vice-President.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (17145)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Duties of President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17145&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the President of every Board--`
  line
  line `(a) unless prevented by reasonable cause, to convene and preside at all meetings of the Board and`
  line `to regulate the conduct of business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) to control, direct and supervise the financial and executive administration of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) to perform all the duties and exercise all the powers specifically imposed or conferred on the`
  line `President by or under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) subject to any restrictions, limitations and conditions imposed by this Act, to exercise`
  line `executive power for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act and to be directly`
  line `responsible for the fulfilment of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) in case of gross misconduct during the course of meeting, to suspend a member other than a`
  line `Chief Executive Officer from attending the unconcluded part of the meeting of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, by order in writing, empower the Vice-President to exercise all or any of the`
  line `powers and duties referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) other than any power, duty or function which`
  line `he is by resolution of the Board expressly forbidden to delegate.`
  line
  line `(3) The exercise or discharge of any powers, duties or functions delegated by the President under this`
  line `section shall be subject to such restrictions, limitations and conditions, if any, as may be laid down by the`
  line `President and to the control of, and to revision by, the President.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order made under sub-section (2) shall forthwith be communicated to the Board and to the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (17146)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Duties of Vice-President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17146&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Vice-President of every Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the absence of the President and unless prevented by reasonable cause, to preside at`
  line `meetings of the Board and when so presiding to exercise the authority of the President under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(b) during the incapacity or temporary absence of the President or pending his appointment or`
  line `succession to perform any other duty and exercise any other power of the President; and`
  line
  line `(c) to exercise any power and perform any duty of the President which may be delegated to him`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 21.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (17147)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Allowances to Vice-President and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17147&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Vice-President and each elected member of`
  line `the Board shall be entitled to receive such allowances, as the Central Government may, by rule, prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (17148)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appointment of Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17148&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every cantonment there shall be a Chief`
  line `Executive Officer appointed by the Central Government or by such person as the Central Governmentay authorise in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the event of temporary absence of the Chief Executive Officer, not exceeding ninety`
  line `days, the Principal Director shall designate an officer under his jurisdiction to perform the duties of the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer during such period.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than one-half of the salary of the Chief Executive Officer shall be paid by the Central`
  line `Government and the balance from the cantonment fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer shall be the Member-Secretary of the Board and of every Committee`
  line `of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (17149)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Duties of Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17149&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of clause (c) and clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21, the Chief Executive Officer shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise all the powers and perform all the duties conferred or imposed upon him by or under`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to any restrictions, limitations and conditions imposed by this Act, to exercise`
  line `executive power to ensure that the administration of the Board is carried out in accordance with`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the duties of, and exercise supervision and control over the acts and proceedings of`
  line `all, officers and employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) be responsible for the custody of all records of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) arrange for the performance of such duties relative to the proceedings of the Board or of any`
  line `Committee of the Board or of any Committee of Arbitration constituted under this Act, as those`
  line `bodies may respectively impose on him; and`
  line
  line `(f) comply with every requisition of the Board on any matter pertaining to the administration of`
  line `the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (17150)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Special power of Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17150&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may direct the`
  line `execution of any work or the doing of any act, in public interest and in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder, and incur such expenditure as may be necessary in executing such`
  line `work or doing such act, as the case may be, subject to the financial limits which the Board may by`
  line `resolution determine subject to general guidelines issued by the Director General, Defence Estates with`
  line `the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may, in case of emergency, direct the execution of any work or the`
  line `doing of any act which would ordinarily require the sanction of the Board and immediate execution or`
  line `doing of which is in his opinion, necessary for the service or safety of the public, and may direct that the`
  line `expense of executing such work or doing such act shall be paid from the cantonment fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall not act under this section without the previous sanction of the President or, in his`
  line `absence, of the Vice-President;`
  line
  line `(b) he shall not act under this section in contravention of any order of the Board prohibiting the`
  line `execution of any particular work or the doing of any particular act; and`
  line
  line `(c) he shall report forthwith the action taken under this section and the reasons there for to the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (17151)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17151&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board or, where a Board is not constituted in any place declared by`
  line `notification under sub-section (1) of section 3 to be a cantonment, the Officer Commanding the station,`
  line `shall prepare and publish an electoral roll showing the names of persons qualified to vote at elections to`
  line `the Board and such roll shall be prepared, revised and finally published in such manner and on such date`
  line `in each year as the Central Government may by rule prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person whose name appears in the final electoral roll shall, so long as the roll remains in`
  line `force, be entitled to vote at an election to the Board, and no other person shall be so entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) When a cantonment has been divided into wards, the electoral roll shall be divided into separate`
  line `lists for each ward.`
  line
  line `(4) If a new electoral roll is not published in any year on the date prescribed, the Central Government`
  line `may direct that the old electoral roll shall continue in operation until the new roll is published.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (17152)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Qualification of electors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17152&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who, on such date as may be fixed by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette here in after in this section referred to as`
  line `the qualifying date, is not less than eighteen years of age and who has resided in the cantonment for a`
  line `period of not less than six months immediately preceding the qualifying date shall, if not otherwise`
  line `disqualified, be entitled to be enrolled as an elector.`
  line
  line `"Explanation".--When any place is declared a cantonment for the first time, or when any local area is`
  line `first included in a cantonment, residence in the place or area comprising the cantonment on the aforesaid`
  line `date shall be deemed to be residence in the cantonment for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) A person notwithstanding that he is otherwise qualified, shall not be entitled to be enrolled as an`
  line `elector if he on the qualifying date--`
  line
  line `(i) is not a citizen of India, or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been adjudged by a competent court to be of unsound mind, or`
  line
  line `(iii) is an undischarged insolvent, or`
  line
  line `(iv) has been sentenced by a Criminal Court to imprisonment for a term exceeding two years for`
  line `an offence which is declared by the Central Government to be such as to unfit him to become an`
  line `elector or has been sentenced by a Criminal Court for any offence under Chapter IXA of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860):`
  line
  line `Provided that any disqualification incurred by a person under clause (iv) shall terminate on the lapse`
  line `of three years from the expiry of the sentence or order.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person having been enrolled as an elector in any electoral roll subsequently becomes`
  line `subject to any of the disqualifications referred to in sub-section (2), his name shall be removed from the`
  line `electoral roll unless, in the case referred to in clause (iv), the disqualification is removed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (17153)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Qualification for being a member of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17153&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as hereinafter provided, every`
  line `person, not being a person holding any office of profit under the Government, whose name is entered on`
  line `the electoral roll of a cantonment shall be qualified for election as a member of the Board in that`
  line cantonment.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be qualified for nomination as a member of a Board if he is subject to any of the`
  line `disqualifications specified in sub-section (2) of section 28.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be qualified for being chosen whether by election or nomination as, and for being`
  line `a member of a Board, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been dismissed from the service of the Government and is debarred from re-employment`
  line `therein, or is a dismissed employee of a Board;`
  line
  line `(b) is debarred from practising his profession or calling by order of any competent authority;`
  line
  line `(c) holds any place of profit in the gift or at the disposal of the Board, or is a police officer, or is`
  line `the servant or employer of a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(d) is interested in a subsisting contract made with, or in work being done for, the Board except as`
  line `a shareholder other than a director in an incorporated company; or`
  line
  line `(e) is an officer or employee, permanent or temporary, of a Board or of any other local authority;`
  line or
  line
  line `(f) is a member of any other local authority; or`
  line
  line `(g) has, by the authority referred to in clause (f) of section 31, been found to have been guilty of`
  line `any of the corrupt practices specified in sub-section (2) of section 30 unless a period of five years has`
  line `elapsed since the date of the decision of the authority; or`
  line
  line `(h) fails to pay any arrears of any kind due by him otherwise than as an agent, receiver, trustee or`
  line `an executor, to the Board within thirty days after the notice in this behalf has been served upon him;`
  line or
  line
  line `(i) is disqualified under any other provision of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be deemed to have any interest in such a contract or work as is`
  line `referred to in clause (d) by reason only of his having a share or interest in--`
  line
  line `(a) any lease or sale or purchase of immovable property or any agreement for the same; or`
  line
  line `(b) any agreement for the loan of money or any security for the payment of money only; or`
  line
  line `(c) any newspaper in which any advertisement relating to the affairs of the Board is inserted;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) the sale to the Board of any articles in which he regularly trades or the purchase from the`
  line `Board of any articles, to a value in either case not exceeding twenty-five thousand rupees in the`
  line `aggregate in any year during the period of the contract or work.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (17154)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17154&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of sections 27, 28 and 29, 'person' means an individual`
  line `human being.`
  line
  line `(2) The following shall be deemed to be corrupt practices within the meaning of clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section i(3) of section 29, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) "bribery" that is to say--`
  line
  line `(A) any gift, offer or promise by a candidate or his agent or by any other person with the`
  line `consent of a candidate or his agent of any gratification to any person whomsoever, with the`
  line `object, directly or indirectly of inducing--`
  line
  line `(a) a person to stand or not to stand as, or to withdraw or not to withdraw from being, a`
  line `candidate at an election; or`
  line
  line `(b) an elector to vote or refrain from voting at an election, or as a reward to--`
  line
  line `(i) a person for having so stood or not stood, or for having withdrawn or not having`
  line `withdrawn his candidature; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an elector for having voted or refrained from voting;`
  line
  line `(B) the receipt of, or agreement to receive, any gratification, whether as a motive or are`
  line ward--
  line
  line `(a) by a person for standing or not standing as, or for withdrawing or not withdrawing,`
  line `from being a candidate; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any person whomsoever for himself or any other person for voting or refraining`
  line `from voting, or inducing or attempting to induce any elector to vote or refrain from voting, or`
  line `any candidate to withdraw or not to withdraw his candidature.`
  line
  line `"Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, the term "gratification" is not restricted to`
  line `pecuniary gratification or gratifications estimable in money and it includes all forms of entertainment`
  line `and all forms of employment for reward but it does not include the payment of any expenses bona`
  line `fide incurred at, or for the purpose of, any election.`
  line
  line `(2) Undue influence, that is to say, any direct or indirect interference or attempt to interfere on the`
  line `part of the candidate or his agent, or of any other person with the consent of the candidate or his agent`
  line `with the free exercise of any electoral right:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of this clause any such person as is referred`
  line `to therein who--`
  line
  line `(i) threatens any candidate or any elector, or any person in whom a candidate or an elector is`
  line `interested, with injury of any kind including social ostracism and ex-communication or expulsion`
  line `from any caste or community; or`
  line
  line `(ii) induces or attempts to induce a candidate or an elector to believe that he, or any person in`
  line `whom he is interested, will become or will be rendered an object of divine displeasure or spiritual`
  line `censure, shall be deemed to interfere with the free exercise of the electoral right of such candidate`
  line `or elector within the meaning of this clause;`
  line
  line `(b) a declaration of public policy, or a promise of public action, or the mere exercise of a legal right`
  line `without intent to interfere with an electoral right shall not be deemed to interfere within the meaning of`
  line `this clause.`
  line
  line `(3) The appeal by a candidate or his agent or by any other person with the consent of a candidate or`
  line `his agent to vote or refrain from voting for any person on the ground of his religion, race, caste,`
  line `community or language or the use of, or appeal to religious symbols or the use of, or appeal to, national`
  line `symbols, such as national flag or the national emblem for the furtherance of the prospects of the election`
  line `of that candidate or for prejudicially affecting the election of any candidate.`
  line
  line `(4) The promotion of, or attempt to promote, feelings of enmity or hatred between different classes of`
  line `the citizens of India on grounds of religion, race, caste, community or language, by a candidate or his`
  line `agent or any other person with the consent of a candidate or his agent for the furtherance of the prospects`
  line `of the election of that candidate or for prejudicially affecting the election of any candidate.`
  line
  line `(5) The publication by a candidate or his agent or by any other person, with the consent of a candidate`
  line `or his agent, of any statement of fact which is false, and which he either believes to be false or does not`
  line `believe to be true, in relation to the personal character or conduct of any candidate, or in relation to the`
  line `candidature, or withdrawal of any candidate, being a statement reasonably calculated to prejudice the`
  line `prospects of that candidate's election.`
  line
  line `(6) The hiring or procuring, whether on payment or otherwise, of any vehicle or vessel by a candidate`
  line `or his agent or by any other person with the consent of a candidate or his agent or the use of such vehicle`
  line `or vessel for the free conveyance of any elector other than the candidate himself, the members of his`
  line `family or his agent to or from any polling station or place fixed for the poll:`
  line
  line `Provided that the hiring of a vehicle or vessel by any elector or by several electors at their joint costs`
  line `for the purpose of conveying him or them to and from any such polling station or place fixed for the poll`
  line `shall not be deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause if the vehicle or vessel so hired is a vehicle`
  line `or vessel not propelled by mechanical power:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the use of any public transport vehicle or vessel or any tramcar or railway`
  line `carriage by any elector at his own cost for the purpose of going to or coming from any such polling`
  line `station or place fixed for the poll shall not be deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, the expression "vehicle" means any vehicle used or capable of being`
  line `used for the purpose of road transport, whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise and whether`
  line `used for drawing other vehicles or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(7) The obtaining or procuring or abetting or attempting to obtain or procure by a candidate or his`
  line `agent or, by any other person with the consent of a candidate or his agent, any assistance other than the`
  line `giving of vote for the furtherance of the prospects of that candidate's election, from any person in the`
  line `service of the Government or the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person, in the service of the Government or the Board in the discharge or`
  line `purported discharge of his official duty, makes any arrangements or provides any facilities or does any`
  line `other act or thing, for, to, or in relation to, any candidate or his agent or any other person acting with the`
  line `consent of the candidate or his agent whether by reason of the office held by the candidate or for any`
  line `other reason, such arrangements, facilities or act or thing shall not be deemed to be assistance for the`
  line `furtherance of the prospects of that candidate's election.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expression "agent" includes any person who is held to have acted`
  line `as an agent in connection with the election with the consent of the candidate.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (17155)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules regulating elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17155&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, either generally or`
  line `specially for any cantonment or group of cantonments, after previous publication, make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act to regulate all or any of the following matters for the purpose of the holding of elections`
  line `under this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the division of a cantonment into wards;`
  line
  line `(b) the determination of the number of members to be elected by each ward;`
  line
  line `(c) the preparation, revision and final publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(d) the reservation of wards for election of the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and`
  line women;
  line
  line `(e) the registration of electors, the nomination of candidates, the time and manner of holding`
  line `elections and the method by which votes shall be recorded;`
  line
  line `(f) the authority which may be an officer of the State Government by which and the manner in`
  line `which disputes relating to electoral rolls or arising out of elections shall be decided, and the powers`
  line `and duties of such authority and the circumstances in which such authority may declare a casual`
  line `vacancy to have been created or any candidate to have been elected;`
  line
  line `(g) the fee to be paid for admission and consideration of any application relating to election or`
  line `election disputes;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter relating to elections or election disputes in respect of which the Central`
  line `Government is empowered to make rules under this Chapter or in respect of which this Act makes no`
  line `provision or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (17156)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Member not to vote on matter in which he is interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17156&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of a Board shall vote`
  line `at a meeting of the Board or of any Committee of the Board on any question relating to his own conduct`
  line `or vote or take part in any discussion on any matter, other than a matter affecting generally the inhabitants`
  line `of the cantonment, which affects his own pecuniary interest or the valuation of any property in respect of`
  line `which he is directly or indirectly interested, or of any property of or for which he is a manager or agent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any member of the Board present at the meeting of the Board or any committee of the`
  line `Board believes that the person presiding over such meeting has pecuniary or other interest in any matter`
  line `under discussion and moves a motion to that effect, the person so presiding--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not be entitled to vote on such motion, and`
  line
  line `(b) shall, if such motion is carried, absent himself from the meeting during such discussion.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (17157)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Liability of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17157&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every member of a Board shall be liable for the loss, waste or`
  line `misapplication of any money or other property belonging to, vested in, or entrusted to the management of,`
  line `the Board if such loss, waste or misapplication is a direct consequence of his neglect or misconduct while`
  line `such member; and a suit for compensation for the same may be instituted against him either by the Board`
  line `or by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (17158)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Removal of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17158&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may remove from a Board any member`
  line `thereof, who--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes or is found to have been at the time of his election or nomination subject to any of`
  line `the disqualifications specified in sub-section (2) of section 28 or in section 29; or`
  line
  line `(b) has absented himself for more than three consecutive meetings or three months (whichever is`
  line `later) of the Board and is unable to explain such absence to the satisfaction of the Board.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the aforesaid period of three consecutive months, no account shall`
  line `be taken of any period of absence with the leave of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) has knowingly contravened the provisions of section 32; or`
  line
  line `(d) being a legal practitioner, acts or appears on behalf of any other person against the Board in`
  line `any legal proceeding or against the Government in any such proceeding relating to any matter in`
  line `which the Board is or has been concerned or acts or appears on behalf of any person in any criminal`
  line `proceeding instituted by or on behalf of the Board against such person; or`
  line
  line `(e) has himself done or aided or abetted encroachments and illegal constructions on defence land`
  line `in contravention of the provisions of this Act and the rules and bye-laws made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may remove from a Board any member who, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, has so abused in any manner his position as a member of the Board as to render his`
  line `continuance as a member detrimental to the public interests.`
  line
  line `(3) The General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command may, on receipt of a report from the`
  line `Officer Commanding the station remove from a Board any military officer nominated as a member of the`
  line `Board who is, in the opinion of the Officer Commanding the station, unable to discharge his duties as a`
  line `member of the Board and has failed to resign his office.`
  line
  line `(4) No member shall be removed from a Board under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of this`
  line `section unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against his removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (17159)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Consequences of removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17159&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member removed under clause (b) of sub-section (1) or under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 34 shall, if otherwise qualified, be eligible for re-election or re-nomination.`
  line
  line `(2) A member removed under clause (c) or clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 34 shall not be`
  line `eligible for re-election or nomination for the period during which, but for such removal, he would have`
  line `continued in office.`
  line
  line `(3) A member removed under sub-section (2) of section 34 shall not be eligible for re-election or`
  line `nomination until the expiry of three years from the date of his removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (17160)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Member of the Board to be deemed a public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17160&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Board shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and`
  line `clause (c) of section 2 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (17161)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Disqualification of person as an employee of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17161&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who has directly or`
  line `indirectly by himself or his partner any share or interest in a contract with, by or on behalf of a Board, or`
  line `in any employment under, by or on behalf of a Board, otherwise than as an employee of the Board, shall`
  line `become or remain an employee of such Board.`
  line
  line `(2) An employee of a Board who knowingly acquires or continues to have directly or indirectly by`
  line `himself or his partner any share or interest in a contract with, by or on behalf of the Board or, in any`
  line `employment under, by or on behalf of, the Board, otherwise than as an employee of the Board, shall be`
  line `deemed to have committed an offence under section 168 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to any share or interest in any contract with, by or on behalf of,`
  line `or employment under, by or on behalf of a Board if the same is a share in a company contracting with, or`
  line `employed by, or on behalf of, the Board or is a share or interest acquired or retained with the permission`
  line `of the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command in any lease or sale to, or purchase by the`
  line `Board of land or building or in any agreement for the same.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person applying for employment as an employee of a Board shall, if he is related by blood`
  line `or marriage to any member of the Board or to any person not being a lower grade employee, in receipt of`
  line `remuneration from the Board, notify the fact and the nature of such relationship to the appointing`
  line `authority before the appointment is made, and if he has failed to do so, his appointment shall be invalid`
  line `but without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (17162)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Cantonment employee to be deemed a public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17162&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Every officer or employee, permanent`
  line `or temporary of a Board shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and clause (c) of section 2 of the Prevention of Corruption Act,`
  line `1988 (49 of 1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (17163)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17163&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall meet at least once in a month to transact its business on such`
  line `day as may be fixed by the President and in his absence by the Vice-President, and its notice shall be`
  line `given in such manner as may be provided in the regulations made by the Board under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, whenever he thinks fit, and shall, upon a requisition in writing by not less than`
  line `one-fourth of the members of the Board, convene a special meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Any meeting may be adjourned until the next or any subsequent day, and an adjourned meeting`
  line `may be further adjourned in like manner but not more than twice except in case of a public emergency.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (17164)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Business to be transcted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17164&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any regulation made by the Board under this Chapter,`
  line `any business may be transacted at any meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that no business relating to the imposition, abolition or modification of any tax shall be`
  line `transacted at a meeting unless notice of the same and of the date fixed there for has been sent to each`
  line `member not less than seven days before that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (17165)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title Quorum.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17165&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a meeting of the Board`
  line `shall be one-half of the number of members of the Board holding the office:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the number of members of the Board holding office at a particular time is an odd`
  line `number, the quorum shall be one-half of the number obtained by adding one to the number of such`
  line members.
  line
  line `(2) If a quorum is not present, the President or in his absence, the Vice-President or in the absence of`
  line `both, the Member-Secretary shall adjourn the meeting and the business which would have been brought`
  line `before the original meeting if there had been a quorum present thereat shall be brought before, and may`
  line `be transacted at, an adjourned meeting, whether there is a quorum present or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (17166)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17166&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of--`
  line
  line `(a) both the President and the Vice-President from any meeting of a Board in which there is more`
  line `than one elected member,`
  line
  line `(b) the President from a meeting of a Board constituted under sub-section (6) of section 12 or`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13,`
  line
  line `the members present shall elect one from among their own members to preside.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (17167)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title Minutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17167&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The minutes of the proceedings of each meeting shall be recorded in a book and`
  line `shall be signed by the person presiding over the meeting and the Chief Executive Officer, before the close`
  line `of the meeting and shall, at such times and in such place as may be fixed by the Board, be open to`
  line `inspection free of charge by any inhabitant of the cantonment and its authenticated copies may be made`
  line `available to him on request, at a nominal cost to be decided by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Copies of the minutes shall, as soon as possible after each meeting, be forwarded for information`
  line `to every Member of the Board, the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, the District`
  line `Magistrate and the Defence Estate Officer and in cantonments where Navy or Air Force stations are`
  line `located copies of the minutes shall be forwarded for information to the Command Headquarters of the`
  line `Navy or, as the case may be, the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (17168)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Meetings to be public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17168&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every meeting of a Board shall be open to the public unless in any case`
  line `the person presiding over the meeting, for reasons to be recorded in the minutes, otherwise directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (17169)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Method of deciding questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17169&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) All questions coming before a meeting shall be decided by`
  line `the majority of the votes of the members present and voting.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of an quality of votes, the person presiding over the meeting, shall have a second or`
  line `casting vote.`
  line
  line `(3) The dissent of any member from any decision of the Board shall, if the member so requests, be`
  line `entered in the minutes, together with a short statement of the ground for such dissent.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (17170)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Civil area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17170&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in Official Gazette, declare the`
  line `civil area, in a cantonment, which is inhabited largely by civil population to be the civil area for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may in consultation with the Board undertake, as and when required and`
  line `shall undertake after every census, a review of the boundaries of the civil area in each cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (17171)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Committees for civil areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17171&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board constituted under section 12 in a cantonment shall`
  line `appoint a committee consisting of the elected members of the Board, the Health Officer and the Executive`
  line `Engineer for the administration of the civil area in the cantonment as notified under section 46 of this Act`
  line `and may delegate its powers and duties to such committee in the manner provided in clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 48.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-President of the Board shall be the Chairman of the committee appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The powers, duties and functions of the Board under sub-section (1) of section 137, section143,`
  line `section 147, section 149 and section 262 shall be exercised or discharged in respect of a civil area by the`
  line `civil area committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Health Officer dissents from any decision arrived at by the committee under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 137, section 143, section 147 and section 149 on health grounds, the matter may`
  line `be referred to the Board by the President for decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (17172)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17172&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may make regulations consistent with this Act and`
  line `with the rules made thereunder to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and place of its meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which notice of the meeting shall be given;`
  line
  line `(c) the conduct of proceedings at meetings and the adjournments of meetings;`
  line
  line `(d) the custody of the common seal of the Board and the purposes for which it shall be used; and`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment of committees for any purpose and the determination of all matters relating to`
  line `the constitution and procedure of such committees, and the delegation to such committees, subject to`
  line `any conditions which the Board thinks fit to impose, of any of the powers or duties of the Board`
  line `under this Act other than a power to make regulations or bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation made under clause (e) of sub-section (1) shall take effect until it has been approved`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No regulation made under this section shall take effect until it has been published in such manner`
  line `as the Central Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (17173)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Joint action with other local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17173&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) join with any other local authority--`
  line
  line `(i) in appointing a joint committee for any purpose in which they are jointly interested and in`
  line `appointing a chairman of such committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) in delegation to such committee power to frame terms binding on the Board and such`
  line `other local authority as to the construction and future maintenance of any joint work or to`
  line `exercise any power which might be exercised by the Board or by such other local authority; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in making regulations for regulating the proceedings of any such committeer relating to`
  line `the purposes for which it has been appointed; or`
  line
  line `(b) with the previous sanction of the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, and`
  line `the State Government concerned, enter into an agreement with any other local authority regarding the`
  line `levy of any tax or toll whereby the said tax or toll respectively leviable by the Board and by such`
  line `other local authority may be levied together instead of separately within the limits of the area`
  line `hereafter in this section referred to as the aggregate area subject to the control of the Board and such`
  line `other local authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If any difference of opinion arises between any Board and other local authority acting together`
  line `under this section, the decision thereon of the Central Government or of an officer appointed by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) When any agreement such as is referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) has been entered into,`
  line then--
  line
  line `(a) where the agreement relates to octroi or terminal tax or toll, the party to the agreement (the`
  line `Board, or as the case may be, such other local authority) which is specified in this behalf in the`
  line agreement,--
  line
  line `(i) shall have the same powers to establish octroi limits and octroi stations and places for the`
  line `collection of octroi, terminal tax and toll within the aggregate area as it has within the area`
  line `ordinarily subject to its control;`
  line
  line `(ii) shall have the same powers of collecting such octroi, terminal tax or toll in the aggregate`
  line `area and the provisions of any enactment in force relating to the levy of such octroi, terminal tax`
  line `or toll by it shall apply in the same manner as if the aggregate area were comprised within the`
  line `area ordinarily subject to its control;`
  line
  line `(b) the total of the collection of such octroi, tax or toll made in the aggregate area and the costs`
  line `thereby incurred shall be divided between the cantonment fund and the fund subject to the control of`
  line `such other local authority, in such proportion, as may have been determined by the agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (17174)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Report on administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17174&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall, as soon as may be after the close of the`
  line `financial year and not later than the date fixed in this behalf by the Central Government, submit to the`
  line `Central Government through the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, a report on the`
  line `administration of the cantonment during the preceding financial year, in such form and containing such`
  line `details as the Central Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The comments, if any, of the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, on such`
  line `report shall be communicated by him to the Board which shall be allowed a reasonable time to furnish a`
  line `reply thereto, and the comments together with the reply, if any, shall be forwarded to the Central`
  line `Government along with the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (17175)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of Central Government to require production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17175&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government or such officer or authority as may be authorised by the Central Government in this behalf`
  line `may at any time require a Board--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce any record, correspondence, plan or other document in its possession or under its`
  line control;
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any return, plan, estimate, statement, account or statistics relating to its proceedings,`
  line `duties or works;`
  line
  line `(c) to furnish or obtain and furnish any report.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (17176)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17176&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the`
  line `Command or the Director General or the Principal Director, may depute any person in the service of the`
  line `Government to inspect or examine any department of the office of, or any service or work undertaken by,`
  line `or thing belonging to, a Board, and to report thereon, and the Board and its officers and employees shall`
  line `be bound to afford the person so deputed access at all reasonable times to the premises and property of the`
  line `Board and to all records, accounts and other documents the inspection of which he may consider`
  line `necessary to enable him to discharge his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (17177)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power to call for documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17177&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or the`
  line `Principal Director, may, by order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) call for any book or document in the possession or under the control of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) require the Board to furnish such statements, accounts, reports and copies of documents`
  line `relating to its proceedings, duties or works as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (17178)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to require execution of work, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17178&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If, on receipt of any information or report obtained`
  line `under section 51 or section 52 or section 53, the Central Government or the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or the Director General or the Principal Director is of opinion-`
  line
  line `(a) that any duty imposed on a Board by or under this Act has not been performed or has been`
  line `performed in an imperfect, inefficient or unsuitable manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) that adequate financial provision has not been made for the performance of any such duty,`
  line
  line `it or he may direct the Board, within such period as it or he thinks fit, to make arrangements to its or his`
  line `satisfaction for the proper performance of the duty, or as the case may be, to make financial provision to`
  line `its or his satisfaction for the performance of the duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that unless in the opinion of the Central Government or the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or the Director General or the Principal Director, as the case may`
  line `be, the immediate execution of such order is necessary, it or he shall, before making any direction under`
  line `this section, give the Board an opportunity of showing cause why such direction should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (17179)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to provide for enforcement of direction under section 54.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17179&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `If, within the period fixed`
  line `by a direction made under section 54, any action the taking of which has been directed under that section`
  line `has not been duly taken, the Central Government or the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the`
  line `Command or the Director General, or the Principal Director, as the case may be, may make arrangements`
  line `for the taking of such action, and may direct that all expenses connected therewith shall be defrayed out`
  line `of the cantonment fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (17180)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to override decision of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17180&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the President dissents from any decision of the`
  line `Board which he considers prejudicial to the health, welfare, discipline or security of the Forces in the`
  line `cantonment, he may, for reasons to be recorded in the minutes, by order in writing, direct the suspension`
  line `of action thereon for any period not exceeding one month and, if he does so, shall forthwith refer the`
  line `matter to the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command.`
  line
  line `(2) If the District Magistrate considers any decision of a Board to be prejudicial to the public health,`
  line `safety or convenience, he may, after giving notice in writing of his intention to the Board, refer the matter to the Central Government, and pending the disposal of the reference to the Central Government no action`
  line `shall be taken on the decision.`
  line
  line `(3) If any Magistrate who is a member of a Board, being present at a meeting, dissents from any`
  line `decision which he considers prejudicial to the public health, safety or convenience, he may, for reasons to`
  line `be recorded in the minutes and after giving notice in writing of his intention to the President, report the`
  line `matter to the District Magistrate; and the President shall, on receipt of such notice, direct the suspension`
  line `of action on the decision for a period sufficient to allow of a communication being made to the District`
  line `Magistrate and of his taking proceedings as provided in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) If the Chief Executive Officer considers any decision of the Board taken at a meeting, to be in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules, regulations or bye-laws made there under and the`
  line `general guidelines issued by the Central Government from time to time in this regard, he may, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing and after informing the President in this behalf, forthwith refer the matter to the`
  line `Principal Director who shall if considered appropriate direct the suspension of action on the said decision`
  line `for a period not exceeding one month.`
  line
  line `(5) The Principal Director shall, for reasons to be recorded in writing on the reference made under`
  line `sub-section (4), refer the matter to the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command along with`
  line `recommendation on whether or not the said decision of the Board should be revoked and inform the`
  line `matter to Director General Defence Estates.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (17181)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Central Government to review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17181&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, at any time, review`
  line `any decision or order of the Board or the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, and pass`
  line `such orders thereon as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is proposed to modify a decision or order of the Board reasonable opportunity`
  line `shall be given to the Board to show cause why the decision or order in question should not be modified.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (17182)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, on reference under section 56 or otherwise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17182&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, may at any time--`
  line
  line `(a) direct that any matter or any specific proposal other than one which has been referred to the`
  line `Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 56 be considered or reconsidered by the Board;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) direct the suspension, for such period as may be stated in the order, of action on any decision`
  line `of a Board, other than a decision which has been referred to him under sub-section (1) of section 56,`
  line `and thereafter cancel the suspension or after giving the Board a reasonable opportunity of show in`
  line `cause why such direction should not be made, direct that the decision shall not be carried into effect`
  line `or that it shall be carried into effect with such modifications as he may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) When any decision of a Board has been referred to him under sub-sections (1) and (4) of`
  line `section 56, the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, may, by order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) cancel the order given by the President directing the suspension of action; or`
  line
  line `(b) extend the duration of the order for such period as he thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(c) after giving the Board a reasonable opportunity of showing cause why such direction should`
  line `not be made, direct that the decision shall not be carried into effect or that it shall be carried into`
  line `effect by the Board with such modifications as he may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (17183)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power of Central Government on a reference made under section 56.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17183&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `decision of a Board has been referred to the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 56, the`
  line `Central Government may, after consulting the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, by`
  line `order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) direct that no action be taken on the decision; or`
  line
  line `(b) direct that the decision be carried into effect either without modification or with such`
  line `modifications as it may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (17184)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Supersession of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17184&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the Central Government, any Board is not`
  line `competent to perform or persistently makes default in the performance of the duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under this Act or otherwise by law, or exceeds or abuses its powers, the Central Government may by an`
  line `order published, together with the statement of the reasons there for, in the Official Gazette, declare the`
  line `Board to be incompetent or in default or to have exceeded or abused its powers, as the case may be, and`
  line `supersede it for such period as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Board shall be superseded unless a reasonable opportunity has been given to it to`
  line `show cause against the supersession.`
  line
  line `(2) When a Board is superseded by an order under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) all members of the Board shall, on such date as may be specified in the order, vacate their`
  line `offices as such members but without prejudice to their eligibility for election or nomination under`
  line `clause (c);`
  line
  line `(b) during the supersession of the Board, all powers and duties conferred and imposed upon the`
  line `Board by or under this Act shall be exercised and performed by the Officer Commanding the station,`
  line `or by such officer as may be authorised by the Central Government, subject to such reservation if any,`
  line `as the Central Government may prescribe in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(c) before the expiry of the period of supersession elections shall be held and nominations made`
  line `for the purpose of reconstituting the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (17185)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Validity of proceedings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17185&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of a Board or of any committee of a`
  line `Board shall be invalid by reason only of the existence of a vacancy in the Board or committee.`
  line
  line `(2) No disqualification or defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as the`
  line `President or a member of a Board or of any such committee shall vitiate any act or proceeding of the`
  line `Board or committee if the majority of the persons present at the time of the act being done or the`
  line `proceeding being taken were duly qualified members thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Any document or minutes which purport to be the record of the proceedings of a Board or any`
  line `committee of a Board shall, if made and signed substantially in the manner prescribed for the making and`
  line `signing of the record of such proceedings, be presumed to be a correct record of the proceedings of a duly`
  line `convened meeting, held by a duly constituted Board or committee, as the case may be, whereof all the`
  line `members were duly qualified.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (17186)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Duties of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17186&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every Board, so far as the funds at its disposal permit, to`
  line `make reasonable provision within the cantonment for--`
  line
  line `(i) lighting streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(ii) watering streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(iii) cleansing streets, public places and drains, abating nuisances and removing noxious`
  line vegetation;
  line
  line `(iv) regulating offensive, dangerous or obnoxious trades, callings and practices;`
  line
  line `(v) removing, on the ground of public safety, health or convenience, undesirable obstructions and`
  line `projections in streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(vi) securing or removing dangerous buildings and places;`
  line
  line `(vii) acquiring, maintaining, changing and regulating places for the disposal of the dead;`
  line
  line `(viii) constructing, altering and maintaining streets, culverts, bridges, causeways, markets,`
  line `slaughter-houses, latrines, privies, urinals, drains, drainage works and sewerage works and regulating`
  line `their use;`
  line
  line `(ix) planting and maintaining trees on roadsides and other public places;`
  line
  line `(x) providing or arranging for a sufficient supply of potable water, where such supply does not`
  line `exist, guarding from pollution water used for human consumption, and preventing polluted water`
  line `from being so used;`
  line
  line `(xi) registering births and deaths;`
  line
  line `(xii) preventing and checking spread of dangerous diseases; establishing and maintaining a`
  line `system of public vaccination and inoculation for the said objective;`
  line
  line `(xiii) establishing and maintaining or supporting public hospitals, maternity and child welfare`
  line `centres and dispensaries, and providing public medical relief;`
  line
  line `(xiv) establishing and maintaining or assisting primary schools;`
  line
  line `(xv) rendering assistance in extinguishing fires, and protecting light and property when fire`
  line occurs;
  line
  line `(xvi) maintaining and developing the value of property vested in, or entrusted to, the`
  line `management of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xvii) establishing and maintaining civil defence services;`
  line
  line `(xviii) preparing and implementing town planning schemes;`
  line
  line `(xix) preparing and implementing plans for economic development and social justice;`
  line
  line `(xx) naming and numbering of streets and premises;`
  line
  line `(xxi) according or refusing permission to erect or re-erect building;`
  line
  line `(xxii) organising, promoting or supporting cultural and sports activities;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) celebrating Independence Day and Republic Day and incurring expenditure thereon;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) fulfilling any other obligation imposed upon it by or under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (17187)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power to manage property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17187&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `A Board may, subject to any conditions imposed by the Central`
  line `Government, manage any property entrusted to its management by the Central Government on such terms`
  line `as to the sharing of rents and profits accruing from such property as may be determined by rule made`
  line `under section 346.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (17188)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Discretionary functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17188&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may, within the cantonment, make provision`
  line for--
  line
  line `(i) laying out in areas, whether previously built upon or not, new streets, and acquiring land for`
  line `that purpose and for the construction of buildings, and compounds of buildings, to about on such`
  line streets;
  line
  line `(ii) constructing, establishing or maintaining public parks, gardens, offices, dairies, bathing or`
  line `washing places, drinking fountains, tanks, wells and other works of public utility;`
  line
  line `(iii) reclaiming unhealthy localities;`
  line
  line `(iv) furthering educational objects by measures other than the establishment and maintenance of`
  line `primary schools;`
  line
  line `(v) setting up or supporting higher schools, colleges and vocational, professional and special`
  line education;
  line
  line `(vi) constructing, and maintaining works and structures, including rainwater harvesting, for`
  line `providing supply of water for public and private purposes;`
  line
  line `(vii) constituting, maintaining and managing supply and distribution of electricity, including by`
  line `exploiting non-conventional energy sources, to public and private premises;`
  line
  line `(viii) taking a census and granting rewards for information which may tend to secure the correct`
  line `registration of vital statistics;`
  line
  line `(ix) making a survey;`
  line
  line `(x) giving relief on the occurrence of local epidemics, floods, famines or other natural calamities`
  line `by the establishment or maintenance of relief work or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(xi) securing or assisting to secure suitable places for the carrying on of any offensive dangerous`
  line `or obnoxious trade, calling or occupation;`
  line
  line `(xii) establishing and maintaining a farm or other place for the disposal of sewage;`
  line
  line `(xiii) constructing, subsidising or guaranteeing tramways or other means of locomotion, and`
  line `electric lighting or electric power work;`
  line
  line `(xiv) establishing and maintaining cattle pounds;`
  line
  line `(xv) arranging for civic reception with prior approval of the Officer Commanding the Station;`
  line
  line `(xvi) providing housing accommodation for any class of inhabitants;`
  line
  line `(xvii) conservation and maintenance of ancient and historical monuments, archaeological sites`
  line `and remains or place of public importance in the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(xviii) developing land resources under the management of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xix) preparing and implementing group housing schemes;`
  line
  line `(xx) establishing and undertaking remunerative projects;`
  line
  line `(xxi) developing small-scale and cottage industries;`
  line
  line `(xxii) developing expertise in different areas of urban governance and local self-government to`
  line `and able to provide consultancy to other Municipal and Development Authorities;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) adopting any measure, other than a measure specified in section 62 or in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this section likely to promote the safety, health or convenience of the inhabitants of the`
  line cantonment;
  line
  line `(xxiv) establishing and maintaining or supporting libraries, museums, art galleries, botanical or`
  line `zoological collections;`
  line
  line `(xxv) establishing and maintaining or supporting stadia, gymnasia, akharas and places for sports`
  line `and games;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) establishing theatres and cinemas;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) organising and managing fairs and exhibitions;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) constructing and maintaining:--`
  line
  line `(a) rest-houses;`
  line
  line `(b) poor-houses;`
  line
  line `(c) infirmaries;`
  line
  line `(d) children's home;`
  line
  line `(e) houses for deaf and dumb and for disabled and handicapped children;`
  line
  line `(f ) shelters for destitute and disabled persons;`
  line
  line `(g) asylums for persons of unsound mind;`
  line
  line `(h) old age homes;`
  line
  line `(i) working women's hostels;`
  line
  line `(xxix) establishing and managing chemical or bacteriological laboratories for the examination or`
  line `analysis of water, food and drugs for the detection of diseases or research connected with the public`
  line `health or medical relief;`
  line
  line `(xxx) providing relief to destitute and disabled persons;`
  line
  line `(xxxi) establishing and maintaining veterinary hospitals;`
  line
  line `(xxxii) constructing and maintaining warehouses and godowns;`
  line
  line `(xxxiii) constructing and managing garages, sheds and stands for vehicles and cattle sheds;`
  line
  line `(xxxiv) constructing and managing community halls and convention halls;`
  line
  line `(xxxv) holding seminars, workshops, public debates, and similar activities particularly on issues`
  line `and rules and regulations of civic importance.`
  line
  line `"Explanation".--For the purposes of clause (xvii)--`
  line
  line `(a) "conservation" means the supervision, management and maintenance of a place to retain its`
  line `historical, architectural, aesthetic or cultural significance or of environment and includes the`
  line `protection, improvement, preservation, restoration, reconstruction and adoption or a combination of`
  line `more than one of these activities, and the use of such place in a way that ensures the social as well as`
  line `economic benefits;`
  line
  line `(b) "ancient and historical monuments, archaeological sites and remains or place of public`
  line `importance" include buildings, arte facts, structures, areas, or precincts of historical or aesthetical or`
  line `educational or scientific or cultural or environmental significance, and those natural features of`
  line `environmental signifcance or scenic beauty, as may be declared by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board may, either within or outside the cantonment, make provision for the doing of anything`
  line `on which expenditure is declared by the Central Government, or by the Board with the sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, to be an appropriate charge on the cantonment fund or the cantonment development`
  line fund.
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (17189)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of expenditure of educational, health and other purposes outside the cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17189&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line A
  line `Board may make provision subject to availability of funds for--`
  line
  line `(i) educational objects in a cantonment;`
  line
  line `(ii) the objectives of public health and medical care;`
  line
  line `(iii) works relating to water-supply, drainage and lighting;`
  line
  line `(iv) the preservation, improvement and upgradation of environment,`
  line
  line `outside the cantonment, if it is satisfied that the interests of the residents of the cantonment will be served`
  line thereby.
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (17190)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `General power of taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17190&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, impose the following taxes for the purposes of this Act:--`
  line
  line `(a) property tax; and`
  line
  line `(b) tax on trades, professions callings and employments.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the taxes specified in sub-section (1) the Board may, for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `impose any tax which under any enactment for the time being in force may be imposed in any`
  line `municipality in the State in which the cantonment is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall revise every five years, the rates of taxes imposed under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2):`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall not abolish any tax imposed under this section or vary it to the`
  line `Board's financial disadvantage without the prior sanction of the Central Government and the tax`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (2) shall not exceed the ceiling prescribed in this behalf by clause (2) of`
  line `article 276 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) The taxes specified in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be imposed, assessed and collected in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, rules and the bye-laws made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Any tax imposed under this section shall take effect from the date of its notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette or where any later date is specified in this behalf in the notification, from such later date.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (17191)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Charging of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17191&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall, for the purposes of this Act, charge the following fees,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) licence fee on vehicles and animals;`
  line
  line `(b) licence fee on advertisements other than advertisements in newspapers;`
  line
  line `(c) fee relating to maintenance of property records;`
  line
  line `(d) processing fee on buildings payable along with application for sanction of the building plan;`
  line
  line `(e) licence fee on entry of vehicles;`
  line
  line `(f) betterment fee on the increase in land value caused by the execution of any development work;`
  line and
  line
  line `(g) such other fee which the Board may by regulation specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee charged under clause (g) of this section shall not be less than the cost incurred`
  line `by the Board for or in connection with the specific service to which the fee relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (17192)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Norms of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17192&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the property tax shall be levied`
  line `on lands and buildings in the cantonment and shall consist of not less than ten and not more than thirty`
  line `per cent. of the annual rateable value of lands and buildings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, when fixing the rate at which the property tax shall be levied during any`
  line `year, determine that the rate leviable in respect of lands and buildings or portions of lands and buildings`
  line `in which any particular class of trade or business is carried on shall be higher than the rate determined in`
  line `respect of other lands and buildings or portions of other lands and buildings by an amount not exceeding`
  line `one half of the rate so fixed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the tax may be levied on graduated scale, if the Board so determines.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where any portion of a land or building is liable to a higher rate of the tax such`
  line `portion shall be deemed to be a separate property for the purpose of municipal taxation alone.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (17193)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Framing of preliminary proposals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17193&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `When a resolution has been passed by the Board`
  line `proposing to impose a tax under section 66, the Board shall in the manner prescribed in section 319`
  line `publish a notice specifying--`
  line
  line `(a) the tax which it is proposed to impose;`
  line
  line `(b) the persons or classes of persons to be made liable and the description of the property or other`
  line `taxable thing or circumstance in respect of which they are to be made liable; and`
  line
  line `(c) the rate at which the tax is to be levied.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (17194)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Objections and disposal thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17194&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any inhabitant of the cantonment may, within thirty days`
  line `from the publication of the notice under section 69, submit to the Board an objection in writing to all or`
  line `any of the proposals contained therein and the Board shall take such objection into consideration and pass`
  line `orders there on by special resolution.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the Board decides to abandon its proposals contained in the notice published under`
  line `section 69, it shall submit to the Central Government through the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief,`
  line `the Command, all such proposals along with the objections, if any, received in connection there with`
  line `together with its opinion thereon and any modifications proposed in accordance with such opinion and the`
  line `notice published under the said section.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (17195)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Imposition of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17195&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may authorise the Board to impose the tax either in`
  line `the original form or, if any objection has been submitted, in that form or any such modified form as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (17196)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17196&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that for securing adequate financial provision for the efficient discharge of the`
  line `duties and functions of a Board it is necessary so to do, it may issue directions to the Board requiring it to`
  line `impose within the cantonment area any tax which it is empowered under this Act to impose and which is`
  line `not already imposed within the said area or to enhance any existing tax in such a manner or to such an`
  line `extent as the Central Government considers fit and the Board shall, in accordance with the direction,`
  line `forthwith impose or enhance such tax in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no such directions shall be issued without giving the Board and the inhabitants of the`
  line `cantonment area, an opportunity of showing cause why such directions should not be issued;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Government shall take into consideration any objection which the Board or any`
  line `inhabitant of the cantonment area may make against the imposition or enhancement of such tax;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall not be lawful for the Board to modify or abolish such tax when imposed or enhanced`
  line `without the sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, at any time, cancel or modify any direction issued by it under`
  line `sub-section (1) with effect from such date as may be specified in the direction and on and from the date so`
  line `specified the imposition or enhancement of such tax, shall cease or be modified accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (17197)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Definition of “annual rateable value”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17197&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter, "annual rateable`
  line `value" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of hotels, colleges, schools, hospitals, factories and any other buildings which the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer decides to assess under this clause, one-twentieth of the sum obtained by`
  line `adding the estimated present cost of erecting the building to the estimated value of the land`
  line `appertaining thereto; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of building or land not assessed under clause (a), the gross annual rent for which`
  line `such building exclusive of furniture or machinery therein or such land is actually let or, where the`
  line `building or land is not let or in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer is let for a sum less than its`
  line `fair letting value, might reasonably be expected to let from year to year:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the annual rateable value of any building is, by reason of exceptional`
  line `circumstances, in the opinion of the President Cantonment Board, excessive if calculated in the aforesaid`
  line `manner, the President Cantonment Board may fix the annual rateable value at any less amount which`
  line `appears to him to be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (17198)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Incidence of taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17198&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided in the notification imposing`
  line `the tax, every tax assessed on the annual rateable value of buildings or lands or of both shall be leviable`
  line `primarily upon the actual occupier of the property upon which the said tax is assessed, if he is the owner`
  line `of the buildings or land or holds them on a building or other lease granted by or on behalf of the`
  line `Government or the Board or on a building lease from any person.`
  line
  line `(2) In any other case, the tax shall be primarily leviable as follows, namely :--`
  line
  line `(a) if the property is let, upon the lessor;`
  line
  line `(b) if the property is sub-let, upon the superior lessor;`
  line
  line `(c) if the property is unlet, upon the person in whom the right to let the same vests.`
  line
  line `(3) The liability of the several owners of any building which is, or purports to be, severally owned in`
  line `parts or flats or rooms or separate tenements for the payment of such tax or any installment thereof`
  line `payable during the period of such ownership shall be joint and several.`
  line
  line `(4) On failure to recover any sum due on account of such tax from the person primarily liable, these`
  line `may be recovered from the occupier of any part of the buildings or lands in respect of which the tax is due`
  line `such portion of the sum due as bears to the whole amount due the same ratio which the rent annually`
  line `payable by such occupier bears to the aggregate amount of rent so payable in respect of the whole of the`
  line `said buildings or lands, or to the aggregate amount of the letting value thereof, if any, stated in the`
  line `authenticated assessment list.`
  line
  line `(5) An occupier who makes any payment for which he is not primarily liable under this section shall,`
  line `in the absence of any contract to the contrary, be entitled to be reimbursed by the person primarily liable`
  line `for the payment, and, if so entitled, may deduct the amount so paid from the amount of any rent from time`
  line `to time becoming due from him to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (17199)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17199&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `When a tax assessed on the annual rateable value of buildings or lands or both`
  line `is imposed, the Chief Executive Officer shall cause an assessment list of all buildings or lands in the`
  line `cantonment, or of both, as the case may be, to be prepared in such form and in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may by rule prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (17200)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Revision of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17200&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer shall, at the same time, give public`
  line `notice of a date, not less than one month thereafter, when he shall proceed to consider the valuation and`
  line `assessments entered in the assessment list, and, in all cases in which any property is for the first time`
  line `assessed or the assessment is increased shall also give written notice thereof to the owner and to any`
  line `lessee or occupier of the property.`
  line
  line `(2) Any objection to a valuation or assessment shall be made in writing to the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `before the date fixed in the notice, and shall state in what respect the valuation or assessment is disputed,`
  line `and all objections so made shall be recorded in a register to be kept for the purpose by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The objections shall be inquired into and investigated, and the persons making them shall be`
  line `allowed an opportunity of being heard either in person or by authorised agent by the Chief Executive`
  line Officer.
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (17201)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Authentication of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17201&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) When all objections made under section 76 have been`
  line `disposed of, and the revision of the valuation and assessment has been completed, the assessment list`
  line `shall be authenticated by the signatures of the Chief Executive Officer and the President Cantonment`
  line `Board, who shall, certify that except in the cases if any, in which amendments have been made as shown`
  line `therein no valid objection has been made to the annual rateable value or any other matters entered in the`
  line `said list:`
  line
  line `Provided that whenever the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or the Principal`
  line `Director comes to the conclusion that the assessment lists or any entries therein have not been correctly`
  line `prepared and are prejudicial to the interests of the Board or of the Central Government, they may`
  line `suo moto re-open the said assessment and issue such directions as deemed fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The assessment list so authenticated shall be deposited in the office of the Board, and shall there`
  line `be open, free of charge, during office hours to all owners lessees and occupiers of property comprised`
  line `therein or the authorised agents of such persons, and a public notice that it is so open shall forthwith be`
  line published.
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (17202)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Evidential value of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17202&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such alterations as may thereafter be made in`
  line `the assessment list under the provisions of this Chapter and to the result of any appeal made thereunder,`
  line `the entries in the assessment list authenticated and deposited as provided in section 77 shall be accepted`
  line `as conclusive evidence--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purposes of assessing any tax imposed under this Act, of the annual rateable value or`
  line `other valuation of all buildings and lands to which such entries respectively refer; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purposes of any tax imposed on buildings or lands, of the amount of each such tax`
  line `leviable thereon during the year to which such list relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (17203)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Amendment of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17203&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may after obtaining the`
  line `approval of President Cantonment Board amend the assessment list at any time--`
  line
  line `(a) by inserting or omitting the name of any person whose name ought to have been or ought to`
  line `be inserted or omitted; or`
  line
  line `(b) by inserting or omitting any property which ought to have been or ought to be inserted or`
  line `omitted; or`
  line
  line `(c) by altering the assessment on any property which has been erroneously valued or assessed`
  line `through fraud, accident or mistake whether on the part of administration or assessees; or`
  line
  line `(d) by revaluing or re-assessing any property the value of which has been increased; or`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a tax payable by an occupier, by changing the name of the occupier:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall by reason of any such amendment become liable to pay any tax or`
  line `increase of tax in respect of any period prior to the commencement of the year in which the assessment is`
  line made.
  line
  line `(2) Before making any amendment under sub-section (1) the Chief Executive Officer shall give to any`
  line `person affected by the amendment, notice of not less than one month that he proposes to make the`
  line amendment.
  line
  line `(3) Any person interested in any such amendment may tender an objection to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer in writing before the time fixed in the notice, and shall be allowed an opportunity of being heard`
  line `in support of the same in person or by authorised agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (17204)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Preparation of new assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17204&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer shall prepare a new`
  line `assessment list at least once in every three years, and for this purpose the provisions of sections 75 to 79`
  line `shall apply in like manner as they apply for the purpose of the preparation of an assessment list for the`
  line `first time.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (17205)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Notice of transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17205&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the title of any person primarily liable for the payment of a`
  line `tax on the annual rateable value of any building or land to or over such building or land is transferred, the`
  line `person whose title is transferred and the person to whom the same is transferred shall, within three months`
  line `after the execution of the instrument of transfer or after its registration, if it is registered, or after the`
  line `transfer is effected, if no instrument is executed, give notice of such transfer to the Chief Executive`
  line Officer.
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the death of any person primarily liable as aforesaid, the person on whom the title`
  line `of the deceased devolves shall give notice of such devolution to the Chief Executive Officer within`
  line `six months from the death of the deceased.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice to be given under this section shall be in such form as may be determined by rules`
  line `made under section 346, and the transferee or other person on whom the title devolves shall, if so`
  line `required, be bound to produce before the Chief Executive Officer any documents evidencing the transfer`
  line `or devolution.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person who makes a transfer as aforesaid without giving such notice to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer shall continue liable for the payment of all taxes assessed on the property transferred until he`
  line `gives notice or until the transfer has been recorded in the registers of the Board, but nothing in this section`
  line `shall be held to affect the liability of the transferee for the payment of the said tax.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Executive Officer shall record every transfer or devolution of title notified to him`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in the assessment list and other tax registers of the Board.`
  line
  line `(6) Any failure to comply with the provisions contained in sub-sections (1) to (3) shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (17206)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Notice of erection of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17206&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any building is erected or re-erected within the meaning`
  line `of section 235, the owner shall give notice thereof to the Chief Executive Officer within thirty days from`
  line `the date of its completion or occupation, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person failing to give the notice required by sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand or ten times the amount of the tax payable on the said building, as`
  line `erected or re-erected, as the case may be, in respect of a period of three months, whichever is greater.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (17207)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Demolition, etc., of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17207&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `If any building is wholly or partly demolished or destroyed or`
  line `otherwise deprived of value, the Board may, on the application in writing of the owner or occupier, remit`
  line `or refund such portion of any tax assessed on the annual rateable value thereof as it thinks fit but no`
  line `remission or refund shall take effect in respect of any period commencing more than two months before`
  line `the delivery of such application.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (17208)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Remission of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17208&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `In a cantonment when any building or land has remained vacant and`
  line `unproductive of rent for sixty or more consecutive days the Chief Executive Officer shall remit or refund,`
  line `as the case may be, one-half of such portion of any tax assessed on the annual rateable value thereof as`
  line `may be proportionate to the number of days during which the said building or land has remained vacant`
  line `and unproductive of rent:--`
  line
  line `Provided that in any cantonment which the Central Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, has declared to be a hill cantonment and in respect of which the Central Government by the same`
  line `or a like notification has declared a portion of the year to be the season for the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) when any building or land is leased for occupation through the season only, but the rent`
  line `charged is the full annual rent, no remission or refund shall be admissible under this section in respect`
  line `of anytime outside the season during which the building or land remains vacant;`
  line
  line `(b) when such building or land has remained vacant and unproductive of rent, in respect of any`
  line `time, not being less than sixty consecutive days during which within the season, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer shall remit or refund one-half of such portion of any tax assessed on the annual rateable value`
  line `thereof as bears to the whole of the tax so assessed the same proportion as the number of days during`
  line `which the building or land has remained vacant and unproductive of rent bears to the total length of`
  line `the season.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (17209)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to require entry in assessment list of details of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17209&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of`
  line `obtaining a partial remission or refund of tax, the owner of a building composed of separate tenements`
  line `may request the Chief Executive Officer at the time of the assessment of the building, to enter in the`
  line `assessment list, in addition to the annual rateable value of the whole building, a note recording in detail`
  line `the annual rateable value of each separate tenement.`
  line
  line `(2) When any tenement, the annual value of which has been thus separately recorded, has remained`
  line `vacant and unproductive of rent for sixty or more consecutive days one-half of such portion of any tax`
  line `assessed on the annual rateable value of the whole building shall be remitted or refunded as would have`
  line `been remitted or refunded if the tenement had been separately assessed.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (17210)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Notice to be given of the circumstances in which remission or refund is claimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17210&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line No
  line `remission or refund under section 84 or section 85 shall be made unless notice in writing of the fact that`
  line `the building, land or tenement has become vacant and unproductive of rent, has been given to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer and no remission or refund shall take effect in respect of any period commencing more`
  line `than fifteen days before the delivery of such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (17211)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `What buildings, etc., are to be deemed vacant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17211&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of sections 84 and 85 no`
  line `building, tenement or land shall be deemed vacant if maintained as a resort or town or country house or be`
  line `deemed unproductive of rent if let to a tenant who has a continuing right of occupation thereof, whether`
  line `he is in actual occupation or not.`
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving all facts entitling any person to claim relief under section 83 or section 84`
  line `or section 85 shall be upon him.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (17212)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Notice to be given of every occupation of vacant building or house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17212&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of any`
  line `building, tenement or land in respect of which a remission or refund of tax has been given under`
  line `section 84 or section 85 shall give notice of the re-occupation of such building, tenement or land within`
  line `fifteen days of such re-occupation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any owner failing to give the notice required by sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than twice the amount of the tax payable on such building, tenement or land in`
  line `respect of the period during which it has been re-occupied and which may extend to two thousand five`
  line `hundred rupees, or to ten times the amount of the said tax, whichever sum is greater.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (17213)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Tax on buildings and land to be a charge thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17213&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `A tax assessed on the annual rateable`
  line `value of any building or land shall, subject to the prior payment of the land-revenue, if any, due to the`
  line `Government thereon, be a first charge upon the building or land.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (17214)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Inspection of imported goods, octroi, terminal tax and toll, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17214&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Every person bringing or`
  line `receiving any goods, vehicles or animals within the limits of any cantonment in which octroi or terminal`
  line `tax or toll is leviable shall, when so required by an officer duly authorised by the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `in this behalf, so far as may be necessary for ascertaining the amount of tax chargeable--`
  line
  line `(a) permit that officer to inspect, examine or weigh such goods, vehicles or animals; and`
  line
  line `(b) communicate to that officer any information, and exhibit to him any bill, in voice or`
  line `document of a like nature, which such person may possess relating to such goods, vehicles or animals.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (17215)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to seize, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17215&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who takes or attempts to take past any octroi station or any`
  line `other place appointed within a cantonment for the collection of octroi, terminal tax or toll any goods,`
  line `vehicles or animals, on account of which octroi, terminal tax or toll is leviable and thereby evades, or`
  line `attempts to evade, the payment of such octroi, terminal tax or toll and any person who abets any such`
  line `evasion or attempt at evasion, shall be punishable with fine which may extend either to ten times the`
  line `value of such octroi, terminal tax or toll, or to two thousand five hundred rupees, whichever is greater,`
  line `and which shall not be less than twice the value of such octroi, terminal tax or toll, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of non-payment of any octroi or terminal tax or toll on demand, the officer empowered to`
  line `collect the same may seize any goods, vehicles or animals on which the octroi, terminal tax or toll is`
  line `chargeable or any part or number thereof which is of sufficient value to satisfy the demand and shall give`
  line `a receipt specifying the items seized.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer, or an officer of the Board authorised by him, after the lapse of`
  line `five days from the seizure, and after the issue of a notice in writing to the person in whose possession the`
  line `goods, vehicles or animals were at the time of seizure, fixing the time and place of sale, may cause the`
  line `property so seized, or so much thereof as may be necessary, to be sold by auction to satisfy the demand`
  line `and meet expenses occasioned by the seizure, custody and safe thereof, unless the demand and expenses`
  line `are in the meantime paid:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Executive Officer may, in any case, order that any article of a perishable`
  line `nature which cannot be kept for five days without serious risk of damage, or which cannot be kept safe at`
  line `a cost which, together with the amount of octroi, terminal tax or toll, is likely to exceed its value, shall be`
  line `sold after the lapse of such shorter times as he may, having regard to the nature of the article, think`
  line proper.
  line
  line `(4) If, at any time before the sale has begun, the person whose property has been seized tenders to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer the amount of all expenses incurred and of the octroi, terminal tax or toll, the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer shall release the property seized.`
  line
  line `(5) The surplus, if any, of the sale proceeds shall be credited to the cantonment fund, and shall, on`
  line `application made to the Chief Executive Officer within six months after the sale, be paid to the person in`
  line `whose possession the property was at the time of seizure, and, if no such application is made, shall`
  line `become the property of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (17216)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Lease of octroi, terminal tax or toll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17216&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the Chief Executive Officer, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Board to lease the collection of any octroi, terminal tax or toll for any period not`
  line `exceeding one year; and the lessee and all persons employed by him in the management and collection of`
  line `the octroi, terminal tax or toll shall, in respect thereof,--`
  line
  line `(a) be bound by any orders made by the Chief Executive Officer for their guidance;`
  line
  line `(b) have such powers exercisable by officers or employees of the Board under this Act as the`
  line `Board may confer upon them; and`
  line
  line `(c) be entitled to the same remedies and be subject to the same responsibilities as if they were`
  line `employed by the Board for the management and collection of the octroi, terminal tax or toll, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no article distrained may be sold except under the orders of the Chief Executive`
  line Officer.
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (17217)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Appeals against assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17217&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal against the assessment or levy of, or against the`
  line `refusal to refund, any tax under this Act shall lie to the District Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the District Court, on the hearing of an appeal under this section, entertains reasonable doubt on`
  line `any question as to the liability to, or the principle of assessment of, a tax, the Court may, either on its own`
  line `motion or on the application of the appellant, draw up statement of the facts of the case and the point on`
  line `which doubt is entertained, and refer the statement with its opinion on the point for the decision of the`
  line `High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) On a reference being made under sub-section (2), the subsequent proceedings in the case shall be,`
  line `as nearly as may be, in conformity with the rules relating to references to the High Court contained in`
  line `order XLVI of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and sections 94, 95, 96, 97 and 102, "District Court",`
  line `in relation to a cantonment, means the Principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction having jurisdiction`
  line `over the area in which that cantonment is situated, and includes such other Civil Court having jurisdiction`
  line `over that area as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line `behalf, in consultation with the High Court having jurisdiction over that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (17218)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Costs of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17218&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `In every appeal the costs shall be in the discretion of the District Court hearing`
  line `the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (17219)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Recovery of costs from Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17219&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Board fails to pay any cost awarded to an appellant`
  line `within ten days after the date of the order for payment thereof, the District Court awarding the costs may`
  line `order the person having the custody of the balance of the cantonment fund to pay the amount.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the appellant fails to pay any costs awarded to the Board within ten days after the date of`
  line `the order for payment thereof, the same shall be recoverable by the Board in the same manner as moneys`
  line `recoverable by the Board under section 324.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (17220)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Conditions of right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17220&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `No appeal shall be heard or determined under this Chapter`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) the appeal is, in the case of a tax assessed on the annual rateable value of buildings or lands or`
  line `both, brought within thirty days next after the date of the authentication of the assessment list under`
  line `section 77 (exclusive of the time required for obtaining a copy of the relevant entries therein), or, as the case may be, within thirty days of the date on which an amendment is finally made under`
  line `section 79 and in the case of any other tax, within thirty days next after the date of the receipt of the`
  line `notice of assessment or of alteration of assessment or, if no notice has been given, within thirty days`
  line `next after the date of the presentation of the first bill in respect thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiration of the period prescribed there for by`
  line `this section if the appellant satisfies the District Court before whom the appeal is preferred that he had`
  line `sufficient cause for not preferring it within that period;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount including the assessed tax or duty, if any, in dispute in the appeal shall be`
  line `deposited by the appellant every year on or before the due date in the office of the Board till the`
  line `appeal is decided by the District Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (17221)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Finality of appellate orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17221&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `The order of a District Court confirming, setting aside or`
  line `modifying an order in respect of any valuation or assessment or liability to assessment or taxation shall be`
  line `final:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for the District Court, upon application or on its own motion, to`
  line `review any order passed by it in appeal if application in this behalf is made within three months from the`
  line `date of the original order.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (17222)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Time and manner of payment of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17222&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided under this Act,`
  line `any tax imposed under the provisions of this Act shall be payable on such dates and in such manner, as`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer may, by public notice, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (17223)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Public notice for taxes due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17223&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any tax has become due the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `shall cause a separate bill and public notice to be issued as well as published in a local newspaper`
  line `specifying the tax and the period for which it is due for payment.`
  line
  line `(2) The tax shall become due for payment from the date of issue of public notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) above.`
  line
  line `(3) Any non-receipt of a Bill by a person shall not be a cause for non-payment of the tax notified`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (17224)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17224&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the amount of tax for which public notice has been issued or a bill`
  line `has been presented is not paid within thirty days from the issue of public notice or presentation of the bill,`
  line `as the case may be, the Chief Executive Officer may cause to be served upon the person liable for the`
  line `payment of the same a notice of demand in the form set forth in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) For every notice of demand which the Chief Executive Officer causes to be served on any person`
  line `under this section, a fee of such amount, not exceeding two hundred rupees as shall in each case be fixed`
  line `by the Chief Executive Officer, shall be payable by the said person and shall be included in the costs of`
  line recovery.
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (17225)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Recovery of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17225&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person liable for the payment of any tax does not, within thirty`
  line `days from the service of the notice of demand, pay the amount due, or show sufficient cause for`
  line `non-payment of the same to the satisfaction of the Chief Executive Officer, such sum, with all costs of`
  line `recovery, may be recovered under a warrant, issued in the form set forth in Schedule II, by distress and`
  line `sale of the movable property or attachment and sale of the immovable property of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Executive Officer shall not recover any sum the liability for which has been`
  line `remitted on appeal under this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the sale of any immovable property attached under this sub-section shall not be`
  line `made save under the orders of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every warrant issued under this section shall be signed by the Chief Executive Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (17226)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Interest payable on taxes due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17226&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person on whom a notice of demand has been served`
  line `under section 100, does not, within thirty days from the service of such notice, pay the sum demanded in the notice, he shall be liable to pay by way of interest, in addition to the sum and other charges due one`
  line `per cent., of the sum due for each complete month from the date of expiry of the period of thirty days as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) The amount of interest shall be recoverable in the same manner as moneys recoverable by the`
  line `Board under section 324.`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) where no appeal has been preferred, the Chief Executive officer with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Board; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the District Court hearing the appeal under section 93,`
  line
  line `may remit the whole or any part of the interest payable in respect of any period.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (17227)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title Distress.
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17227&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for any official of the Board to whom a warrant issued under`
  line `section 101 is addressed to distrain, wherever it may be found in the cantonment, any movable property of`
  line `or standing timber, growing crops or grass belonging to the person therein named as defaulter, subject to`
  line `the following conditions, exceptions and exemption, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the following property shall not be distrained--`
  line
  line `(i) the necessary wearing apparel and bedding of the defaulter or of his wife or of his`
  line children;
  line
  line `(ii) tools of artisans;`
  line
  line `(iii) books of account; or`
  line
  line `(iv) when the defaulter is an agriculturist, his implements of husbandry, seed-grain, and such`
  line `cattle as may be necessary to enable the defaulter to earn his livelihood;`
  line
  line `(b) the distress shall not be excessive, that is to say, the property distrained shall be as nearly as`
  line `possible equal in value to the amount recoverable under the warrant, and if any property has been`
  line `distrained which, in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, should not have been distrained, it`
  line `shall forthwith be returned.`
  line
  line `(2) The person charged with the execution of a warrant of distress shall forthwith make an inventory`
  line `of the property which he seizes under such warrant, and shall, at the same time, give a written notice in`
  line `the form in Schedule III to the person in possession thereof at the time of seizure that the said property`
  line `will be sold as therein mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (17228)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Disposal of distrained property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17228&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the property seized is subject to speedy and`
  line `natural decay, or when the expense of keeping it in custody is, when added to the amount to be recovered,`
  line `likely to exceed its value, the Chief Executive Officer shall give notice to the person in whose possession`
  line `the property was at the time of seizure that it will be sold at once, and shall sell it accordingly by public`
  line `auction unless the amount mentioned in the warrant is forthwith paid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the warrant is not in the meantime suspended by the Chief Executive Officer, or discharged, the`
  line `property seized shall, after the expiry of the period named in the notice served under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 103, be sold by public auction by order of the Chief Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) For every distraint made under this Chapter a fee of such amount, not exceeding two hundred`
  line `rupees, as shall in each case be fixed by the Chief Executive Officer shall be charged, and the said fee`
  line `shall be included in the costs of recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (17229)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Attachment and sale of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17229&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a warrant is issued for the`
  line `attachment and sale of immovable property, the attachment shall be made by an order prohibiting the`
  line `defaulter from transferring or charging the property in any way, and all persons from taking any benefit`
  line `from such transfer or charge, and declaring that such property would be sold unless the amount of tax due`
  line `with all costs of recovery is paid in the office of the Board within fifteen days from the date of`
  line attachment.
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) shall be displayed at some place on or adjacent to such property by`
  line `pasting the same conspicuously and by publishing the same in a newspaper having circulation in the area in which the property is situated or by any other means or mode as may be considered appropriate by the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Any transfer of or charge on the property attached or any interest thereon made without the`
  line `written permission of the Chief Executive Officer shall be void as against all claims of the Board`
  line `enforceable under the attachment.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the sum due to the Board with the cost incurred by the Board in the sale of the property,`
  line `including publication of notice in newspaper and a sum equal to five per cent. of the purchase money for`
  line `payment to the purchaser is paid by the defaulter, before the confirmation of the sale under`
  line `sub-section (5), the attachment, if any, of the immovable property shall be deemed to have been removed.`
  line
  line `(5) After the sale of the property by auction as aforesaid, it shall be confirmed in writing by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer who shall put the person declared to be the purchaser in possession of the same and`
  line `shall grant him a certificate to the effect that he has purchased the property to which the certificate refers.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may make rules for--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the manner of execution of warrants for the attachment and sale of immovable`
  line property;
  line
  line `(b) charging of fees for the attachment and sale of immovable property, to be included in the cost`
  line `of recovery of the tax due;`
  line
  line `(c) summary determination of any claim made by any person other than the person liable for the`
  line `payment of any tax, in respect of any property attached in execution of warrant under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (17230)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Recovery from a person about to leave cantonment and refund of surplus sale proceeds, if any.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17230&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Chief Executive Officer has reason to believe that any person from whom any sum is due`
  line `or is about to become due on account of any tax is about to move from the cantonment, he may direct the`
  line `immediate payment by such person of the sum so due or about to become due, and cause a notice of`
  line `demand for the same to be served on such person.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on the service of such notice, such person does not forthwith pay the sum so due or about to`
  line `become due, the amount shall be leviable by distress and sale of movable property or attachment and sale`
  line `of immovable property in the manner hereinbefore provided in this Chapter, and the warrant of such`
  line `distress and sale or attachment and sale may be issued and executed without any delay.`
  line
  line `(3) The surplus of the sale proceeds arising out of section 104, section 105 and this section, if any,`
  line `shall immediately after the sale of the property, be credited to the cantonment fund, and the notice of such`
  line `credit shall immediately be given to the person whose property has been sold, or to his legal`
  line `representative and, if such money is claimed, within a period of one year from the date of notice, a refund`
  line `thereof shall be made to the said person or his representative.`
  line
  line `(4) Any surplus of the sale proceeds not claimed within one year as aforesaid shall be the property of`
  line `the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (17231)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Power to institute suit for recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17231&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `Instead of proceeding against a defaulter by distress and`
  line `sale of movable property or attachment and sale of immovable property as hereinbefore provided in this`
  line `Chapter, or after a defaulter has been so proceeded against unsuccessfully or with only partial success,`
  line `any sum due or the balance of any sum due, as the case may be, from such defaulter on account of a tax`
  line `may be recovered from him by a suit in any court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (17232)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Board to be a Municipality for taxation purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17232&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `A Board shall be deemed to be a`
  line `municipal committee for the purposes of taxation as per the Municipal Taxation Act, 1881 (11 of 1881).`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (17233)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Payment to be made to a Board as service charges by Central Government or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17233&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `The Central or the State Government, as the case may be, shall pay to a Board annually`
  line `service charges for providing collective municipal services or development work in a cantonment where the Central or the State Government properties are situated as worked out by the Board based on the`
  line `guidelines issued in this behalf by the Central Government or the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (17234)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power to be make special provision for conservancy in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17234&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `A Board may make`
  line `special provisions for the cleansing of any factory, hotel, club or group of buildings or lands used for any`
  line `one purpose and under one management, and may fix a special rate and the dates and other conditions for`
  line `periodical payment thereof, which shall be determined by a written agreement with the person liable for`
  line `payment of the conservancy or scavenging tax in respect of such factory, hotel, club or group of buildings`
  line `or lands:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in fixing the amount, proper regard shall be had to the probable cost to the Board of the`
  line `services to be rendered.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (17235)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Exemption in case of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17235&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) When in pursuance of section 110, a Board has fixed a`
  line `special rate for the cleansing of any factory, hotel, club or group of buildings or lands, such premises shall`
  line `be exempted from the payment of conservancy or scavenging tax imposed in the cantonment.`
  line
  line `(2) The following buildings and lands shall be exempt from any property tax other than tax imposed`
  line `to cover the cost of specific services rendered by the Board, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) places set apart for public worship and either actually so used or used for no other purpose and`
  line `rendering services free of cost without deriving any income whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) buildings used for educational purposes, public libraries, playgrounds and dharamshalas`
  line `which are open to the public and from which no income is derived;`
  line
  line `(c) hospitals and dispensaries maintained wholly by charitable contributions;`
  line
  line `(d) burning and burial grounds, not being the property of the Government or a Board, which are`
  line `controlled under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) buildings or lands vested in a Board; and`
  line
  line `(f) any buildings or lands, or portion of such buildings or lands, which are the property of the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (17236)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `General power of exemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17236&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, exempt, either wholly or in part from the payment of any tax imposed under this Act, any person,`
  line `or class of persons or any property or goods or class of property or goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (17237)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Exemption of poor persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17237&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `A Board may exempt, for a period not exceeding one year at a`
  line `time from the payment of any tax, or any portion of a tax imposed under this Act, any person who in its`
  line `opinion is by reason of poverty unable to pay the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (17238)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title Composition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17238&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous sanction of the General Commanding`
  line `Officer-in-Chief, the Command, allow any person to compound for any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) Every sum due by reason of the composition of a tax under sub-section (1) shall be recoverable as`
  line `if it were a tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (17239)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Irrecoverable debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17239&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `The Board may write off any sum due on account of any tax or rate or of`
  line `the costs of recovering any tax or rate if such sum is, in its opinion, irrecoverable:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the sum written off in favour of any one person exceeds two thousand and five`
  line `hundred rupees, the sanction of the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command shall be first`
  line obtained.
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (17240)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Obligation to disclose liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17240&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer, may, by written notice, call`
  line `upon any inhabitant of the cantonment to furnish such information as may be necessary for the purpose of`
  line ascertaining--
  line
  line `(a) whether such inhabitant is liable to pay, or has correctly paid, any tax imposed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) at what amount he should be assessed; or`
  line
  line `(c) the annual value of the building or land which he occupies and the name and address of the`
  line `owner or lessee thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person, when called upon under sub-section (1) to furnish information, neglects to furnish`
  line `it within the period specified in this behalf by the Chief Executive Officer or furnishes information which`
  line `is not true to the best of his knowledge or belief, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to`
  line `five thousand rupees and shall also be liable to be assessed at such amount on account of tax as the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer may deem proper, and the assessment so made shall, subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (17241)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Immaterial error not to affect liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17241&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `No assessment and no charge or demand on account`
  line `of any tax or fee shall be impeached or affected by reason only of any mistake in the name of any person`
  line `liable to pay such tax or fee, or in the description of any property or thing, or any mistake in the amount`
  line `of the assessment, charge or demand, if the directions contained in this Act and the rules and bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder have in substance and effect been complied with; but any person who sustains any`
  line `special damage by reason of any such mistake shall be entitled to recover such compensation for the`
  line `same, as the Board may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (17242)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Distraint not to be invalid by reason of immaterial defect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17242&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `No distress levied or attachment`
  line `made under this Chapter shall be deemed unlawful, nor shall any person making the same be deemed a`
  line `trespasser, on account only of any defect of form in the notice of demand, warrant of distress or`
  line `attachment and sale or other proceeding relating thereto; nor shall any such person be deemed a trespasser`
  line `ab initio on account of any irregularity afterwards committed by him; but any person who sustains any`
  line `special damage by reason of any such irregularity shall be entitled to recover such compensation for the`
  line `same, as the Board may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (17243)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Cantonment fund and cantonment development fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17243&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed for every`
  line `cantonment a cantonment fund and there shall be placed to the credit thereof the following sums,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance if any, of the cantonment fund formed for the cantonment under the Cantonments`
  line `Act, 1924 (2 of 1924);`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by or on behalf of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall also be formed for every cantonment, a cantonment development fund and there shall`
  line `be placed to the credit, thereof the following sums, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) any sum received from the Central Government or the Government of any State by way of`
  line `contributions, grants, subsidies or by any other way for the implementation of any specific scheme or`
  line `for the execution of any specific project;`
  line
  line `(ii) any sum received from any individual or association of individuals by way of gift or deposit;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) any sum raised or borrowed under section 121 for the execution of specific development`
  line projects.
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (17244)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Custody of cantonment fund and cantonment development fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17244&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The cantonment fund`
  line `and the cantonment development fund shall be kept in separate accounts which shall be maintained in`
  line `State Bank of India or any of its subsidiary banks or any nationalised bank or any scheduled commercial`
  line `bank having its branch either in the cantonment or in the municipal area adjoining the cantonment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "nationalised bank" means corresponding new bank specified in the First Schedule to the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act,1980 (40 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(ii) "State Bank of India" means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(iii) "subsidiary bank" means a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India`
  line `(Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959).`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may with the previous sanction of the President Cantonment Board`
  line `may invest any portion of cantonment fund or cantonment development fund in securities of Central`
  line `Government or in such securities, including fixed deposits in banks in the best interest of the Board and`
  line `may dispose of such investments or vary them for others of a like nature.`
  line
  line `(3) The income resulting from any fixed deposit or from any such securities as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) or from the proceeds of the sale of any such security shall be credited to the cantonment`
  line `fund or, as the case may be, the cantonment development fund.`
  line
  line `(4) Every action taken under sub-sections (2) and (3) may be subsequently brought to the next`
  line `meeting of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (17245)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of Board to borrow money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17245&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `A Board may from time to time by a resolution passed in`
  line `this behalf borrow money from another Board, on mutually agreeable terms any sum of money which`
  line `may be required for the schemes or projects covered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (17246)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title Property.
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17246&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any special reservation made by the Central Government all property of`
  line `the nature hereinafter in this section specified which has been acquired or provided or is maintained by a`
  line `Board shall vest in and belong to that Board, and shall be under its direction, management and control,`
  line `that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) all markets, slaughter-houses, manure and night-soil depots, and buildings of every`
  line description;
  line
  line `(b) all water-works for the supply, storage or distribution of water for public purposes and all`
  line `bridges, buildings, engines, materials, and things connected there with or appertaining thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) all sewers, drains, culverts and water-courses, and all works, materials and things appertaining`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(d) all dust, dirt, dung, ashes, refuse, animal matter, filth and rubbish of every kind, and dead`
  line `bodies of animals collected by the Board from the streets, houses, privies, sewers, cesspools or`
  line `elsewhere, or deposited in places appointed by the Board for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(e) all lamps and lamp-posts and apparatus connected therewith or appertaining thereto;`
  line
  line `(f) all lands or other property transferred to the Board by the Central or a State Government, or by`
  line `gift, purchase or otherwise for local public purposes; and`
  line
  line `(g) all streets and the pavements, stones and other materials thereof, and also all trees, erections,`
  line `materials, implements, and things existing on or appertaining to streets.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (17247)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Application of cantonment fund, cantonment development fund and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17247&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line The
  line `cantonment fund, cantonment development fund and all property vested in a Board shall be applied for`
  line `the purposes, whether express or implied, for which, by or under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, powers are conferred or duties or obligations are imposed upon the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not incur any expenditure for acquiring or renting land beyond the`
  line `limits of the cantonment or for constructing any work beyond such limits except--`
  line
  line `(a) with the sanction of the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) on such terms and conditions as the Central Government may impose:`
  line
  line `Provided further that priority shall be given in the order hereinafter set forth to the following`
  line `liabilities and obligations of a Board, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) to the liabilities and obligations arising from a trust legally imposed upon or accepted by the`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(b) to the repayment of, and the payment of interest on, any loan incurred under the provisions of`
  line `the Local Authorities Loan Act, 1914 (9 of 1914) or under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(c) to the payment of establishment charges;`
  line
  line `(d) to the payment of any sum the payment of which is expressly required by the provisions of`
  line `this Act or any rule or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (17248)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Acquisition of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17248&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `When there is any hindrance to the permanent or`
  line `temporary acquisition upon payment of any land required by a Board for the purposes of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Board, procure the acquisition there of under the`
  line `provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), and on payment by the Board of the`
  line `compensation awarded under that Act and of the charges incurred by the Government in connection with`
  line `the proceedings, the land shall vest in the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (17249)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power to make rules regarding cantonment fund, cantonment development fund and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17249&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules consistent with this Act to provide for all or any of`
  line `the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions on which property may be acquired by Boards or on which property vested in a`
  line `Board may be transferred by sale, mortgage, lease, exchange or otherwise; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter relating to the cantonment fund or cantonment development fund or`
  line `cantonment property, in respect of which no provision or insufficient provision is made by or under`
  line `this Act and provision is, in the opinion of the Central Government necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (17250)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Contracts by whom to be executed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17250&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, every Board`
  line `shall be competent to enter into and perform any contract necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (17251)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title Sanction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17251&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every contract--`
  line
  line `(a) for which budget provision does not exist, or`
  line
  line `(b) which involves a value or amount exceeding rupees fifty thousand shall require the sanction`
  line `of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every contract other than a contract such as is referred to in sub-section (1) shall be sanctioned by`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer on behalf of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (17252)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Execution of contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17252&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every contract made by or on behalf of a Board, the value or`
  line `amount of which exceeds fifty thousand rupees, shall be in writing, and every such contract shall, be`
  line `signed by two members, of whom the President or the Vice-President shall be one, and be countersigned`
  line `by the Chief Executive Officer and be sealed with the common seal of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chief Executive Officer executes a contract on behalf of the Board sanctioned under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 127, he shall submit a report, on the execution of the contract, to the Board at its`
  line `next meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (17253)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Contracts improperly executed not to be binding on a Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17253&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `If any contract is executed by`
  line `or on behalf of a Board, otherwise than in conformity with the provisions of this Chapter, it shall not be`
  line `binding on the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (17254)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Responsibility for sanitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17254&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `The following officers shall, for the purposes of sanitation,`
  line `have control over, and be responsible for maintaining in a sanitary condition, those parts of a cantonment,`
  line `respectively, which are specified in the case of each, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Officer Commanding the army in the cantonment--all buildings and lands which are`
  line `occupied or used for army purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) the Officer Commanding the navy in the cantonment--all buildings and lands which are`
  line `occupied or used for naval purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) the Officer Commanding the air force in the cantonment--all buildings and lands which are`
  line `occupied or used for air force purposes;`
  line
  line `(d) the Officer Commanding the station in the cantonment--all buildings and lands, occupied or`
  line `used for any defence purpose, other than those referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c);`
  line
  line `(e) the head of any civil department or railway administration occupying as such any part of the`
  line `cantonment--all buildings and lands in his charge as head of that department or administration;`
  line
  line `(f) the head of any establishment or installation of the Defence Research and Development`
  line `Organisation in the cantonment--buildings and lands which are occupied or used for the purposes of`
  line `the Defence Research and Development Organisation in the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(g) the head of a Public Sector Undertaking--the buildings and lands belonging to such`
  line `undertaking in the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(h) the Chief Executive Officer--the buildings and lands in the civil area of the cantonment and`
  line `all other buildings and lands not covered in clauses (a) to (g) above.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (17255)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `General duties of Health Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17255&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Health Officer shall be the Advisor to the Board in`
  line `all matters relating to sanitation and exercise a general sanitary supervision over the cantonment and shall`
  line `periodically submit a report along with his recommendations at least once in every month to the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Assistant Health Officer shall perform such duties in connection with the sanitation of the`
  line `cantonment as are, subject to the control of the Board, allotted to him by the Health Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (17256)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Public latrines, urinals and conservancy establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17256&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `All public latrines and urinals`
  line `provided or maintained by a Board shall be so constructed as to provide separate compartments for each`
  line `sex and the compartments so constructed shall be made accessible to and barrier free for the persons with`
  line `disabilities and shall be provided with all necessary conservancy establishments, and shall regularly be`
  line `cleansed and kept in proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (17257)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Duty of occupier to collect and desposit rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17257&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of an occupier of`
  line `a building or land--`
  line
  line `(a) to make adequate arrangements for the house scavenging of the building or land;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide receptacles of the type and in the manner prescribed by the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `for the collection therein of all filth, rubbish and other offensive matter from such building or land`
  line `and to keep such receptacle in good condition and repair;`
  line
  line `(c) to cause all filth, rubbish and other offensive matter collected in receptacles and to be`
  line `removed and deposited in the public receptacles, depots or places provided or appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 135.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of this section and section 134, "house scavenging" means the removal of filth,`
  line `rubbish or other offensive matter from a privy, latrine, urinal, drain, cesspool or other common receptacle`
  line `for such matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (17258)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Power of Board to undertake private conservancy arrangement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17258&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the application or`
  line `with the consent of the occupier of any building or land, or, where the occupier of any building or land`
  line `fails to make arrangements to the satisfaction of the Chief Executive Officer for the matters referred to in`
  line `this section, without such consent, and after giving notice in writing to the occupier, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may undertake the house scavenging of any building or land in the cantonment for such period as`
  line `he thinks fit on such terms as he may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chief Executive Officer has undertaken the duties referred to in this section, all matter`
  line `removed in the performance of such duties shall be the property of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (17259)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Deposits and disposal of rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17259&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall provide or appoint, in proper`
  line `and convenient situations, public receptacles, depots or places for the temporary deposit or disposal of`
  line `household rubbish, offensive matter, car cases of dead animals and sewage.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may, by public notice, issue directions as to the time at which, the`
  line `manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, any matter referred to in sub-section (1) may be`
  line `removed along a street or may be deposited or otherwise disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) All matter deposited in receptacles, depots or places provided or appointed under this section shall`
  line `be the property of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (17260)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Cesspools, receptacles, for filth, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17260&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer of any cantonment may, by`
  line `notice in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) require any person having the control whether as owner, lessee or occupier of any land or`
  line `building in the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(i) to close any cesspool appertaining to the land or building which, in the opinion of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, is a nuisance, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to keep in a clean condition, in such manner as may be prescribed by notice, any receptacle`
  line `for filth or sewage accumulating on the land or in a building, or`
  line
  line `(iii) to prevent the water of any private latrine, urinal, sink or bathroom or any other offensive`
  line `matter, from soaking, draining or flowing, or being put, from the land or building upon any street or`
  line `other public place, or into any water-course or into any drain not intended for the purpose, or`
  line
  line `(iv) to collect and deposit for removal by the conservancy establishment of the Board, within`
  line `such time and in such receptacle or place, as may be specified in the notice, any offensive matter or`
  line `rubbish which such person has allowed to accumulate or remain under, in or on such building or`
  line `land; or`
  line
  line `(b) require any person to desist from making or altering any drain leading into a public drain; or`
  line
  line `(c) require any person having the control of a drain in the cantonment to cleanse, purify, repair or`
  line `alter the same, or otherwise put it in good order, within such time as may be specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (17261)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Filling up of tank, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17261&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any well, tank, cistern, reservoir container, desert cooler or`
  line `any other, receptacle or place in the cantonment where water is stored or accumulated, whether within any`
  line `private enclosure or not, is in such a condition as to create a nuisance or, in the opinion of the Health`
  line `Officer, is or is likely to be a breeding place for mosquitoes, the Board may, by notice in writing, require`
  line `the owner, lessee or occupier thereof within such period as may be specified in the notice, to fill up or`
  line `cover the well, cistern, reservoir or receptacle, or to fill up the tank, or to drain off or remove the water, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may from time to time take such measures as are necessary in its opinion for`
  line `prevention of breeding of mosquitoes, insects or any bacterial or viral carriers of disease in public places`
  line `under the control or management of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, if it thinks fit, meet the whole or any portion of the expenses incurred in`
  line `execution of work mentioned in sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (17262)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Provision of latrines, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17262&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the`
  line `owner or lessee of any building or land in the cantonment to provide, in such manner as may be specified`
  line `in the notice, any latrine, urinal, cesspool, dust-bin or other receptacle for filth, sewage, or rubbish, or any`
  line `additional latrine, urinal, cesspool or other receptacle as aforesaid, which should, in his opinion, be`
  line `provided for the building or land.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (17263)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Sanitation in factories, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17263&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `Every person employing, whether on behalf of the Government or`
  line `otherwise, more than ten workmen or labourers, and every person managing or having control of a`
  line `market, school, theatre or other place of public resort, in a cantonment shall give notice of the fact to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer, and shall provide such latrines and urinals, and shall employ such number of sweepers, as the Chief Executive Officer thinks fit, and shall cause the latrines and urinals to be kept`
  line `clean and in proper order:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply in the case of a factory to which the Factories`
  line `Act, 1948 (63 of 1948) applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (17264)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Private latrines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17264&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Employment of Manual Scavenger and`
  line `Construction of Dry Latrine (Prohibition) Act, 1993 (46 of 1993), the Chief Executive Officer or any`
  line `official of the Board authorised by him may, by notice in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) require the owner or other person having the control of any private latrine, or, urinal in the`
  line `cantonment not to put the same to public use; or`
  line
  line `(b) where any plan for the construction of private latrines or urinals has been approved, and`
  line `copies thereof may be obtained free of charge on application--`
  line
  line `(i) require any person repairing or constructing any private latrine or urinal not to allow the`
  line `same to be used until it has been inspected by an official of the Board authorised by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, or under the direction of the Health Officer and approved by him as`
  line `conforming with such plan; or`
  line
  line `(ii) require any person having control of any private latrine or urinal to re-build or alter the`
  line `same in accordance with such plan; or`
  line
  line `(c) require the owner or other person having the control of any such private latrine or urinal`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, constitutes a nuisance, to remove the latrine or`
  line `urinal; or`
  line
  line `(d) require any person having the control whether as owner, lessee or occupier of any land or`
  line `building in the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(i) to have any latrines provided for the same shut out by a sufficient roof and wall or fence`
  line `from the view of persons passing by or dwelling in the neighborhood, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to cleanse in such manner as the Chief Executive Officer may specify in the notice any`
  line `latrine or urinal belonging to the land or building;`
  line
  line `(e) require any person being the owner and having the control of any drain in the cantonment to`
  line `provide, within ten days from the service of the notice, such covering as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (17265)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Special provisions for collection of rubbish and solid waste management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17265&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) All solid`
  line `waste material generated in a cantonment shall be removed by the Board and be brought to the compost`
  line `sites or sanitary land sites or trenching sites earmarked by it for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall also devise schemes for collecting rubbish and garbage from each house in the`
  line `cantonment and may, if considers necessary, associate residents' welfare associations or such other`
  line `non governmental organisation for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) As far as possible the Board shall devise appropriate system to ensure that all compostable or`
  line `bio-degradable waste in the cantonment is recycled and used for generating manure, bio-gas or any other`
  line `form of energy.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (17266)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Removal of congested buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17266&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to a Board that any block of buildings`
  line `in the cantonment is in an unhealthy condition by reason of the manner in which the buildings are`
  line `crowded together, or of the narrowness or closeness of the street, or of the want of proper drainage or`
  line `ventilation, or of the impracticability of cleansing the buildings or other similar cause, it may cause the`
  line `block to be inspected by a committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Health Officer,`
  line
  line `(b) the Civil Surgeon of the district or, if his services are not available, some other medical officer`
  line `in the service of the Government,`
  line
  line `(c) the Executive Engineer or a person deputed by the Executive Engineer in this behalf, and`
  line
  line `(d) two non-official members of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The committee shall make a report in writing to the Board regarding the sanitary condition of the`
  line `block, and, if it considers that the condition thereof is likely to cause risk of disease to the inhabitants of`
  line `the building or of the neighbourhood or otherwise to endanger the public health, it shall clearly indicate`
  line `on a plan verified by the Executive Engineer or the person deputed by him to serve on the committee, the`
  line `buildings which should in its opinion wholly or in part be removed in order to abate the unhealthy`
  line `condition of the block.`
  line
  line `(3) If, upon receipt of such report, the Board is of opinion that all or any buildings indicated should be`
  line `removed, it may, by notice in writing, require the owners thereof to remove them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall make compensation as it thinks fit to the owners for any buildings so`
  line `removed which have been erected under proper authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board may if it considers it equitable in the circumstances so to do pay to the`
  line `owners such sum as it thinks fit as compensation for any buildings so removed which have not been`
  line `erected under proper authority.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section buildings includes enclosure, walls and fences appertaining to`
  line buildings.
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (17267)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Overcrowding of dwelling houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17267&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to a Board that any building or part`
  line `of a building in the cantonment which is used as a dwelling house is so overcrowded as to endanger the`
  line `health of the inmates thereof, it may, after such inquiry as it thinks fit, by notice in writing require the`
  line `owner or occupier of the building or part thereof, as the case may be, within such time not being less than`
  line `one month as may be specified in the notice, to abate the overcrowding of the same by reducing the`
  line `number of lodgers, tenants, or other inmates to such number as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who fails, without reasonable cause, to comply with a requisition made upon him`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred`
  line `rupees, and, in the case of a continuing offence, to an additional fine which may extend to two hundred`
  line `fifty rupees for everyday after the first during which the failure has continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (17268)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Power to require repair or alternation of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17268&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building in a cantonment is`
  line `so ill-constructed or dilapidated as to be, in the opinion of the Board, in an insanitary state, the Board`
  line `may, by notice in writing, require the owner, within such time as may be specified in the notice, to`
  line `execute such repairs or to make such alterations as it thinks necessary for the purpose of removing such`
  line defects.
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notice issued under sub-section (1) shall be conspicuously pasted on the building`
  line `to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(3) A notice issued under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have been complied with, if the owner of`
  line `the building to which it relates has, instead of executing the repairs or making the alterations directed by`
  line `the notice, removed the building.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (17269)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Power to require land or building to be cleansed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17269&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any building or land, whether`
  line `tenantable or otherwise, is--`
  line
  line `(i) in an insanitary, filthy or unwholesome state; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, a nuisance to persons residing in the`
  line `neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(iii) overgrown with prickly-pear or rank and noisome vegetation the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `may, by notice in writing, require the owner, lessee or occupier of such building or land to clean,`
  line `lime-wash internally or externally, clear, or otherwise put such building or land in a proper state`
  line `within such period as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who fails to comply with the notice issued under sub-section (1) shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, and, in the case of a continuing offence, with an`
  line `additional fine which may extend to two hundred fifty rupees for each day after the first during which the`
  line `offence continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (17270)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Prohibition in respect of air pollutant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17270&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `No owner, occupier, lessee or any other occupant of`
  line `the premises shall allow or cause to be allowed any air pollutant above the standards, laid down under`
  line `clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 17 of the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution)`
  line `Act, 1981 (14 of 1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (17271)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Power to order disuse of house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17271&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `If a Board is satisfied that any building or part of a building`
  line `in the cantonment which is intended for or used as a dwelling place is unfit for human habitation, it may`
  line `cause a notice to be pasted on some conspicuous part of the building prohibiting the owner or occupier`
  line `thereof from using the building or room for human habitation, or allowing it to be so used, until it has`
  line `been rendered fit for such use to the satisfaction of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (17272)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Removal of noxious vegetation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17272&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing,`
  line `require the owner, lessee, or occupier of any land in the cantonment to clear away and remove any thick`
  line `or noxious vegetation or undergrowth which appears to him to be injurious to health or offensive to`
  line `persons residing in the neighbourhood.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (17273)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Agriculture and irrigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17273&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Where, in the opinion of a Board, the cultivation in the`
  line `cantonment of any description of crop or the use therein of any kind of manure or the irrigation of any`
  line `land therein in any specified manner is likely to be injurious to the health of persons dwelling in the`
  line `neighbourhood, the Board may, by public notice, prohibit such cultivation, use or irrigation after such`
  line `date as may be specified in the notice, or may, by a like notice, direct that it shall be carried out subject to`
  line `such conditions as the Board thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, when a notice is issued under this section, any land to which it relates has been`
  line `lawfully prepared for cultivation or any crop is sown therein or is standing there on, the Board shall, if it`
  line `directs that the notice is to take effect on a date earlier than that by which the crop would ordinarily be`
  line `sown or reaped, as the case may be, make compensation to all persons interested in the land or crop for`
  line `the loss, if any, incurred by them respectively by reason of compliance with the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (17274)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to call for information regarding burial and burning grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17274&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner or person in-charge of any burial or burning ground`
  line `in the cantonment to supply such information as may be specified in the notice concerning the condition,`
  line `management or position of such ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (17275)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Permission for use of new burial or burning ground.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17275&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place in a cantonment which`
  line `has not been used as a burial or burning ground before the commencement of this Act shall be so used`
  line `without the permission in writing of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Such permission may be granted subject to any conditions which the Board thinks fit to impose`
  line `for the purpose of preventing annoyance to, or danger to the health of, persons residing in the`
  line neighbourhood.
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (17276)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Power to require closing of burial or burning ground.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17276&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Board, after making or`
  line `causing to be made local inquiry, is of opinion that any burial or burning ground in the cantonment has`
  line `become offensive to, or dangerous to the health of, persons living in the neighbourhood, it may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government by notice in writing, require the owner or person in charge`
  line `of such ground to close the same from such date as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Government sanctions the issue of any notice under sub-section (1) it shall`
  line `declare the conditions on which the burial or burning ground may be re-opened, and a copy of such`
  line `declaration shall be annexed to the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Government sanctions the issues of any such notice, it shall require a new`
  line `burial or burning ground to be provided at the expense of the cantonment fund, or, if the community`
  line `concerned is willing to provide a new burial or burning ground, the Central Government shall require a`
  line `grant to be made from the cantonment fund towards the cost of the same.`
  line
  line `(4) No corpse shall be buried or burnt in any burial or burning ground in respect of which a notice`
  line `issued under this section is for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (17277)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Exemption from operation of sections 150 to 152.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17277&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 150, 151 and`
  line `152 shall not apply in the case of any burial ground which is for the time being managed by or on behalf`
  line `of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (17278)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Removal of corpses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17278&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by public notice, prescribe routes in the cantonment by`
  line `which alone corpses may be removed to burial or burning grounds.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (17279)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Obligation concerning infectious, contagious o communicable diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17279&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person`
  line `being in charge of, or in attendance, whether as a medical practitioner or otherwise, upon any person in a`
  line `cantonment whom he knows or has reason to believe to be suffering from a contagious, communicable or`
  line `infectious disease, or being the owner, lessee or occupier of any building in a cantonment in which he`
  line `knows that any person is so suffering, shall forthwith give information to the Board respecting the`
  line `existence of such disease.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) knowing that he is suffering from a contagious, communicable or an infectious disease,`
  line `expose other persons to the risk of infection by his presence or conduct in any public street or public`
  line place;
  line
  line `(b) having the care of a person whom he knows to be suffering from a contagious, communicable`
  line `or an infectious disease cause or permit that person to expose other persons to the risk of infection by`
  line `his presence or conduct in any such street or place as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) place or cause to be placed in a dustbin or other receptacle for the deposit of rubbish any`
  line `matter which he knows or has reason to believe to have been exposed to infection from a contagious,`
  line `communicable or an infectious disease and which has not been disinfected properly;`
  line
  line `(d) throw or cause to be thrown into any latrine or urinal any matter which he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to have been exposed to infection from a contagious, communicable or an infectious`
  line `disease and which has not been disinfected properly.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall apply in the case of venereal disease`
  line `where the person suffering there from is under specific and adequate medical treatment and is by reason`
  line `of his habits and conditions of life and residence unlikely to spread the disease.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to give information or gives false information to the Board respecting the existence of`
  line `such disease as is referred to in sub-section (1), or`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes the provisions of sub-section (2), shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be punishable for failure to give information if he had reasonable cause`
  line `to believe that the information had already been duly given.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (17280)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Blood Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17280&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of any Act made in this regard and the rules and`
  line `regulation made thereunder, whoever, being in charge of a blood bank or any other establishment which`
  line `collects or supplies blood, plasma, marrow or any other substance for transfusion or treatment of patients`
  line `or for any other medical use, fails to take adequate precautions or exercise adequate supervision thereby`
  line `leading to or resulting in the supply of infected or contaminated blood, plasma, marrow or any other`
  line `substance, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to five years or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (17281)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Special measures in case of outbreak of infectious or epidemic diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17281&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of`
  line `a cantonment being visited or threatened by an outbreak of any infectious or contagious disease among the inhabitants thereof or of any epidemic disease among any animals therein, the Officer Commanding`
  line `the Station, if he thinks that the provisions of this Act or of any law for the time being in force in the`
  line `cantonment are insufficient for the purpose, may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) take such special measures, and`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice, make such temporary regulations to be observed by the public or by any`
  line `class or section of the public, as he thinks necessary to prevent the outbreak or the spread of the`
  line `disease:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the opinion of the Officer Commanding the Station, immediate measures are`
  line `necessary, he may take action without such sanction as aforesaid and, if he does so, shall forthwith report`
  line `such action to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits a breach of any temporary regulation made under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `deemed to have committed an offence under section 188 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (17282)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Power to require names of a dairyman‟s customers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17282&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Where it is certified to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer by a medical practitioner that the outbreak or spread of any infectious or contagious`
  line `disease in the cantonment is, in the opinion of such medical practitioner, attributable to the milk supplied`
  line `by any dairyman, the Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the dairyman, with in`
  line `such time as may be specified in the notice, to furnish him with a full and complete list of the names and`
  line `addresses of all his customers within the cantonment, or to give him such information as will enable him`
  line `to trace the persons to whom the dairyman has sold milk.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (17283)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Power to require names of a washerman‟s customers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17283&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `Where it is certified to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer by the Health Officer that it is desirable, with a view to prevent the spread of any`
  line `infectious or contagious disease in the cantonment, that the Health Officer should be furnished with a list`
  line `of the customers of any washerman, the Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the`
  line `washerman, within a time to be specified in the notice, to furnish the Health Officer with a full and`
  line `complete list of the names and addresses of all owners within the cantonment of clothes and other articles`
  line `which the washerman washes or has washed during the six weeks immediately preceding the date of the`
  line notice.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "washerman" shall mean an individual,`
  line `body corporate, association of persons engaged in washing clothes in a cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (17284)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Power to require names of patients or customers of a medical practitioner or paramedical workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17284&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Where it is certified to the Chief Executive Officer by the Health Officer or a doctor in the`
  line `employment of the Board that there is apprehension of the outbreak or spreading of any infectious or`
  line `contagious or communicable disease in the cantonment because of use of contaminated needles, syringes`
  line `or any other such equipment by a medical practitioner or by any paramedical worker, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may, by notice in writing, require the medical practitioner or the paramedical worker, within such`
  line `time as may be specified in the notice, to furnish him with a full and complete list of the names and`
  line `addresses of all his customers or patients within the cantonment, or to give him such information as will`
  line `enable him to trace the persons whom the medical practitioner or the paramedical worker has attended to`
  line `or treated in the six weeks preceding the date of issuing the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (17285)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Report after inspection of dairy or washerman or medical practitioner‟s place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17285&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `Where, after inspection the Health Officer is of opinion that any infectious, contagious or`
  line `communicable disease is caused or is likely to arise in the cantonment from the consumption of the milk`
  line `supplied from a dairy or from the washing of clothes or other articles in any place, or from any process`
  line `employed by a washerman, or from use of contaminated needles, syringes or other such equipment by a`
  line `medical practitioner or any paramedical staff, he shall report the matter to the Chief Executive Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (17286)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Action on report submitted by Health Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17286&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `Upon receipt of a report submitted by the`
  line `Health Officer under section 161, the Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibit the supply of milk from the dairy until the notice has been withdrawn; or`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit the washerman from washing clothes or other articles in any such place or by any`
  line `such process as aforesaid until the notice has been withdrawn or unless he uses such place in such`
  line `manner, or washes by process, as the Chief Executive Officer may direct in the notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) prohibit the medical practitioner or the paramedical worker from using any such needles,`
  line `syringes or other such equipment unless the notice is withdrawn or rectification as may be required in`
  line `the notice is carried out.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (17287)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Examination of milk, washed clothes or needles, syringes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17287&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `The Health Officer or a`
  line `doctor in the employment of the Board may take possession of any milk, clothes or other articles which`
  line `are or have recently been in the possession of any dairyman on whom a notice has been served under`
  line `section 158, or of any clothes or other articles which are or have recently been in the possession of any`
  line `washerman, on whom a notice has been served under section 159, or any needles, syringes or such other`
  line `equipment which are or have recently been in the possession of the medical practitioner or paramedical`
  line `worker to whom a notice under section 160 has been issued and may subject the same or cause the same`
  line `to be subjected to such chemical or other process as he may think necessary; and the Board shall pay from`
  line `the cantonment fund all the costs of the process and shall also pay to the owner of the milk, clothes or`
  line `other articles such sum as compensation for any loss occasioned by such process as may appear to it to be`
  line reasonable.
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (17288)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Contamination of public conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17288&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in a cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) uses a public conveyance while suffering from an infectious or contagious disease, or`
  line
  line `(b) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of a person who is suffering from any such disease,`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of the corpse of a person who has died from any`
  line `such disease,`
  line
  line `shall be bound to take proper precautions against the communication of the disease to other persons using`
  line `or who may there after use the conveyance and to notify such use to the owner, driver or person in charge`
  line `of the conveyance, and further to report without delay to the Chief Executive Officer the number of the`
  line `conveyance and the name of the person so notified.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (17289)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Disinfection of public conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17289&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person suffering from, or the corpse of any`
  line `person who has died from, an infectious, communicable or contagious disease has been carried in a public`
  line `conveyance which ordinarily plies in a cantonment, the driver thereof shall forthwith report the fact to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer who shall forth with cause the conveyance to be disinfected if that has not`
  line `already been done.`
  line
  line `(2) No such conveyance shall be brought again into use until the Chief Executive Officer has granted`
  line `a certificate stating that it can be used without causing risk of infection.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (17290)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Penalty for failure to report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17290&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to make to the Chief Executive Officer any report`
  line `which he is required to make by section 164 or section 165 shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (17291)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Driver of conveyance not bound to carry person suffering from infectious or contagious disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17291&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no owner, driver or`
  line `person in charge of a public conveyance shall be bound to convey or to allow to be conveyed in such`
  line `conveyance in or in the vicinity of a cantonment any person suffering from an infectious or contagious`
  line `disease or the corpse of any person who has died from such disease unless and until such person pays or`
  line `tenders a sum fixed by the Chief Executive Officer from time to time, to cover any loss and expense`
  line `which would ordinarily be incurred in disinfecting the conveyance.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (17292)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Disinfection of building or articles therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17292&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Where a Board is, upon the advice of the Health`
  line `Officer, of opinion that the cleansing and disinfection of any building or part of a building in the`
  line `cantonment or of any articles in any such building or part which are likely to retain infection, or the`
  line `renewal of the flooring of any such building or part of such building, would tend to prevent or check the`
  line `spread of any infectious or contagious disease, the Board may by notice in writing, require the owner or occupier to cleanse and disinfect, the said building, part or articles, as the case may be, or to renew the`
  line `said flooring, within such time as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the Board the owner or occupier is from poverty or any other`
  line `cause unable effectually to carry out any such requisition, the Board may, at the expense of the`
  line `cantonment fund, cleanse and disinfect the building, part or articles, or as the case may be, renew the`
  line flooring.
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (17293)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Destruction of infectious hut or shed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17293&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the destruction of any hut or shed in a`
  line `cantonment is, in the opinion of the Board, necessary to prevent the spread of any infectious or contagious`
  line `disease, the Board may, by notice in writing, require the owner to destroy the hut or shed and the`
  line `materials thereof within such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the President of a Board is satisfied that the destruction of any hut or shed in the`
  line `cantonment is immediately necessary for the purpose of preventing the spread of any infectious or`
  line `contagious disease, he may order the owner or occupier of the hut or shed to destroy the same forthwith,`
  line `or may himself cause it to be destroyed after giving not less than two hours' notice to the owner or`
  line `occupier thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall pay compensation to the owner of any hut or shed destroyed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (17294)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Temporary shelter for inmates of disinfected or destroyed buildings or shed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17294&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `The Board`
  line `shall provide free of charge temporary shelter or house accommodation for the members of any family in`
  line `which an infectious or contagious disease has appeared who have been compelled to leave their dwelling`
  line `by reason of any proceedings taken under section 168 or section 169, and who desire such shelter or`
  line `accommodation as aforesaid to be provided for them.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (17295)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Disinfection of building before letting the same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17295&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in a cantonment any building or`
  line `part of a building is intended to be let, in which any person has, within six weeks immediately preceding,`
  line `been suffering from an infectious or contagious disease, the person letting the building or part shall before`
  line `doing so disinfect the same in such manner as the Chief Executive Officer may, by public or special`
  line `notice, direct, together with all articles therein liable to retain infection.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, the keeper of a hotel, lodging house or sarai shall be deemed to`
  line `let to any person who is admitted as a guest therein that part of the building in which such person is`
  line `permitted to reside.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (17296)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Disposal of infected article without disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17296&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without previous`
  line `disinfection of the same, give, lend, sell, transmit or otherwise dispose of to another person any article or`
  line `thing which he knows or has reason to believe has been exposed to contamination by any infectious or`
  line `contagious disease and is likely to be used in, or taken into, a cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (17297)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Means of disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17297&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall--`
  line
  line `(a) provide proper places with necessary attendants and apparatus for the disinfection of`
  line `conveyances, clothing, bedding or other articles which have been exposed to infection;`
  line
  line `(b) cause conveyances, clothing or other articles brought for disinfection to be disinfected either`
  line `free of charge or on payment of such charges as the Chief Executive Officer may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may notify places at which articles of clothing, bedding,`
  line `conveyances or other articles which have been exposed to infection shall be washed, and, if it does so, no`
  line `person shall wash any such thing at any place not so notified without having previously disinfected such`
  line thing.
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may direct the destruction of any clothing, bedding or other article in`
  line `the cantonment likely to retain infection, and may give such compensation as he thinks fit for any article`
  line `so destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (17298)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Marking or selling of food, etc., or washing clothes by infected person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17298&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, while`
  line `suffering from, or in circumstances in which he is likely to spread, any infectious or contagious disease,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes, carries or offers for sale in a cantonment or takes any part in the business of making,`
  line `carrying or offering for sale therein any article of food or drink or any medicine or drug for human`
  line `consumption, or any article of clothing or bedding for personal use or wear, or`
  line
  line `(b) takes any part in the business of the washing or carrying of clothes,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (17299)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Power to restrict or prohibit sale of food or drink.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17299&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `When a cantonment is visited or`
  line `threatened by an outbreak of any infectious or contagious disease, the Chief Executive Officer on behalf`
  line `of the Board may, by public notice, restrict in such manner or prohibit for such period, as may be`
  line `specified in the notice, the sale or preparation of any article of food or drink for human consumption`
  line `specified in the notice or the sale of any flesh of any description of animals so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (17300)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Control over wells, tanks, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17300&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Chief Executive Officer on the advice given by the`
  line `Health Officer is of opinion that the water in any well, tank or other place is likely, if used for drinking, to`
  line `endanger, or cause the spread of, any disease, it may,--`
  line
  line `(a) by public notice, prohibit the removal or use of such water for drinking;`
  line
  line `(b) by notice in writing, require the owner or person having control of such well, tank or place to`
  line `take such steps as may be directed by the notice to prevent the public from having access to or using`
  line `such water; or`
  line
  line `(c) take such other steps as it may consider expedient to prevent the outbreak or spread of any`
  line `such disease.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of a cantonment or any part of a cantonment being visited or threatened by an`
  line `outbreak of any infectious or contagious disease, the Health Officer or any person authorised by him in`
  line `this behalf may, without notice and at any time, inspect and disinfect any well, tank or other place from`
  line `which water is, or is likely to be, taken for the purposes of drinking, and may further take such steps as he`
  line `thinks fit to ensure the purity of the water or to prevent the use of the same for drinking purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (17301)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Disposal of infectious corpse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17301&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `Where any person has died in a cantonment from any infectious`
  line `or contagious disease, the Chief Executive Officer, may, by notice in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) require any person having charge of the corpse to convey the same to a mortuary, thereafter to`
  line `be disposed of in accordance with law; or`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit the removal of the corpse from the place where death occurred except for the purpose`
  line `of being buried or burned or of being conveyed to a mortuary.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (17302)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Maintenance or aiding of hospitals or dispensaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17302&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide and maintain either within or without the cantonment as many hospitals and`
  line `dispensaries as it thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(b) make, upon such terms as it thinks fit to impose, a grant-in-aid to any hospital or dispensary or`
  line `veterinary hospital, whether within or without the cantonment, not maintained by it.`
  line
  line `(2) Every hospital or dispensary maintained or aided under sub-section (1) shall have attached to it a`
  line `ward or wards for the treatment of persons suffering from infectious or contagious diseases.`
  line
  line `(3) The Medical Officer appointed by the Board shall be in charge of every Hospital and dispensary`
  line `maintained or aided under this section and be responsible to the Health Officer for medical activities and`
  line `to the Chief Executive Officer for over all administrative activities of the hospital.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (17303)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Medical supplies, appliances, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17303&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every hospital or dispensary maintained or aided under`
  line `section 178 shall be maintained in accordance with any general or special orders of the Central`
  line `Government for the conduct of hospitals and dispensaries or in accordance with the said orders modified`
  line `in such manner as the Central Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause every such hospital or dispensary to be provided with all requisite drugs,`
  line `instruments, apparatus, furniture and appliances and with sufficient cots, bedding and clothing for`
  line in-patients.
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (17304)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Free patients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17304&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `At every hospital or dispensary maintained or aided under section 178, the sick`
  line `poor of the cantonment, and other inhabitants of the cantonment suffering from infectious, communicable`
  line `or contagious disease, and, with the sanction of the Board, any other sick persons, may receive medical or surgical treatment free of cost, and, if treated as in-patients, shall be either dieted gratuitously or, if the`
  line `medical officer in charge so directs, shall be granted subsistence allowance on such scale as the Board`
  line `may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (17305)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Paying patients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17305&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Any sick person who is ineligible to receive medical or surgical treatment`
  line `free of cost in any hospital or dispensary under section 180 may be admitted for treatment therein upon`
  line `such terms as the Board thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (17306)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Power to order person to attend hospital or dispensary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17306&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Health Officer or the`
  line `Medical Officer in charge of a hospital or dispensary maintained or aided under section 178 has reason to`
  line `believe that any person living in the cantonment is suffering from an infectious, communicable or`
  line `contagious disease, he may, by notice in writing, call upon such person to attend for examination at any`
  line `such hospital or dispensary at such time as may be specified in the notice and not to quit it without the`
  line `permission of the Medical Officer in charge; and, on the arrival of such person at the hospital or`
  line `dispensary, the Medical Officer in charge thereof may examine him for the purpose of satisfying himself`
  line `whether or not such person is suffering from an infectious, communicable or contagious disease:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if, having regard to the nature of the disease or the condition of the person suffering`
  line `there from, or the general environment and circumstances of such person, the Health Officer or Medical`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, considers that the attendance of such person at a hospital or dispensary is`
  line `likely to prove unnecessary or inexpedient, he shall examine such person at such person's own residence.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person on examination under sub-section (1), is found to be suffering from an infectious or`
  line `contagious disease, the Health Officer or Medical Officer, as the case may be, may cause him to be`
  line `detained in hospital until he is free from the infection or contagion:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if having regard to the nature of the disease or the condition of the person suffering`
  line `there from, or the general environment and circumstances of such person, he considers that the detention`
  line `of such person at a hospital or dispensary is unnecessary or inexpedient, he shall discharge such person`
  line `and take such measures or give such directions in the matter as he thinks necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (17307)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Power to exclude from cantonment persons refusing to attend hospital or dispensary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17307&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `If the Health Officer or the Medical Officer in charge of a hospital or dispensary maintained or aided`
  line `under section 178 reports in writing to the Officer Commanding the station that any person having`
  line `received a notice under section 182 has refused or omitted to attend at the hospital or dispensary,`
  line `specified in the notice, or that such person, having attended the hospital or dispensary, has quitted it`
  line `without the permission of such Medical Officer, or that any person has failed to comply with any`
  line `direction given to him under section 182, the Officer Commanding the station may, by order in writing,`
  line `direct such person to be removed from the cantonment within twenty-four hours and not to re-enter it`
  line `without his permission in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who has under sub-section (1) been ordered to be removed from and not to re-enter a`
  line `cantonment shall enter any other cantonment without the written permission of the Officer Commanding`
  line `the station.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (17308)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Routes for pilgrims and others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17308&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may provide or prescribe suitable routes for the`
  line `use of persons assing through the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) on their way to or from fairs or places of pilgrimage or other places of public resort; or`
  line
  line `(b) during times when an infectious or contagious disease is prevalent, and may, by public notice,`
  line `require such persons as aforesaid to use such routes and no others.`
  line
  line `(2) All routes provided or prescribed under sub-section (1) shall be clearly and sufficiently indicated`
  line `by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (17309)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Conditions of service of Safai Karamcharis and others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 2-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17309&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) No person employed in any`
  line `essential service under a Board in a cantonment shall, in the absence of any contract, resign without`
  line `reasonable cause or absent himself from duty without proper authority and in case of such resignation or`
  line `absence from duty, disciplinary proceedings shall be initiated against him in accordance with such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that on and from such`
  line `date as may be specified in the notification, the provisions of this section shall apply in the case of any`
  line `specified class of employees employed by a Board whose functions intimately concern the public health`
  line `or safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (17310)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Maintenance of water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17310&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every cantonment where a sufficient supply of potable`
  line `water for domestic use does not exist, the Board shall provide or arrange for the provision of such a`
  line supply.
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall, as far as possible, make adequate provision that such supply shall be continuous`
  line `throughout the year, and that the water shall be at all times fit for human consumption.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of every Board to practise and propagate the scientific methods of water`
  line `harvesting including harvesting of rain water for use and make arrangement for recharging the sources of`
  line `ground water including underground aquifers and to preserve rivers, streams, springs and other natural`
  line `sources of water within and in the vicinity of the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (17311)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Terms of water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17311&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the following`
  line `words and expression in relation to water supply shall have the respective meanings given below,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) "communication pipe" means:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the premises supplied with water abut on the part of the street in which the main is laid,`
  line `and the service pipe enters those premises otherwise than through the outer wall of a building abutting`
  line `on the street and has a stopcock placed in those premises and as near to the boundary of that street as`
  line `is reasonably practicable, so much of the service pipe as lies between the main and that stopcock;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, so much of the service pipe as lies between the main and the boundary of`
  line `the street in which the main is laid, and includes the ferrule at the junction of the service pipe with the`
  line `main, and also,--`
  line
  line `(i) where the communication pipe ends at in a stopcock, that stopcock, and`
  line
  line `(ii) any stopcock fitted on the communication pipe between the end thereof and the main.`
  line
  line `(2) "main" means a pipe laid by the Board for the purpose of giving a general supply of water as`
  line `distinct from a supply to individual consumers and includes any apparatus used in connection with such a`
  line pipe.
  line
  line `(3) "service pipe" means so much of any pipe for supplying water from a main to any premises as is`
  line `subject to water pressure from that main, or would be so subject but for the closing of some tap.`
  line
  line `(4) "supply pipe" means so much of any service pipe as is not a communication pipe.`
  line
  line `(5) "trunk main" means a main constructed for the purpose of conveying water from a source of`
  line `supply to a filter or reservoir or from one filter or reservoir to another filter or reservoir, or for the purpose`
  line `of conveying water in bulk from one part of the limits of supply to another part of those limits, or for the`
  line `purpose of giving or taking a supply of water in bulk.`
  line
  line `(6) "water fittings" includes pipes (other than mains), taps, cocks, valves, ferrules, meters, cisterns,`
  line `baths and other similar apparatus used in connection with the supply and use of water.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (17312)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Board to carry out survey and formulate proposals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17312&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, when so`
  line required,--
  line
  line `(a) carry out a survey of the existing consumption of and demand for water supplies in`
  line `cantonment and of the water resources in or likely to be made available in the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(b) prepare an estimate of the future water supply requirements of the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(c) carry out a survey of the existing quantity of sewage collection;`
  line
  line `(d) formulate proposals as to--`
  line
  line `(i) the existing or future water supply requirements of the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(ii) the existing or future sewage collection requirement in cantonment including proposals`
  line `for the manner in which and the place or places at which sewage should be carried, collected and`
  line treated.
  line
  line `(2) If the Board is of the opinion that the works and other properties for the time being vested in the`
  line `Board, are inadequate for the purpose of sufficient supply of water or for the purpose of efficient`
  line `collection of sewage under this Act it may take steps in accordance with the provisions of this Act for the`
  line `construction of additional works, whether within cantonment or outside the cantonment with the approval`
  line `of the Principal Director and for the acquisition of additional properties for such works.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (17313)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Control over sources of public water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17313&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous sanction`
  line `of the Central Government, by public notice, declare any lake, stream, spring, well, tank, reservoir or`
  line `other source, whether within or without the limits of the cantonment other than a source of water-supply`
  line `under the control and in use of the Military Engineer Services or the Public Works Department from`
  line `which water is or may be made available for the use of the public in the cantonment to be source of public`
  line water-supply.
  line
  line `(2) Every such source shall be under the control of the Board and it shall be the duty of the Board to`
  line `preserve and maintain such source.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (17314)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Power to require maintenance or closing of private source of public drinking water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17314&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner or any person`
  line `having the control of any source of public water-supply which is used for drinking purposes--`
  line
  line `(a) to keep the same in good order and to clear it from time to time of silt, refuse and decaying`
  line `vegetation; or`
  line
  line `(b) to protect the same from contamination in such manner as the Chief Executive Officer may`
  line `direct; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the water therein is proved to the satisfaction of the Chief Executive Officer to be unfit for`
  line `drinking purposes, to take such measures as may be specified in the notice to prevent the public from`
  line `having access to or using such water:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of a well, such person as aforesaid may, instead of complying with the`
  line `notice, signify in writing his desire to be relieved of all responsibility for the proper maintenance of the`
  line `well and his readiness to place it under the control and supervision of the Board for the use of the public,`
  line `and, if he does so, he shall not be bound to carry out the requisition, and the Board shall undertake the`
  line `control and supervision of the well.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (17315)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17315&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the guidelines made by the Board in this regard, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer may permit the owner, lessee or occupier of any building or land to connect the`
  line `building or land with a source of public water-supply by means of communication pipes of such size and`
  line `description as may be specified for the purpose of obtaining water for domestic use.`
  line
  line `(2) The occupier of every building so connected with the water-supply shall be entitled to have for`
  line `domestic use, in return for the water tax, if any, such quantity of water as the Chief Executive Officer may`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(3) All water supplied in excess of the quantity to which such supply is limited under sub-section (2)`
  line `and, in a cantonment in which a water tax is not imposed, all water supplied under this section, shall be`
  line `paid for at such rate as the Board may fix keeping in view its financial viability.--`
  line
  line `(4) The supply of water for domestic use shall not be deemed to include any supply for--`
  line
  line `(a) animals or for washing vehicles where such animals or vehicle are kept for sale or hire;`
  line
  line `(b) any trade, manufacture or business;`
  line
  line `(c) fountains, swimming baths or any ornamental or mechanical purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) gardens or for purposes of irrigation;`
  line
  line `(e) making or watering roads or paths; or`
  line
  line `(f) building purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (17316)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Power to require water-supply to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17316&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Chief Executive Officer that`
  line `any building or land in the cantonment is without a proper supply of potable water, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner, lessee or occupier of the building or land to obtain`
  line `from a source of public water-supply such quantity of water, as is, adequate to the requirements of the`
  line `persons usually occupying or employed upon the building or land, and to provide communication pipes of`
  line `the prescribed size and description, and to take all necessary steps for the above purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (17317)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `Supply of water under agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17317&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the guidelines made by the Board in this`
  line `regard, the Chief Executive Officer may, by agreement, supply, from any source of public water supply,`
  line `the owner, lessee or occupier of any building or land in the cantonment with any water for any purpose,`
  line `other than a domestic purpose, on such terms and conditions, consistent with this Act and the rules and`
  line `bye laws made thereunder, as may be agreed upon between the Chief Executive Officer and such owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may withdraw such supply or curtail the quantity thereof at any time`
  line `if it should appear necessary to do so for the purpose of maintaining sufficient supply of water for`
  line `domestic use by inhabitants of the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (17318)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Board not liable for failure of supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17318&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any obligation imposed on Boards`
  line `under this Act, a Board shall not be liable to any forfeiture, penalty or damages for failure to supply water`
  line `or for curtailing the quantity thereof if the failure or curtailment, as the case may be, arises from accident`
  line `or from drought or other unavoidable cause unless, in the case of an agreement for the supply of water`
  line `under section 193, the Board has made express provision for forfeiture, penalty or damages in the event of`
  line `such failure or curtailment.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (17319)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Conditions of universal application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17319&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything herein before contained or`
  line `contained in any agreement under section 193, the supply of water by a Board to any building or land`
  line `shall be, and shall be deemed to have been granted subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the owner, lessee or occupier of any building or land in or on which water supplied by the`
  line `Board is wasted by reason of the pipes, drains or other works being out of repair shall, if he has`
  line `knowledge thereof, give notice of the same to such officer as the Chief Executive Officer may appoint`
  line `in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Executive Officer or any other officer or employee of the Board authorised by him`
  line `in writing in this behalf may enter into or on any premises supplied with water by the Board, for the purpose of examining all pipes, taps, works and fittings connected with the supply of water and of`
  line `ascertaining whether there is any waste or misuse of such water;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Executive Officer may, after giving notice in writing, cut off the connection between`
  line `any source of public water-supply and any building or land to which water is supplied for any purpose`
  line `there from, or turn off such supply if--`
  line
  line `(i) the owner or occupier of the building or land neglects to pay the water tax or water rate or`
  line `other charges connected with the water supply within one month from the date on which such tax`
  line `or rate or charge falls due for payment;`
  line
  line `(ii) the occupier refuses to admit the Chief Executive Officer or other authorised officer or`
  line `employee of the Board into the building or land for the purpose of making any examination or`
  line `inquiry authorised by clause (b) or prevents the making of such examination or inquiry;`
  line
  line `(iii) the occupier wilfully or negligently misuses or causes waste of water;`
  line
  line `(iv) the occupier wilfully or negligently injures or damages his meter or any pipe or tap`
  line `conveying water from the water works;`
  line
  line `(v) any pipes, taps, works or fittings connected with the supply of water to the building or`
  line `land are found, on examination by any other officer or employee of the Board authorised by the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer in writing in this behalf, to be out of repair to such an extent as to cause`
  line `waste of water;`
  line
  line `(d) the expense of cutting off the connection or of turning off the water in any case referred to in`
  line `clause (c) shall be paid by the owner or occupier of the building or land;`
  line
  line `(e) no action taken under or in pursuance of clause (c) shall relieve any person from any penalty`
  line `or liability which he may otherwise have incurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (17320)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Supply to persons outside cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17320&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `A Board may allow any person not residing within`
  line `the limits of the cantonment to take or be supplied with water for any purpose from any source of public`
  line `water supply on such terms as it may prescribe, and may at any time withdraw or curtail such supply.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (17321)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17321&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) uses for other than domestic purposes any water supplied by a Board for domestic use; or`
  line
  line `(b) where water is supplied by agreement with a Board for a specified purpose, uses that water for`
  line `any other purposes shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred`
  line `rupees, and in addition, the Board shall be entitled to recover from him the cost of the water misused.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (17322)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Power of Board to lay wires, connections, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17322&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `A Board may carry any cable, wire, pipe,`
  line `drain, sewer or channel of any kind,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of carrying out, establishing or maintaining any system of water-supply,`
  line `lighting, drainage, or sewerage, through, across, under or over any road or street or any place laid out`
  line `or intended as a road or street, or, after giving reasonable notice in writing to the owner or occupier,`
  line `into, through, across, under or over any land or building, or up side of any building, situated within`
  line `the cantonment; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of supplying water or of the introduction or distribution of outflow of water or`
  line `for the removal or outflow of sewage, after giving reasonable notice in writing to the owner or`
  line `occupier, into, through, across, under or over any land or building, or up side of any building, situated`
  line `outside the cantonment and may at all times do all acts and things which may be necessary or`
  line `expedient for repairing or maintaining any such cable, wire, pipe, drain, sewer or channel in an`
  line `effective state for the purpose for which the same may be used or is intended to be used:`
  line
  line `Provided that no nuisance shall be caused in excess of what is reasonably necessary for the proper`
  line `execution of the work:`
  line
  line `Provided further that compensation shall be payable to the owner or occupier for any damage`
  line `sustained by him which is directly occasioned by the carrying out of any such operation.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (17323)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Wires, etc., laid above surface of ground.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17323&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `In the event of any cable, wire, pipe, drain, sewer`
  line `or channel being laid or carried above the surface of any land or through, over or up side of any building,`
  line `such cable, wire, pipe, drain sewer or channel shall be so laid or carried as to interfere as little as possible`
  line `with the rights of the owner or occupier to the due enjoyment of such land or building, and compensation`
  line `shall be payable by the Board in respect of any substantial interference with the right to any such`
  line enjoyment.
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (17324)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title `Connection with main not be made without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17324&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, for any`
  line `purpose whatsoever, without the permission of the Board at any time make or cause to be made any`
  line `connection or communication with any cable, wire, pipe, drain, sewer or channel constructed or`
  line `maintained by, or vested in, a Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (17325)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Power to prescribe ferrules and establish meters, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17325&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may`
  line `prescribe the size of the ferrules to be used for the supply of gas, if any, and may establish meters or other`
  line `appliances for the purpose of measuring the quantity of any water or gas or testing the quality thereof`
  line `supplied to any premises by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (17326)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Power of inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17326&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `The ferrules, communication pipes, connections, meters, stand pipes and`
  line `all fittings thereon or connected therewith leading from water mains or from pipes, drains, sewers or`
  line `channels into any house or land, to which water or gas is supplied by a Board, and the pipes, fittings, and`
  line `works inside any such house or within the limits of any such land, shall in all cases be installed or`
  line `executed subject to the inspection and to the satisfaction of the Chief Executive Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (17327)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Power to fix rates and charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17327&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `A Board may fix the charges to be made for the`
  line `establishment by them or through their agency or communications from, and connections with, mains, or`
  line `pipes for the supply of water, or gas, or for meters or other appliances for measuring the quantity, or`
  line `testing the quantity thereof supplied, and may levy such charges accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (17328)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Government water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17328&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any cantonment there is a water-supply (other than a`
  line `public water-supply under the control of the Board) under the control of the Military Engineer Services or`
  line `the Public Works Department, the Officer of the Military Engineer Services or of the Public Works`
  line `Department, as the case maybe, in charge of such water-supply (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the`
  line `Officer) may publish in the cantonment in such manner as he thinks fit a notice declaring any lake,`
  line `stream, spring, well, tank, reservoir or other source, whether within or without the limits of the`
  line `cantonment other than a source of public water-supply and the officer may, for the purpose of keeping`
  line `any such source in good order or of protecting it from contamination or from use, require the Board to`
  line `exercise any power conferred upon it by section 190.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any water-supply such as is referred to in sub-section (1), the following provisions`
  line `of this Chapter, namely, the provisions of sections 191, 193, 194, 195, 197, 198, 199, 200, 201, 202 and`
  line `203 shall, as far as may be, be applicable in respect of the supply of water to the cantonment, and for the`
  line `purpose of such application references to the Board shall be construed as references to the Officer, and`
  line `references to the Chief Executive Officer or other officer or employee of the Board shall be construed as`
  line `references to such person as may be authorised in this behalf by the Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 193 shall be applicable in respect of the supply of water by agreement to`
  line `the Board by the Officer for use for any purpose other than a domestic purpose in like manner as they are`
  line `applicable to such supply to the owner, lessee or occupier of any building or land in the cantonment.`
  line
  line `(4) In order to preserve the underground water level, the Board may make regulations for the digging`
  line `or use of bore wells in the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (17329)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Water supply for domestic consumption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17329&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer that any dwelling house in the cantonment is without supply of water for domestic consumption`
  line `and that such a supply can be given from mains which is not more than one hundred feet distance from any part of such dwelling house, the Chief Executive Officer may by notice require the owner to obtain`
  line `supply and to execute all such works as may be necessary for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall not be lawful for the owner of any premises which may be constructed or reconstructed, to`
  line `occupy it or cause or permit it to be occupied until he has obtained a certificate from the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer that there is provided within, or within a reasonable distance of, the house supply of wholesome`
  line `water as appears to the Chief Executive Officer to be sufficient for domestic consumption and use of the`
  line `inmates of the house.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (17330)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 206
  title `Recovery of charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17330&sectionno=206&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `In any case in which the provisions of section 204 apply and in which`
  line `the Board is not receiving a bulk supply of water under section 207, the water-tax, if any, imposed in the`
  line `cantonment and all other rates arising out of the supply of water which may be imposed under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter as applied by section 204 shall be recovered by the Board, and all monies so`
  line `recovered, or such proportion thereof as the Central Government may in each case determine, shall be`
  line `paid by the Board to the Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (17331)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 207
  title `Supply of water from Government water-supply to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17331&sectionno=207&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any`
  line `cantonment there is a water-supply such as is referred to in sub-section (1) of section 204, the Board may,`
  line `and so long as the Board is unable to provide a water-supply of its own, it shall receive from the Military`
  line `Engineer Services or the Public Works Department, as the case may be, at such point or points as may be`
  line `agreed upon between the Board and the Military Engineer Services or Public Works Department, a supply`
  line `of water adequate to the requirements for domestic use of all persons in the cantonment other than entitled`
  line consumers.
  line
  line `(2) Any supply of water received under sub-section (1) shall be a bulk supply, and the Board shall`
  line `make such payments to the Military Engineer Services or Public Works Department for all water so`
  line `received as may be agreed upon between the Board and the Military Engineer Services or Public Works`
  line `Department, or, in default of such agreement, as may be determined by the Central Government to be`
  line `reasonable having regard to the actual cost of supplying the water in the cantonment and the rate charge`
  line `for water in any adjacent municipality:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Board shall not charge for the`
  line `supply to persons in the cantonment of water received by the Board under this section a rate calculated to`
  line `produce more than the sum of the payments made to the Military Engineer Services or Public Works`
  line `Department for water received and the actual cost of the supply thereof by the Board to consumers.`
  line
  line `(3) If any dispute arises between the Board and the Military Engineer Services or Public Works`
  line `Department regarding the rate and amount of water adequate to the requirements of persons in the`
  line `cantonment other than entitled consumers, the disputes shall be referred to the Central Government whose`
  line `decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (17332)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 208
  title `Functions of the Board in relation to distribution of bulk supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17332&sectionno=208&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `Where under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) of section 207 a bulk supply of water is received by the Board, the Board`
  line `shall be solely responsible for the supply of water to all persons in the cantonment other than entitled`
  line `consumers; and the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such bulk supply were a source of public`
  line `water-supply under the control of the Board and as if the communications from and connections with such`
  line `bulk supply for the purpose of supplying water to such persons were a system of water supply established`
  line `and maintained by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (17333)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 209
  title `Special provisions concerning drainage and sewage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17333&sectionno=209&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `(1) All public drains, all drains in,`
  line `alongside or under any public street, except those vesting in the Military Engineer Services or any`
  line `Department of the Central Government or a State Government or any autonomous body under the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government and all sewage collection works, whether constructed out of the`
  line `cantonment fund or otherwise and all works, material and things appertaining thereto, which are situated`
  line `in the cantonment shall vest in the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All public and other drains, which are vested in the Board are hereafter in this Act referred to as`
  line `cantonment drains.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of enlarging, deepening or otherwise repairing or maintaining any such drain or`
  line `sewage collection work so much of the sub-soil appertaining thereto as may be necessary for the said`
  line `purpose shall be deemed also to vest in the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) All drains and ventilation shafts, pipes and all appliances and fittings connected with drainage`
  line `works constructed, erected or set up out of the cantonment fund in or upon premises not belonging to the`
  line `Board whether--`
  line
  line `(a) before or after the commencement of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the use of the owner or occupier of such premises or not, shall unless the Board has`
  line `otherwise determined, or does at any time otherwise determine, vest and be deemed always to have`
  line `vested in the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (17334)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 210
  title `Construction of and control of drains and sewage collection and disposal works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17334&sectionno=210&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) All`
  line `cantonment drains, all sewage collection and all works, materials and things appertaining thereto shall be`
  line `under the control of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer shall maintain and keep in repair all cantonment drains and sewage`
  line `collection and sewage disposal works when authorised by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall construct as many new drains and sewage collection and sewage disposal works`
  line `as may from time to time be necessary for effectual drainage and sewage collection.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall ensure that the sewage effluents are treated in accordance with the norms laid`
  line `down under the relevant laws relating to pollution before it is dispersed into a river, stream, lake or open`
  line land.
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (17335)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 211
  title `Certain matters not to be passed into cantonments drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17335&sectionno=211&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `No person shall throw, empty or`
  line `turn into any cantonment drain or into any drain communicating with a cantonment drain--`
  line
  line `(a) any matter likely to injure the drain or to interfere with the free flow of its contents, or to`
  line `affect prejudicially the treatment and disposal of its contents; or`
  line
  line `(b) any chemical, refuse or waste stream, or any liquid of a temperature higher than forty-five`
  line `degrees centigrade, being refuse or stream which, or liquid which when so heated is, either alone or in`
  line `combination with the contents of the drain be dangerous, or the cause of a nuisance, or prejudicial to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(c) any dangerous petroleum.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expression "dangerous petroleum" has the same meaning as in the`
  line `Petroleum Act, 1934 (3 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (17336)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 212
  title `Application by owners and occupiers to drain into cantonment drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17336&sectionno=212&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf, the owner or occupier of any premises`
  line `having a private drain, or the owner of any private drain within cantonment may apply to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer to have his drain made to communicate with the cantonment drains and thereby to`
  line `discharge foul water and surface water from those premises or that private drain:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall entitle any person--`
  line
  line `(a) to discharge directly or indirectly into any cantonment drain--`
  line
  line `(i) any trade effluent from any trade premises except in accordance with bye-laws made in`
  line `this behalf; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any liquid or other matter the discharge of which into cantonment drains is prohibited by`
  line `or under this Act or any other law; or`
  line
  line `(b) where separate cantonment drains are provided for foul water and for surface water to`
  line `discharge directly or indirectly--`
  line
  line `(i) foul water into a drain provided for the surface water; or`
  line
  line `(ii) except with the permission of the Chief Executive Officer, surface water into a drain`
  line `provided for foul water; or`
  line
  line `(c) to have his drains made to communicate directly with a storm-water overflow drain.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person desirous of availing himself of the provisions of sub-section (1) shall give to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer notice of his proposals, and at any time within one month after receipt thereof, the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer may by notice to him refuse to permit the communication to be made, if it`
  line `appears to him that the mode of construction or condition of the drain is such that the making of the`
  line `communication would be prejudicial to the drainage system, and for the purpose of examining the mode`
  line `of construction and condition of the drain he may, if necessary, require it to be laid open for inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may, if he thinks fit, construct such parts of the work necessary for`
  line `having a private drain made to communicate with a cantonment drain, as is in or under a public street and`
  line `in such a case, the expenses incurred by the Chief Executive Officer shall be paid by the owner or`
  line `occupier of the premises, or as the case may be, the owner of the private drain and shall be recoverable`
  line `from the owner or occupier as an arrears of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (17337)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 213
  title `Drainage of undrained premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17337&sectionno=213&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any premises are in the opinion of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, without sufficient means of effectual drainage and a cantonment drain or some place`
  line `approved by the Chief Executive Officer for the discharge of filth and other polluted and obnoxious`
  line `matter is situated at a distance of not exceeding thirty metres from any part of the said premises, he may,`
  line `by written notice, require the owner of the said premises--`
  line
  line `(a) to make a drain emptying into such cantonment drain or place;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide and set up all such appliances and fittings as may appear to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer necessary for the purposes of gathering and receiving the filth and other polluted and`
  line `obnoxious matter from, and conveying the same off, the said premises and of effectually flushing`
  line `such drain and every fixture connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) to remove any existing drain or other appliance or thing used or intended to be used for`
  line `drainage which is injurious to health;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide a closed drain in substitution of an open drain or to provide such other appliance or`
  line `thing either newly or in substitution of any existing appliance or thing or to provide both a close drain`
  line `and such other appliance or thing in substitution of the existing open drain and other appliance or`
  line `thing, which is or is likely to be injurious to health;`
  line
  line `(e) to provide and set up all such appliances and fitting as may appear to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer to be necessary for the purpose of gathering and receiving the waste water from floors and`
  line `galleries of buildings when they are washed, and conveying the same through spouts, by down-take`
  line `pipes so as to prevent such waste water from discharging directly on streets or inside any lower`
  line `portion of the premises;`
  line
  line `(f) to carry out any work to improve or re-model an existing drain which is inadequate,`
  line `insufficient or faulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in any case not provided for in sub-section (1) any premises are, in the opinion of the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer, without sufficient means of effectual drainage, he may, by written notice, require`
  line `the owner of the premises`
  line
  line `(a) to construct a drain up to a point to be prescribed in such notice but not at a distance or more`
  line `than thirty meters from any part of the premises; or`
  line
  line `(b) to construct a closed cesspool or soakage pit and drain or drains emptying into such cesspool`
  line `or soakage pit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any requisition for the construction of any drain under sub-section (2) may contain any of the`
  line `details specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (17338)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 214
  title `New premises not be erected without drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17338&sectionno=214&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to erector to`
  line `re-erect any premises in a cantonment or to occupy any such premises unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a drain be constructed of such size, materials and description, at such level and with such fall`
  line `as shall appear to the Chief Executive Officer to be necessary for the effectual drainage of such`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(b) there have been provided and set up on such premises such appliances and fittings as may`
  line `appear to the Chief Executive Officer to be necessary for the purposes of gathering or receiving the`
  line `filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter from, and conveying the same off, the said premises`
  line `and of effectually flushing the drain of the said premises and every fixture connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) The drain so constructed shall empty into a cantonment drain situated at a distance of not`
  line `exceeding thirty meters from the premises; but if no cantonment drain is situated within that distance then`
  line `such drain shall empty into a cesspool situated within that distance to be specified by the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (17339)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 215
  title `Power to drain group or block of premises by combined operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17339&sectionno=215&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer that any group or block of premises may be drained more economically or`
  line `advantageously in combination than separately, and a cantonment drain of sufficient size already exists or`
  line `is about to be constructed within thirty metres of any part of that group or block of premises, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer may cause that group or block of premises to be drained by a combined operation.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses incurred in carrying out any work under sub-section (1) in respect of any group or`
  line `block of premises shall be paid by the owners of such premises in such proportions as the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may determine and shall be recoverable from them as an arrears of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Not less than fifteen days before any such work is commenced, the Chief Executive Officer shall`
  line `give to each such owner--`
  line
  line `(a) written notice of the nature of the proposed work; and`
  line
  line `(b) an estimate of the expenses to be incurred in respect thereof and of the proportion of such`
  line `expenses payable by him.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officer may require the owners of such groups or block or premises to`
  line `maintain the work executed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (17340)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 216
  title `Power to close or limit the use of private drains in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17340&sectionno=216&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `Where a drain connecting`
  line `any premises with a cantonment drain is sufficient for the effectual drainage of such premises and is`
  line `otherwise unobjectionable but is not in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, adapted to the general`
  line `system of drainage in the cantonment, he may, by written notice addressed to the owner of the premises,`
  line direct--
  line
  line `(a) that such drain be closed, discontinued or destroyed and that any work necessary for that`
  line `purpose be done; or`
  line
  line `(b) that such drain shall, from such date as may be specified in the notice in this behalf, be used`
  line `for filth and polluted water only or for rain water and unpolluted sub-soil water only:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no drain may be closed, discontinued or destroyed by the Chief Executive Officer under`
  line `clause (a) except on condition of his providing another drain equally effectual for the drainage of the`
  line `premises and communicating with any cantonment drain which he thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenses of the construction of any drain so provided by the Board and of any work done`
  line `under clause (a) may be paid out of the cantonment fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (17341)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 217
  title `Use of drain by a person other than the owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17341&sectionno=217&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where the Chief Executive Officer either`
  line `on receipt of an application from the owner of any premises or otherwise is of the opinion that the only, or`
  line `the most convenient means of effectual drainage of the premises into a cantonment drain is through a`
  line `drain belonging to another person, the Chief Executive Officer may by notice in writing require the owner`
  line `of such a drain to show cause within a period specified in the notice as to why an order under this section`
  line `should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where no cause is shown within the specified period or the cause shown appears to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer invalid or insufficient, the Chief Executive Officer may by order in writing either`
  line `authorise the owner of the premises to use the drain or declare him to be a joint owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made under sub-section (2) may contain directions as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the payment of rent or compensation by the owner of the premises;`
  line
  line `(b) the construction of a drain for the premises for the purpose of connecting it with the aforesaid`
  line drain;
  line
  line `(c) the entry upon the land in which the aforesaid drain is situate with assistants and workmen at`
  line `all reasonable hours;`
  line
  line `(d) the respective responsibilities of the parties for maintaining, repairing, flushing, cleaning and`
  line `emptying the aforesaid drain.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (17342)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Sewage and rain water drains to be distinct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17342&sectionno=218&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `Wherever it is provided in this Chapter that`
  line `steps shall or may be taken for the effectual drainage of any premises, it shall be competent to the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer to require that there shall be one drain for filth and polluted water and an entirely`
  line `distinct drain for rain water and unpolluted sub-soil water or both rain water and unpolluted sub-soil`
  line `water, each emptying into separate cantonment drains or other suitable places.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (17343)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Power to require owner to carry out certain works for satisfactory drainage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17343&sectionno=219&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `For the`
  line `purpose of efficient drainage of any premises, the Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) require any courtyard, alley or passage between two or more buildings to be paved by the`
  line `owner or owners of such buildings with such materials and in such manner as may be approved by the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer; and`
  line
  line `(b) require such paving to be kept in proper repair.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (17344)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Appointment of places for the emptying of drains and collection of sewage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17344&sectionno=220&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Executive Officer may cause any or all of the cantonment drains to empty into, and all sewage to be`
  line `collected of at, such place or places as he considers suitable:`
  line
  line `Provided that no place which has not been before the commencement of this Act used for any of the`
  line `purposes specified in this section shall, after such commencement be used there for without the approval`
  line `of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided further that on and after such date as may be appointed by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf no sewage shall be discharged into any water course until it has been so treated as not to affect`
  line `prejudicially the purity and quality of the water into which it is discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (17345)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 221
  title `Connection with water works and drains not to be made without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17345&sectionno=221&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `Without the`
  line `written permission of the Chief Executive Officer, no person shall, for any purpose whatsoever, at any`
  line `time make or cause to be made any connection or communicate with any drain referred to in section 210`
  line `or any water works, constructed or maintained by, or vested in, the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (17346)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 222
  title `Buildings, railways and private streets not to be erected or constructed over drains or water works without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17346&sectionno=222&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `(1)(a) No railway works shall be constructed on any cantonment`
  line `drain or any water works constructed or maintained by, or vested in the Board, without the approval of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(b) If any railway works are constructed on any drains or water works as aforesaid without the written`
  line `permission of the Central Government, the Chief Executive Officer may remove or otherwise deal with`
  line `the same as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2)(a) No private street shall be constructed and no building, wall, fence or other structure shall be`
  line `erected on any cantonment drain or on any water works constructed or maintained by, or vested in, the`
  line `Board without the approval of the Board.`
  line
  line `(b) If any private street is constructed or any building, wall, fence or structure erected on any drain or`
  line `water works as aforesaid without the written permission of the Board, the Chief Executive Officer may`
  line `remove or otherwise deal with the same as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses incurred by the Chief Executive Officer in doing so shall be paid by the owner of`
  line `the private street or of the building, fence wall or other structure or, as the case may be, by the railway`
  line `administration or the person offending and shall be recoverable as an arrears of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (17347)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 223
  title `Rights or user of property for aqueducts, lines, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17347&sectionno=223&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may`
  line `place and maintain aqueducts, conduits and lines of mains or pipes or drains over, under, along or across`
  line `any immovable property whether within or without the local limits of the cantonment without acquiring`
  line `the same, and may at any time for the purpose of examining, repairing, altering or removing any`
  line `aqueducts, conduits or lines of mains or pipes or drains, enter on any property over, under, along or across`
  line `which the aqueducts, conduits or lines of mains or pipes, or drains have been placed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not acquire any right other than a right of user in the property over,`
  line `under, along or across which any aqueduct, conduit or line of mains or pipes, or drain is placed.`
  line
  line `(2) The power conferred under sub-section (1) shall not be exercisable in respect of any property`
  line `vested in the Union or under the control or management of the Central Government or railway`
  line `administration or vested in any local authority save with the permission of the Central Government or`
  line `railway administration or the local authority, as the case may be, and in accordance with any bye-laws`
  line `made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Executive Officer may, without such permission, repair; renew, or amend any`
  line `existing works of which the character or position is not to be altered if such repair, renewal or amendment`
  line `is urgently necessary in order to maintain without interruption the supply of water, drainage or collection`
  line `of sewage or is such that delay would be dangerous to health, human life or property.`
  line
  line `(3) In exercise of the powers conferred upon him by this section, the Chief Executive Officer shall`
  line `cause as little damage and inconvenience as may be possible, and shall make full compensation for any`
  line `damage or inconvenience caused by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (17348)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 224
  title `Power of owner of premises to place pipes and drains through land belonging to other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17348&sectionno=224&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Chief Executive Officer that the only or most convenient means of`
  line `water supply to, and drainage of, any premises is by placing or carrying any pipe or drains over, under,`
  line `along or across the immovable property of another person, the Chief Executive Officer may, by order in`
  line `writing, authorise the owner of the premises to place or carry such pipe or drain over, under, along or`
  line `across such immovable property:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order the Chief Executive Officer shall give to the owner of the`
  line `immovable property a reasonable opportunity of showing cause within such time as may be prescribed by`
  line `bye-laws made in this behalf as to why the order should not be made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the owner of the premises shall not acquire any right other than a right of user in`
  line `the property over, under, along or across which any such pipe or drain is placed or carried.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the making of an order, under sub-section (1), the owner of the premises may, after giving`
  line `reasonable notice of his intention so to do, enter upon the immovable property with assistants and`
  line `workmen at any time between sunrise and sunset for the purpose of placing a pipe or drain over, under,`
  line `along or across such immovable property or for the purpose of repairing the same.`
  line
  line `(3) In placing or carrying a pipe or drain under this section, as little damage as possible shall be done`
  line `to the immovable property and the owner of the premises shall--`
  line
  line `(a) cause the pipe or drain to be placed or carried with the least practicable delay;`
  line
  line `(b) fill in, re-instate and make good at his own cost and with the least practicable delay, any land`
  line `opened, broken up or removed for the purpose of placing or carrying such pipe or drain; and`
  line
  line `(c) pay compensation to the owner of the immovable property and to any other person who`
  line `sustains damage by reason of the placing or carrying of such pipe or drain.`
  line
  line `(4) If the owner of the immovable property, over, under, along or across which a pipe or drain has`
  line `been placed or carried under this section whilst such immovable property was not built upon, desires to`
  line `erect any building on such property, the Chief Executive Officer, shall, by notice in writing, require the`
  line `owner of the premises to close, remove or divert the pipe or drain in such manner as shall be approved by`
  line `him and to fill in, re-instate and make good the immovable property as if the pipe or drain had not been`
  line `placed or carried over, under, along or across the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such requisition shall be made unless in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer it`
  line `is necessary or expedient for the construction of proposed building or the safe enjoyment thereof that the`
  line `pipe or drain should be closed, removed or diverted.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (17349)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 225
  title `Power to require railway level, etc., to be raised or lowered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17349&sectionno=225&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `If the Board places or carries`
  line `any pipe or drain or does any other work connected with the water supply or drainage across any railway`
  line `line, it may, with the sanction of the Central Government and at the cost of the cantonment fund, require`
  line `the railway administration to raise or lower the level thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (17350)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 226
  title `Power to execute work after giving notice to the person liable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17350&sectionno=226&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line `(1) When under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, any person may be required or is liable to execute any work, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer may, in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of any bye-laws made in this`
  line `behalf, cause such work to be executed after giving such person an opportunity of executing the same`
  line `within such time as may be specified by him for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses incurred or likely to be incurred by the Chief Executive Officer in the execution of`
  line `any such work shall be payable by the said person and the expenses incurred by the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer in connection with the maintenance of such work or the enjoyment of amenities and conveniences`
  line `rendered possible by such work shall be payable by the person or persons enjoying such amenities and`
  line conveniences.
  line
  line `(3) The expenses referred to in sub-section (2) shall be recoverable from the person or persons liable`
  line `there for as an arrears of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (17351)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `Power to affix shafts, etc., for ventilation of drain or cesspool.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17351&sectionno=227&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of`
  line `ventilating any drain or cesspool, whether vested in the Board or not, the Chief Executive Officer may, in`
  line `accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf, erect upon any premises or affix to the outside of any`
  line `building or to any tree any such shaft or pipe as may appear to him to be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (17352)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 228
  title `Power to examine and test drains, etc., believed to be defective.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17352&sectionno=228&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer that there are reasonable grounds for believing that a private drain or cesspool is`
  line `in such condition as to be prejudicial to health or a nuisance or that a private drain communicating`
  line `directly or indirectly with a cantonment drain is so defective as to admit sub soil water, he may examine`
  line `its condition, and for that purpose may apply any test, other than a test by water under pressure, and if he`
  line `deems it necessary, open the ground.`
  line
  line `(2) If on examination the drain or cesspool is found to be in proper condition, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer shall, as soon as possible, re-instate any ground which has been opened by him and make good`
  line `any damage done by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (17353)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 229
  title `Bulk delivery of sewage by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17353&sectionno=229&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall deliver in bulk all the sewage to,`
  line `the authority prescribed by the Central Government or the State Government, subject to such charges for`
  line `the delivery of sewage of the area of cantonment as may be determined by means of an agreement entered`
  line `into between that other authority and the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The agreement mentioned in sub-section (1) shall provide also for a stipulation therein that in case`
  line `of any dispute about the payments to be made to that other authority by the Board, the matter shall be`
  line `referred to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final and binding on both parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (17354)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 230
  title `Employment of Government agencies for repair, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17354&sectionno=230&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, for`
  line `reason to be recorded, direct that any specified work, repair, renewal or replacement which is to be`
  line `undertaken by or for the Board under this Chapter, shall be carried out on behalf of the Board by the`
  line `Central Government and the Board shall pay the charges there for at the rates and subject to the terms for the time being applicable in the case of works constructed by that Government on behalf of a local`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (17355)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 231
  title `Works to be done by licensed plumber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17355&sectionno=231&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a licensed plumber shall`
  line `execute any work described in this Chapter and no person shall permit any such work to be executed`
  line `except by a licensed plumber:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, the work is of a trivial nature, he may`
  line `grant permission in writing for the execution of such work by a person other than a licensed lumber.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who employs a licensed plumber to execute any work shall, when so required,`
  line `furnish to the Chief Executive Officer the name of such plumber.`
  line
  line `(3) When any work is executed except in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1), such`
  line `work shall be liable to be dismantled at the discretion of the Chief Executive Officer without prejudice to`
  line `the right of the Board to prosecute under this Act the person at whose instance such work has been`
  line executed.
  line
  line `(4) The Board may make bye-laws for the guidance of licensed plumbers and a copy of all such`
  line `bye-laws shall be attached to every licence granted to a plumber by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may, from time to time, prescribe the charges to be paid to licensed plumber for any`
  line `work done by them under or for any of the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(6) No licensed plumber shall, for any work referred to in sub-section (5), demand or receive more`
  line `than the charges prescribed there for, under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Board shall make bye-laws providing for--`
  line
  line `(a) the exercise of adequate control on all licensed plumbers;`
  line
  line `(b) the inspection of all works carried out by them; and`
  line
  line `(c) the hearing and disposal of complaints made by the owners or occupiers of premises with`
  line `regard to the quality of work done, material used, delay in execution of work, and the charges made,`
  line `by a licensed plumber.`
  line
  line `(8) No licensed plumber shall contravene any of the bye-laws made under this section or execute`
  line `carelessly or negligently any work under this Act or make use of bad materials, appliances or fittings.`
  line
  line `(9) If any licensed plumber contravenes sub-section (8), his licence may be suspended or cancelled`
  line `whether he is prosecuted under this Act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (17356)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 232
  title `Prohibition of certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17356&sectionno=232&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully obstruct any person acting under the authority of the Board, or the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, in setting out the lines of any works or pull up or remove any pillar, post or stake fixed in the`
  line `ground for the purpose of setting out lines of such work, or deface or destroy any works made for the`
  line `same purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully or negligently break, injure, turn on, open, close, shut off or otherwise interfere with`
  line `any lock, cock, valve, pipe, meter or other work or apparatus belonging to the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) unlawfully obstruct the flow of or flush, draw off, or divert, or take water from any water`
  line `work belonging to the Board; or`
  line
  line `(d) unlawfully obstruct the flow of or flush, draw off, or divert, or take sewage from any sewage`
  line `work belonging to the Board or break or damage any electrical transmission line maintained by the`
  line `Board; or`
  line
  line `(e) obstruct any officer or other employee of the Board in the discharge of his duties under this`
  line `Chapter or refuse or wilfully neglect to furnish him with the means necessary for the making of any`
  line `entry, inspection, examination or inquiry thereunder in relation to any water or sewage work; or`
  line
  line `(f) bathe in, at or upon any water work or wash or throw or cause to enter therein any animal, or`
  line `throw any rubbish, dirt or filth into any water work or wash or clean therein any cloth, wool or leather or the skin of any animal, or cause the water of any sink, or drain or any steam-engine or boiler or any`
  line `polluted water to turn or be brought into any water work, or do any other act whereby the water in any`
  line `water work is fouled or likely to be fouled.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall apply to a consumer closing the stopcock fixed on`
  line `the service pipe supplying water to his premises so long as he has obtained the consent of any other`
  line `consumer whose supply will be affected thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (17357)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 233
  title `Preparation of land use plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17357&sectionno=233&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the commencement of this Act, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer shall with the approval of the Board, cause to be prepared a spatial plan for land use to be`
  line `followed in the cantonment which shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) earmarking of zones for residential, institutional, commercial and other activities; and`
  line
  line `(b) improvement schemes for areas considered sub-standard on account of narrowness of streets,`
  line `poor lighting, poor ventilation or irregular line of buildings in a street.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall give publicity to the land use plan prepared under sub-section (1), by publishing a`
  line `gist of the plan in a local newspaper.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (17358)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 234
  title `Sanction for building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17358&sectionno=234&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `No person shall erect or re-erect a building on any land in a`
  line cantonment--
  line
  line `(a) in an area, other than the civil area, except with the previous sanction of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) in a civil area, except with the previous sanction of the Chief Executive Officer,`
  line
  line `nor otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and of the rules and bye-laws made`
  line `under this Act relating to the erection and re-erection of buildings:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an erected or re-erected building is meant for public purposes, then it shall be made`
  line `accessible to and barrier free for the persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (17359)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 235
  title `Notice of new buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17359&sectionno=235&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever intends to erect or re-erect any building in a`
  line `cantonment shall apply for sanction by giving notice in writing of his intention--`
  line
  line `(a) where such erection or re erection is in an area, other than the civil area, to the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) where such erection or re-erection is in a civil area, to the Chief Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, a person shall be deemed to erect or re-erect a building who--`
  line
  line `(a) makes any material alteration or enlargement of any building; or`
  line
  line `(b) converts into a place for human habitation any building not originally constructed for human`
  line habitation;
  line
  line `(c) converts into more than one place for human habitation a building originally constructed as`
  line `one such place; or`
  line
  line `(d) converts two or more places of human habitation into a greater number of such places; or`
  line
  line `(e) converts into a stable, cattle-shed or cow-house any building originally constructed for human`
  line `habitation; or`
  line
  line `(f) converts into a dispensary, stall, shops, warehouse, godown, factory or garage any building`
  line `originally constructed for human habitation; or`
  line
  line `(g) makes any alteration which there is reason to believe is likely to affect prejudicially the`
  line `stability or safety of any building or the condition of any building in respect of drainage, sanitation or`
  line `hygiene; or`
  line
  line `h) makes any alteration to any building which increases or diminishes the height of, or area`
  line `covered by, or the cubic capacity of, the building, or which reduces the cubic capacity of any room in`
  line `the building below the minimum prescribed by any bye-law made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (17360)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 236
  title `Conditions of valid notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17360&sectionno=236&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person giving the notice required by section 235 shall`
  line `specify the purpose for which it is intended to use the building to which such notice relates.`
  line
  line `(2) No notice shall be valid until the information required under the sub-section (1) and any further`
  line `information and plans and undertakings which may be required under bye-laws made under this Act have`
  line `been furnished to the satisfaction of the Chief Executive Officer, along with the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (17361)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 237
  title `Powers of Board under certain sections exercisable by Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17361&sectionno=237&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line The
  line `powers, duties and functions of the Board under section 238, sub-section (1) of section 241 section 243,`
  line `section 245 and section 248 excluding the provisions to sub-section (1) and the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of the said section 248 shall be exercised or discharged in a civil area by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (17362)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 238
  title `Power of Board to sanction or refuse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17362&sectionno=238&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may either refuse to sanction the`
  line `erection or re-erection, as the case may be, of the building, or may sanction it either absolutely or subject`
  line `to such directions as it thinks fit to make in writing in respect of all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the free passage or way to be left in front of the building;`
  line
  line `(b) the space to be left about the building to secure free circulation of air and facilitate scavenging`
  line `and the prevention of fire;`
  line
  line `(c) the ventilation of the building, the minimum cubic area of the rooms and the number of height`
  line `of the storeys of which the building may consist;`
  line
  line `(d) the provision and position of drains, latrines, urinals, cesspools or other receptacles for filth;`
  line
  line `(e) the level and width of the foundation, the level of the lowest floor and the stability of the`
  line structure;
  line
  line `(f) the line of frontage with neighbouring buildings if the building abuts on a street;`
  line
  line `(g) the means to be provided for egress from the building in case of fire;`
  line
  line `(h) the materials and method of construction to be used for external and party walls for rooms,`
  line `floors, fire-places and chimneys;`
  line
  line `(i) the height and slope of the roof above the uppermost floor upon which human beings are to`
  line `live or cooking operations are to be carried on; and`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter affecting the ventilation and sanitation of the buildings, and the person`
  line `erecting or re-erecting the building shall obey all such written directions in every particular.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may refuse to sanction the erection or re-erection of any building on any grounds`
  line `sufficient in the opinion of the Board affecting the particular building:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall refuse to accord sanction the erection or re-erection of any building if`
  line `such erection or re-erection is not in conformity with any general scheme sanctioned under section 240.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board, before sanctioning the erection or re-erection of a building on land which is under the`
  line `management of the Defence Estates Officer, shall refer the application to the Defence Estates Officer for`
  line `ascertaining whether there is any objection on the part of the Government to such erection or re-erection;`
  line `and the Defence Estates Officer shall return the application together with his report thereon to the Board`
  line `within thirty days after it has been received by him.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may refuse to sanction the erection or re-erection of any building--`
  line
  line `(a) when the land on which it is proposed to erect or re-erect the building is held on a lease from`
  line `the Government, if the erection or re-erection constitutes a breach of the terms of the lease; or`
  line
  line `(b) when the land on which it is proposed to erect or re-erect the building is entrusted to the`
  line `management of the Board by the Government if the erection or re-erection constitutes a breach of the`
  line `terms of the entrustment of management or contravenes any of the instructions issued by the`
  line `Government regarding the management of the land by the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) when the land on which it is proposed to erect or re-erect the building is not held on a lease`
  line `from the Government, if the right to build on such land is in dispute between the person applying for`
  line `sanction and the Government.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Board decides to refuse to sanction the erection or re-erection of the building, it shall`
  line `communicate in writing the reasons for such refusal to the person by whom notice was given.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Board neglects or omits, for one month after the receipt of a valid notice, to make and`
  line `to deliver to the person who has given the notice any order of any nature specified in this section, and`
  line `such person thereafter by a written communication sent by registered post to the Board calls the attention`
  line `of the Board to the neglect or omission, then, if such neglect or omission continues for a further period of`
  line `fifteen days from the date of such communication the Board shall be deemed to have given sanction to the`
  line `erection or re-erection, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in any case to which the provisions of sub-section (3) apply, the period of one month`
  line `herein specified shall be reckoned from the date on which the Board has received the report referred to in`
  line `that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (17363)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 239
  title `Order of stoppage of building or works in certain cases and disposal of things removed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17363&sectionno=239&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the erection of any building or execution of any work has been commenced or is being carried`
  line `on without or contrary to the sanction, but has not been completed, referred to in section 238 or in`
  line `contravention of any condition subject to which such sanction has been accorded or in contravention of`
  line `any provision of this Act or bye-laws made thereunder, the Chief Executive Officer may in addition to`
  line `any other action that may be taken under this Act, by order require the person at whose instance the`
  line `building or the work has been commenced or is being carried on to stop the same forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2) If an order made by the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (1) directing any person to stop`
  line `the erection of any building or execution of any work is not complied with, the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `may require any police officer to remove such person and all his assistants and workmen from the`
  line `premises or to seize any construction material, tool, machinery, scaffolding or other things used in the`
  line `erection of any building or execution of any work within such time as may be specified in the requisition`
  line `and such police officer shall comply with the requisition accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Any of the things caused or to be seized by the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (2) shall`
  line `be disposed of by him in a manner specified in sub-sections (6) and (7).`
  line
  line `(4) After the requisition under sub-section (2) has been complied with the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `may, if he thinks fit, depute by a written order a police officer or an officer or an employee of the Board`
  line `to watch the premises in order to ensure that the erection of the building or the execution of work is not`
  line continued.
  line
  line `(5) Where a police officer or an officer or an employee of the Board has been deputed under`
  line `sub-section (4) to watch the premises, the cost of such deputation shall be paid by the person at whose`
  line `instance such erection or execution is being continued or to whom notice under sub-section (1) was given`
  line `and shall be recoverable from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Any of the things caused to be removed by the Chief Executive Officer under this section shall`
  line `unless the owner thereof turns up to take back such things and pays to the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `charges for removal and storage of such things be disposed of by the Chief Executive Officer by a public`
  line `auction or in such other manner as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that such things shall only be disposed of by the Chief Executive Officer on the expiry of`
  line `fifteen days in case of non perishable things and twenty-four hours in case of perishable things from the`
  line `date and time of seizure.`
  line
  line `(7) The charges for removal and storage and sale of things sold under sub-section (6) shall be paid out`
  line `of the proceeds of the sale thereof and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the things sold on a claim being made therefor within a period of one year from the date of sale and if no such claim is made`
  line `within the said period, shall be credited to the cantonment fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (17364)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 240
  title `Power to sanction general scheme for prevention of overcrowding, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17364&sectionno=240&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `The General`
  line `Officer Commanding-in-Chief the Command in Consultation with the Principal Director may sanction a`
  line `general scheme of erection or re-erection of buildings within such limits as may be specified in the`
  line `sanction for the prevention of overcrowding or for purpose of sanitation, or in the interest of persons`
  line `residing within those limits or for any other purpose, and may, in pursuance of such scheme, impose`
  line `restrictions on the erection or re-erection of buildings within those limits:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such scheme shall be sanctioned by the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the`
  line `Command unless an opportunity has been given by a public notice to be published locally by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer requiring persons affected or likely to be affected by the proposed scheme, to file their`
  line `objections or suggestions in the manner specified in the notice, within a period of thirty days of the`
  line `publication of such notice, and the Chief Executive Officer shall after considering such objections and`
  line `suggestions, if any, forward the same along with his recommendations to the Principal Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (17365)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 241
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17365&sectionno=241&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `(1) No compensation shall be claimable by any person for any damage or loss`
  line `which he may sustain in consequence of the refusal of the Board of sanction to the erection of any`
  line `building or in respect of any direction issued by it under sub-section (1) of section 238.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall make compensation to the owner of any building for any actual damage or loss`
  line `sustained by him inconsequence of the prohibition of the re-erection of any building or of its requiring`
  line `any land belonging to him to be added to the street:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not be liable to make any compensation in respect of the prohibition of`
  line `the re-erection of any building which for a period of three years or more immediately preceding such`
  line `refusal has not been in existence or has been unfit for human habitation.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (17366)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 242
  title `Completion notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17366&sectionno=242&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `Every person to whom sanction for the erection or re-erection of any`
  line `building in any area in a cantonment has been given under section 237 or section 238 by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer or, as the case may be, by the Board shall, within thirty days after completion of the`
  line `erection or re-erection of the building give a notice of completion in writing to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer or the Board, as the case may be, and the Chief Executive Officer or the Board shall on receipt of`
  line `such notice cause the building to be inspected in order to ensure that the building has been completed in`
  line `accordance with the sanction given by the Chief Executive Officer or the Board, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (17367)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 243
  title `Lapse of sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17367&sectionno=243&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `Every sanction for the erection or re-erection of a building given or`
  line `deemed to have been given as herein before provided shall be available for two years from the date on`
  line `which it is given, and, if the building so sanctioned is not begun by the person who has obtained the`
  line `sanction or someone lawfully claiming under him within that period, it shall not thereafter be begun`
  line `unless the Chief Executive Officer, on application made there for has allowed an extension of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (17368)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 244
  title `Restrictions on use of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17368&sectionno=244&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without the written permission of the`
  line `Board or otherwise than in conformity with the conditions, if any, of such permission,--`
  line
  line `(a) use or permit to be used for human habitation any part of a building not originally erected or`
  line `authorised to be used for that purpose or not used for that purpose before any alteration has been`
  line `made therein by any work executed in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) change or allow the change of the use of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) convert or allow the conversion of one kind of tenement into another kind.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall on conviction be punishable`
  line `with a fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and in the case of continuing contravention with an`
  line `additional fine of rupees ten thousand for every day during which the contravention continues after the`
  line `date it comes to the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_245:
  sectionId (17369)
  sectionNo (245)
  orderNo 245
  title `Period for completion of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_245_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17369&sectionno=245&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line `A Board, when sanctioning the erection or re-erection of a`
  line `building as hereinbefore provided, shall specify a reasonable period after the work has commenced within which the erection or re-erection is to be completed, and, if the erection or re-erection is not completed`
  line `within the period so fixed, it shall not be continued thereafter without fresh sanction obtained in the`
  line `manner hereinbefore provided, unless the Board on application made therefor has allowed an extension of`
  line `that period:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than two such extensions, each for not more than one year, shall be allowed`
  line `in any case`
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  sectionId (17370)
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 246
  title `Completion certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17370&sectionno=246&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer shall on receipt of the notice under`
  line `section 242 of this Act cause the building to be inspected either by himself or by the officer authorised by`
  line `him in his behalf in order to ensure that the building has been completed in accordance with the sanction`
  line `given and issue completion certificate provided that the person seeking the completion certificate shall`
  line `assist the Chief Executive Officer in inspection of such building:`
  line
  line `Provided that the building shall not be occupied for habitation unless a certificate is issued by the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer or an officer authorised by him in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Chief Executive Officer fails within a period of thirty days after the receipt`
  line `of the notice of completion, to communicate his refusal to issue such certificate, such certificate shall be`
  line `deemed to have been granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_247:
  sectionId (17371)
  sectionNo (247)
  orderNo 247
  title `Illegal erection and re-erection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_247_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17371&sectionno=247&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line `Whoever begins, continues or completes the erection or`
  line `re-erection of a building--`
  line
  line `(a) without having given a valid notice as required by sections 235 and 236, or before the`
  line `building has been sanctioned or is deemed to have been sanctioned; or`
  line
  line `(b) without complying with any direction made under sub-section (1) of section 238; or`
  line
  line `(c) when sanction has been refused, or has ceased to be available or has been suspended by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 58,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and the cost of sealing the illegal`
  line `construction and its demolition.`
obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_248:
  sectionId (17372)
  sectionNo (248)
  orderNo 248
  title `Power to stop erection or re-erection or to demolish.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_248_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17372&sectionno=248&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may, at any time, by`
  line `notice in writing, direct the owner, lessee or occupier of any land in the cantonment to stop the erection or`
  line `re-erection of a building in any case in which the Board considers that such erection or re-erection is an`
  line `offence under section 247 and may, in any such case or in any other case in which the Board considers`
  line `that the erection or re-erection of a building is an offence under section 247, within twelve months of the`
  line `completion of such erection or re-erection in like manner, direct the alteration or demolition, as it thinks`
  line `necessary, of the building, or any part thereof, so erected or re-erected:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, instead of requiring the alteration or demolition of any such building or`
  line `part thereof, accept by way of composition such sum as it thinks reasonable:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall not, without the previous concurrence of the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, accept any sum by way of composition under the foregoing`
  line `proviso in respect of any building on land which is not under the management of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board shall by notice in writing direct the owner, lessee or occupier of any land in the`
  line `cantonment to stop the erection or re-erection of a building in any case in which the order under`
  line `section 238 sanctioning the erection or re-erection has been suspended by the`
  line `General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command, under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 58,`
  line `and shall in any such case in like manner direct the demolition or alteration, as the case may be, of the`
  line `building or any part thereof so erected or re-erected where the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the`
  line `Command, thereafter directs that the order of the Board sanctioning the erection or re-erection of the`
  line `building shall not be carried into effect or shall be carried into effect with modifications specified by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall pay to the owner of the building compensation for any loss actually`
  line `incurred by him in consequence of the demolition or alteration of any building which has been erected or re-erected prior to the date on which the order of the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the`
  line `Command, has been communicated to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_249:
  sectionId (17373)
  sectionNo (249)
  orderNo 249
  title `Power to seal unauthorised constructions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_249_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17373&sectionno=249&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_249_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, at any time, before or after making an order of demolition under section 248 or of the stoppage of`
  line `erection of any building, or execution of any work, to make an order directing the sealing of such erection`
  line `or work or of the premises in which such erection or work is being carried on or has been completed at`
  line `the cost of the offender in such manner as may be prescribed by rules for the purpose of carrying out the`
  line `provisions of this Act or for preventing any dispute as to the nature and extent of such erection or work.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any erection or work or any premises in which any erection or work is being carried on,`
  line `has or, has been sealed, the Chief Executive Officer may, for the purpose of demolishing such erection or`
  line `work in accordance with the provisions of this Act, order such seal to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall remove such seal except--`
  line
  line `(a) under an order made by the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) under an order of an appellate authority in an appeal made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes the provisions contained in sub-section (3) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_250:
  sectionId (17374)
  sectionNo (250)
  orderNo 250
  title `Courts not to entertain proceedings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_250_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17374&sectionno=250&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this`
  line `Act, no court shall entertain any suit, application or other proceedings in respect of any order or notice`
  line `unless an appeal under section 340 is preferred and the same is disposed of by the appellate authority`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 343 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), every suit, application or other`
  line `proceedings pending in any court immediately before the commencement of this Act shall continue to be`
  line `dealt with and disposed of by that court as if the said section has not been brought into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_251:
  sectionId (17375)
  sectionNo (251)
  orderNo 251
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_251_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17375&sectionno=251&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line `A Board may make bye-laws prescribing--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which notice of the intention to erect or re-erect a building in the cantonment`
  line `shall be given to the Board or, as the case may be, the Chief Executive Officer and the information`
  line `and plans to be furnished with the notice;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which and the form in which a notice of completion of erection or re-erection of`
  line `any building in the cantonment shall be given to the Board or, as the case may be, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer and the information and plans to be furnished with the notice;`
  line
  line `(c) the type or description of buildings which may or may not, and the purpose for which a`
  line `building may or may not, be erected or re-erected in the cantonment or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) the minimum cubic capacity of any room or rooms in a building which is to be erected or`
  line re-erected;
  line
  line `(e) the fees payable on provision by the Board of plans or specifications of the type of buildings`
  line `which may be erected in the cantonment or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) the circumstances in which mosque, temple or church or other sacred building may be erected`
  line `or re-erected; and`
  line
  line `(g) with reference to the erection or re-erection of buildings, or of any class of buildings, or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the line of frontage where the building abuts on a street;`
  line
  line `(ii) the space to be left about the building to secure free circulation of air and facilities for`
  line `scavenging and for the prevention of fire;`
  line
  line `(iii) the materials and method of construction to be used for external and party walls, roofs`
  line `and floors;`
  line
  line `(iv) the position, the materials and the method of construction of stair-cases, fire places,`
  line `chimneys, drains, latrines, privies, urinals and cess-pools;`
  line
  line `(v) height and slope of the roof above the uppermost floor upon which human beings are to`
  line `live or cooking operations are to be carried on;`
  line
  line `(vi) the level and width of the foundation, the level of the lowest floor, the stability of the`
  line `structure and the protection of building from dampness arising from sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(vii) the number and height of the storeys of which the building may consist;`
  line
  line `(viii) the means to be provided for egress from the building in case of fire;`
  line
  line `(ix) the safeguarding of wells from pollution; or`
  line
  line `(x) the materials and method of construction to be used for godowns intended for the storage`
  line `of food grains in excess of eighteen quintals in order to render them rat proof.`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  sectionId (17376)
  sectionNo (252)
  orderNo 252
  title `Prohibition of structures or fixtures which cause obstruction in streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_252_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17376&sectionno=252&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, except with the permission of the Chief Executive Officer, erect or set up any wall, fence, nail, post,`
  line `step, booth or other structure whether fixed or movable or whether of a permanent or temporary nature, or`
  line `any fixture in or upon any street so as to form an obstruction to, or an encroachment upon, or a projection`
  line `over, or to occupy any portion of such street, channel, drain, well or tank.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner or occupier of any such`
  line `building to alter or remove any such projection or encroachment as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of any projection or encroachment lawfully in existence at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Chief Executive Officer shall make compensation for any damage caused`
  line `by the removal or alteration.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may, by order in writing, give permission to the owners or occupiers`
  line `of buildings in any particular street to put up open verandahs, balconies or rooms projecting from any`
  line `upper storey thereof to an extent beyond the line of the plinth or basement wall at such height from the`
  line `level ground or street as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_253:
  sectionId (17377)
  sectionNo (253)
  orderNo 253
  title `Unauthorised buildings over drains, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_253_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17377&sectionno=253&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_253_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in`
  line `writing require any person who has, without his permission in writing, newly erected or re-erected any`
  line `structure over any public sewer, drain, culvert, water-course or water-pipe in the cantonment to pull down`
  line `or otherwise deal with the same as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_254:
  sectionId (17378)
  sectionNo (254)
  orderNo 254
  title `Drainage and sewer connections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_254_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17378&sectionno=254&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_254_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing,`
  line `require the owner or lessee of any building or land in any street, at his own expense and in such manner as`
  line `he thinks fit, to put up and keep in good condition, proper troughs and pipes for receiving and carrying`
  line `rain water from the building or land and for discharging the same or to establish and maintain any other`
  line `connection or communication between such buildings or land and a drain or sewer or a water harvesting`
  line `structure or facility.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of efficiently draining any building or land in the cantonment, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner or lessee of the building or land--`
  line
  line `(a) to pave, with such materials and in such manner as he thinks fit, any courtyard, alley or`
  line `passage between two or more buildings; or`
  line
  line `(b) to keep any such paving in proper repair; or`
  line
  line `(c) to make such arrangements as may be specified by the Board under bye-laws to deliver rain`
  line `water from roof top to the water harvesting facility created or arranged by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_255:
  sectionId (17379)
  sectionNo (255)
  orderNo 255
  title `Power to attach brackets for lamps and other accessories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_255_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17379&sectionno=255&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_255_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may`
  line `attach to the outside of any building, or to any tree in the cantonment, brackets for lamps or any`
  line `accessories for non-conventional sources of energy in such manner as not to occasion injury thereto or`
  line inconvenience.
obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_256:
  sectionId (17380)
  sectionNo (256)
  orderNo 256
  title `Maintenance of Roads.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_256_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17380&sectionno=256&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_256_content:
  string
  line `(1) All roads in the civil area of a cantonment shall be maintained by`
  line `the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All roads outside the civil area as have been vested in the Board shall also be maintained by the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_257:
  sectionId (17381)
  sectionNo (257)
  orderNo 257
  title `Temporary occupation of street, land, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_257_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17381&sectionno=257&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_257_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may, by order in`
  line `writing, permit the temporary occupation of any street, or of any land vested in the Board, for the purpose`
  line `of depositing any building materials or making any temporary excavation therein or erection thereon,`
  line `subject to such conditions as the Board may prescribe for the safety or convenience of the public, and`
  line `may charge a fee for such permission and may in his discretion withdraw such permission.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any article or thing is placed on any street or land under the management of the Board or`
  line `the Defence Estates Officer so as to form an obstruction thereto or any encroachment thereon, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer or, as the case may be, the Defence Estates Officer, may cause such article or thing to`
  line `be removed and recover from the person who placed such article or thing the expenses incurred in that`
  line `behalf in the same manner as moneys recoverable by the Board under section 324 and may also, if such`
  line `person fails to offer satisfactory explanation, order the confiscation of such article or thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_258:
  sectionId (17382)
  sectionNo (258)
  orderNo 258
  title `Closing and opening of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_258_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17382&sectionno=258&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_258_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may open any street for public use.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board shall not permanently close any street without the prior permission of the General Officer`
  line `Commanding in Chief, or the Principal Director:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such street shall be closed for reasons other than the security reasons and without`
  line `giving a public notice inviting objections and suggestions from the general public.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may, by public notice, temporarily close any street or any part of a`
  line `street for repair or for the purpose of carrying out any work connected with drainage, water-supply or`
  line `lighting or any other work which he is by or under this Act required or permitted to carry out:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, owing to any works or repairs or from any other cause, the condition of any`
  line `street or of any water-works, drain, culvert or premise vested in the Board, is such as to be likely to cause`
  line `danger to the public, the Board shall--`
  line
  line `(a) take all reasonable means for the protection of the adjacent buildings and land and provide`
  line `reasonable means of access thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) cause sufficient barriers or fences to be erected for the security of life and property, and cause`
  line `such barriers or fences to be sufficiently lighted from sunset to sunrise.`
obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_259:
  sectionId (17383)
  sectionNo (259)
  orderNo 259
  title `Names of streets and numbers of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_259_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17383&sectionno=259&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_259_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may determine the name or number`
  line `by which any area, street or public place in the cantonment shall be known and may cause name or`
  line `number to be affixed on any building in the cantonment in such place as it thinks fit and may also cause a`
  line `number to be affixed to any such building.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever destroys, pulls down, defaces or alters any such name or number or puts up any name or`
  line `number differing from that put up by the order of the Board shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) When a name or number has been affixed to any building under sub-section (1), the owner of the`
  line `building shall maintain the name or number in order, and shall replace it if removed or defaced, and if he`
  line `fails to do so the Chief Executive Officer may by notice in writing require him to replace it.`
obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_260:
  sectionId (17384)
  sectionNo (260)
  orderNo 260
  title `Group Housing Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_260_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17384&sectionno=260&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_260_content:
  string
  line `A Board, may in accordance with the bye-laws framed for the`
  line `purpose, allow the Group Housing Schemes for construction of houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_261:
  sectionId (17385)
  sectionNo (261)
  orderNo 261
  title `Boundary walls, hedges and fences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_261_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17385&sectionno=261&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_261_content:
  string
  line `(1) No boundary wall, hedge or fence of any material or`
  line `description shall be erected in a cantonment without the permission in writing of the Chief Executive`
  line Officer.
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner or lessee of any land in`
  line `the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) to remove from the land any boundary wall, hedge or fence which is in his opinion unsuitable,`
  line `unsightly or otherwise objectionable; or`
  line
  line `(b) to construct on the land sufficient boundary walls, hedges or fences of such material,`
  line `description or dimensions as may be specified in the notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) to maintain the boundary walls, hedges or fences of such lands in good order:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any such boundary wall, hedge or fence which was erected with the`
  line `consent or under the orders of the Chief Executive Officer or which was in existence at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Board shall make compensation for any damage caused by the`
  line `removal thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner, lessee or occupier of`
  line `any such land to cut or trim any hedge on the land in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line `specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_262:
  sectionId (17386)
  sectionNo (262)
  orderNo 262
  title `Felling, lopping and trimming or trees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_262_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17386&sectionno=262&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_262_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the opinion of a Board, the felling of`
  line `any tree of mature growth standing in a private enclosure in the cantonment is necessary for any reason,`
  line `the Board may, by notice in writing, require the owner, lessee or occupier of the land to fell the tree`
  line `within such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) cause to be lopped or trimmed any tree standing on land in the cantonment which belongs to`
  line `the Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice require all owners, lessees or occupiers of land in the cantonment, or by`
  line `notice in writing require the owner, lessee or occupier of any such land, to lop or trim, in such manner`
  line `as may be specified in the notice, all or any trees standing on such land or to remove any dead trees`
  line `from such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_263:
  sectionId (17387)
  sectionNo (263)
  orderNo 263
  title `Digging of public land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_263_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17387&sectionno=263&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_263_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, without the permission in writing of the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, digs up the surface of any open space in the cantonment, which is not private property, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred rupees and in the case of a`
  line `continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after`
  line `the first during which the offence continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_264:
  sectionId (17388)
  sectionNo (264)
  orderNo 264
  title `Improper use of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_264_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17388&sectionno=264&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, the working of a`
  line `quarry in the cantonment, or the removal of stone, earth or other material from the soil in any place in the`
  line `cantonment, is dangerous to persons residing in or frequenting the neighbourhood or such quarry or place,`
  line `or creates, or is likely to create, a nuisance, the Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing,`
  line `prohibit the owner, lessee or occupier of such quarry or place or the person responsible for such working`
  line `or removal, from continuing or permitting the working of such quarry or the moving of such material, or`
  line `require him to take such steps in the matter as he may direct for the purpose of preventing danger or`
  line `abating the nuisance arising or likely to arise therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in any case referred to in sub-section (1), the Chief Executive Officer is of opinion that such a`
  line `course is necessary in order to prevent imminent danger, he may, by order in writing, require a proper`
  line `hoarding or fence to be put up for the protection of passers-by.`
obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_265:
  sectionId (17389)
  sectionNo (265)
  orderNo 265
  title `Public markers and slaughter-houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_265_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17389&sectionno=265&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may provide and maintain, on the land`
  line `under its control, public markets and public slaughter-houses, to such number as it thinks fit, together`
  line `with stalls, shops, sheds, pens and other buildings or conveniences for the use of persons carrying on`
  line `trade or business in or frequenting such markets or slaughter-houses, and may provide and maintain in any such market buildings, places, machines, weights, scales and measures for the weighment or`
  line `measurement of goods sold therein.`
  line
  line `(2)When such market or slaughter-house is situated beyond cantonment limits, the Board shall have`
  line `the same power for the inspection and proper regulation of the same as if it were situated within those`
  line limits.
  line
  line `(3) The Board may at any time, by public notice, close any public market or public slaughter-house or`
  line `any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise the establishment of a public market or public`
  line `slaughter-house within the limits of any area administered by any local authority other than the Board,`
  line `without the permission of such local authority or otherwise than on such conditions as such local`
  line `authority may approve.`
obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_266:
  sectionId (17390)
  sectionNo (266)
  orderNo 266
  title `Use of public market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_266_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17390&sectionno=266&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without the general or special permission in`
  line `writing of the Chief Executive Officer, sell or expose for sale any animal or article in any public market.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of this section, and any animal or article exposed for sale`
  line `by such person, may be summarily removed from the market by or under the orders of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer or any official of the Board authorised by him in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_267:
  sectionId (17391)
  sectionNo (267)
  orderNo 267
  title `Power to transfer by public auction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_267_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17391&sectionno=267&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_267_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may transfer by public auction, for`
  line `any period not exceeding five years at a time, the right to occupy or use any stall, shop, standing, shed or`
  line `pen in a public market, or public slaughter-house or the right to expose goods for sale in a public market`
  line `or the right to weigh or measure goods sold therein, or the right to slaughter animals in any public`
  line `slaughter-house:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Board is of opinion that such transfer of the aforesaid rights by public auction`
  line `is not considered desirable or expedient, it may, with the previous sanction of the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or in his absence, the Principal Director,--`
  line
  line `(a) either levy such stallages, rents or fees as it thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(b) farm the stallages, rents and fees leviable under clause (a) for any period not exceeding one`
  line `year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the enjoyment of any such aforesaid right by any person for any length of time`
  line `shall never be deemed to create or confer any tenancy right in such stall, shop, standing, shed, pen, public`
  line `market or public slaughter-house.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may transfer by public auction or otherwise any immovable property other than in a`
  line `public market or a public slaughter house if such property is capable of being put to remunerative use for`
  line `such period and on such terms and conditions as may be approved by the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command or in his absence, the Principal Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_268:
  sectionId (17392)
  sectionNo (268)
  orderNo 268
  title `Stallages, rents, etc., to be published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_268_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17392&sectionno=268&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line `A copy of the table of stallages, rents and fees, if any,`
  line `leviable in any public market or public slaughter-house, and of the bye-laws made under this Act for the`
  line `purpose of regulating the use of such market or slaughter-house, printed in English language or in such`
  line `other language or languages as the Board may direct, shall be affixed in some conspicuous place in the`
  line `market or slaughter-house.`
obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_269:
  sectionId (17393)
  sectionNo (269)
  orderNo 269
  title `Private markets and slaughter-houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17393&sectionno=269&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place in a cantonment other than a public`
  line `market shall be used as a market, and no place in a cantonment other than a public slaughter-house shall`
  line `be used as a slaughter-house, unless such place has been licensed as a market or slaughter-house, as the`
  line `case may be, by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-sections shall apply in the case of a`
  line `slaughter-house established and maintained by the Central Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed--`
  line
  line `(a) to restrict these slaughter of any animal in any place on the occasion of any festival or`
  line `ceremony, subject to such conditions as to prior or subsequent notice as the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `with the previous sanction of the District Magistrate may, by public or special notice, impose in this`
  line `behalf; or`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent the Chief Executive Officer, with the sanction of the Board, from setting apart`
  line `places for the slaughter of animals in accordance with religious custom.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever omits to comply with any condition imposed by the Chief Executive Officer under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and,`
  line `in the case of continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to one thousand rupees for`
  line `every day after the first during which the offence is continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (17394)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 270
  title `Conditions of grant of licence for private market or slaughter-house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17394&sectionno=270&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may`
  line `charge such fees as it thinks fit to impose for the grant of a licence to any person to open a private market`
  line `or private slaughter-house in the cantonment, and may grant such licence subject to such conditions,`
  line `consistent with this Act and any bye-laws made thereunder, as it thinks fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may refuse to grant any such licence without giving reasons for such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (17395)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 271
  title `Penalty for keeping market or slaughter-house open without licence, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17395&sectionno=271&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person`
  line `who keeps open for public use any market or slaughter-house in respect of which a licence is required by`
  line `or under this Act, without obtaining licence therefor, or while the licence therefor is suspended, or after`
  line `the same has been cancelled, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and,`
  line `in the case of a continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for`
  line `every day after the first during which the offence is continued.`
  line
  line `(2) When a licence to open a private market or private slaughter-house is granted or refused or is`
  line `suspended or cancelled, the Board shall cause a notice of the grant, refusal, suspension or cancellation to`
  line `be pasted in English or such language or languages as it thinks necessary in some conspicuous place by or`
  line `near the entrance to the place to which the notice relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (17396)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 272
  title `Penalty for using unlicensed market or slaughter-house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17396&sectionno=272&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing that any`
  line `market or slaughter-house has been opened to the public without a licence having been obtained therefor`
  line `when such licence is required by or under this Act, or that the licence granted therefor is for the time`
  line `being suspended or that it has been cancelled, sells or exposes for sale any article in such market, or`
  line `slaughters any animal in such slaughter-house, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees and, in the case of a continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees for every day after the first during which the offence is continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (17397)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 273
  title `Prohibition and restriction of use of slaughter-house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17397&sectionno=273&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the opinion of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, it is necessary on sanitary grounds so to do, he may, by public notice, prohibit for such`
  line `period not exceeding one month, as may be specified in the notice, or for such further period not`
  line `exceeding one month, as he may specify by a like notice, the use of any private slaughter-house specified`
  line `in the notice, or the slaughter therein of any animal of any description so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notice issued under sub-section (1) shall be conspicuously pasted in the`
  line `slaughter-house to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (17398)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 274
  title `Power to inspect slaughter-houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17398&sectionno=274&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any official of a Board, authorised by order in`
  line `writing in this behalf by the Chief Executive Officer or the Health Officer, may, if he has reason to`
  line `believe that any animal has been, is being, or is about to be slaughtered in any place in contravention of`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter, enter into and inspect any such place at any time, whether by day or by`
  line night.
  line
  line `(2) Every such order shall specify the place to be entered and the locality in which the same is`
  line `situated and the period, which shall not exceed seven days for which the order is to remain in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (17399)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 275
  title `Power to regulate certain activities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17399&sectionno=275&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `A Board may, by order, regulate all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the days on, and the hours during, which any private market or private slaughter-house may be`
  line `kept open for use;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of the design, ventilation and drainage of such market or slaughter-houses, and`
  line `the material to be used in the construction thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) the keeping of such markets and slaughter-houses and lands and buildings appertaining thereto`
  line `in a clean and sanitary condition, the removal of filth and refuse therefrom, and the supply therein of`
  line `pure water and of a sufficient number of latrines and urinals for the use of persons using or`
  line `frequenting the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which animals shall be stalled at a slaughter-house;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which animals may be slaughtered;`
  line
  line `(f) the disposal or destruction of animals offered for slaughter which are, from disease or any`
  line `other cause, unfit for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(g) the destruction of carcasses which from disease or any other cause are found after slaughter to`
  line `be unfit for human consumption; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter with respect to the regulation of such markets and slaughter-houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (17400)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 276
  title `Provision of washing places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17400&sectionno=276&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may provide suitable places for the exercise by`
  line `washermen of their calling, and may require payment of such fees for the use thereof as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Board has provided such places as aforesaid it may, by public notice, prohibit the`
  line `washing of clothes by washermen at any other place in the cantonment:`
  line
  line `Provided that such prohibition shall not be deemed to apply to the washing by a washerman of his`
  line `own clothes or of the clothes of any other person who is an occupier of the place at which they are`
  line washed.
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any prohibition contained in a notice is sued under sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (17401)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 277
  title `Licences required for carrying on of certain occupations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17401&sectionno=277&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person of any of the`
  line `following classes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) butchers and vendors of poultry, game or fish;`
  line
  line `(b) persons keeping pigs for profit, and dealers in the flesh of pigs which have been slaughtered`
  line `within or without cantonment;`
  line
  line `(c) persons keeping milch cattle or milch goats for profit;`
  line
  line `(d) persons keeping for profit any animals other than pigs, milch cattle or milch goats;`
  line
  line `(e) dairymen, buttermen and makers and vendors of ghee;`
  line
  line `(f) makers of bread, biscuits or cake and vendors of bread, biscuits or cake made within or`
  line `without cantonment;`
  line
  line `(g) vendors of fruits or vegetables;`
  line
  line `(h) manufacturers of aerated or other potable waters or of ice or ice-cream, and vendors of the`
  line same;
  line
  line `(i) vendors of any medicines, drugs or articles of food or drink for human consumption`
  line `(other than the flesh of pigs, milk, butter, bread, biscuits, cake, fruit, vegetables, aerated or other`
  line `potable waters or ice or ice-cream) which are of a perishable nature;`
  line
  line `(j) vendors of spirituous liquor;`
  line
  line `(k) vendors of water to be used for drinking purposes;`
  line
  line `(l) washermen;`
  line
  line `(m) dealers in hay, straw, wood, charcoal or other inflammable material;`
  line
  line `(n) dealers in fire-works, kerosene oil, petroleum or any other inflammable oil or spirit;`
  line
  line `(o) tanners and dyers;`
  line
  line `(p) persons carrying on any trade or occupation from which offensive or unwholesome smells`
  line arise;
  line
  line `(q) vendors of wheat, rice and other grain or of flour;`
  line
  line `(r) makers and vendors of sugar or sweetmeats;`
  line
  line `(s) barbers and keepers of shaving saloons;`
  line
  line `(t) any other person carrying on such other trade, calling or occupation as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,`
  line
  line `shall carry on his trade, calling or occupation in any part of a cantonment unless he has applied for and`
  line `obtained a licence in this behalf from the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A licence granted under sub-section (1) shall be valid until the end of the year in which it is issued`
  line `and the grant of such licence shall not be withheld by the Board unless it has reason to believe that the`
  line `business which it is intended to establish or maintain would be offensive or dangerous to the public or`
  line `that the premises in which the business is intended to be established or maintained are unfit or unsuitable`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) no person who was, at the commencement of this Act, carrying on his trade, calling or`
  line `occupation in any part of a cantonment shall be bound to apply for a licence for carrying on such`
  line `trade or occupation in that part until he has received from the Board not less than three months notice`
  line `in writing of his obligation to do so, and if the Board refuses to grant him a licence, it shall pay`
  line `compensation for any loss incurred by reason of such refusal;`
  line
  line `(b) no person shall be required to take out a licence for the sale or storage of petroleum or for the`
  line `sale or possession for sale of poisons or white arsenic in any case in which he is required to take out a`
  line `licence for such sale, storage, or possession for sale by or under the Petroleum Act,`
  line `1934 (30 of 1934) or the Poisons Act, 1919 (12 of 1919).`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may charge for the grant of licences, under this section such reasonable fees, as it may`
  line `fix keeping in view the fees levied in this regard in a municipality in the State wherein such cantonment is`
  line situated.
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (17402)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 278
  title `Power to stop use of premises used in contravention of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17402&sectionno=278&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `If the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer is of opinion that any eating house, lodging house, hotel, boarding house, tea shop, coffee house,`
  line `cafe, restaurant, refreshment room or other place where public is admitted for repose or for consumption`
  line `of any food or drink or where food is sold or prepared for sale or any theatre, cinema hall, circus, dancing`
  line `hall or similar other place of public resort, recreation or amusement is kept open without a license or`
  line `otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a license granted in respect thereof, he may stop the use of`
  line `any such premises for any such purpose for a specified period by such means as he may consider`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (17403)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 279
  title `Conditions which may be attached to licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17403&sectionno=279&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `A licence granted to any person under`
  line `section 277 shall specify the part of the cantonment in which the licensee may carry on his trade, calling`
  line `or occupation, and may regulate the hours and manner of transport within the cantonment of any specified`
  line `articles intended for human consumption, and may contain any other conditions which the Board thinks`
  line `fit to impose in accordance with bye-laws made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (17404)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 280
  title `Power to vary licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17404&sectionno=280&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `If the Board is satisfied that any place used under a licence granted`
  line `under this Chapter is a nuisance or is likely to be dangerous to life, health or property, the Board may, by`
  line `notice in writing, require the owner, lessee or occupier thereof to discontinue the use of such place or to`
  line `effect such alternations, additions, or improvements as will, in the opinion of the Board, render it no`
  line `longer a nuisance or dangerous.`
obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (17405)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 281
  title `Carrying on trade, etc., without licence or in contravention of section 280.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17405&sectionno=281&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `carries any trade, calling or occupation for which a licence is required without obtaining a licence therefor`
  line `or while the licence therefor is suspended or after the same has been cancelled, and whoever, after`
  line `receiving a notice under section 280, uses or allows to be used any building or place in contravention`
  line `thereof, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and, in the case of a`
  line `continuing offence, with an additional fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after`
  line `the first during which the offence is continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (17406)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 282
  title `Feeding animals on dirt, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17406&sectionno=282&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `Whoever feeds or allows to be fed on filthy or deleterious`
  line `substances any animal, which is kept for the purpose of supplying milk to, or which is intended to be used`
  line `as food for, the inhabitants of a cantonment or allows it to graze in any place in which grazing has, for`
  line `sanitary reasons, been prohibited by public notice by the Board shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (17407)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 283
  title `Powers of entry and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17407&sectionno=283&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President or the Vice-President, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, the Health Officer, the Assistant Health Officer, or any other official of a Board authorised by it`
  line `in writing in this behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) may at any time enter into any market, building, shop, stall or other place in the cantonment`
  line `for the purpose of inspecting, and may inspect, any animal, article or thing intended for human food`
  line `or drink or for medicine, whether exposed or hawked about for sale or deposited in or brought to any`
  line `place for the purpose of sale, or of preparation for sale, or any utensil or vessel for preparing,`
  line `manufacturing or containing any such article, or thing, and may enter into and inspect any place used`
  line `as a slaughter-house and may examine any animal or article therein;`
  line
  line `(b) may seize any such animal, article or thing which appears to him to be diseased, or`
  line `unwholesome or unfit for human food or drink or medicine, as the case may be, or to be adulterated`
  line `or to be not what it is represented to be, or any such utensil or vessel which is of such a kind or in`
  line `such a state as to render any article prepared, manufactured or contained therein unwholesome or`
  line `unfit for human food, drink or medicine, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any article seized under sub-section (1) which is of a perishable nature may, under the orders of`
  line `the Health Officer or the Assistant Health Officer, forthwith be destroyed if, in his opinion, it is diseased,`
  line `unwholesome or unfit for human food, drink or medicine, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Every animal, article, utensil, vessel or other thing seized under sub-section (1) shall, if it is not`
  line `destroyed under sub-section (2), be taken before a Magistrate who shall give orders as to its disposal.`
  line
  line `(4) The owner or person in possession, at the time of seizure under sub-section (1), of any animal or`
  line `carcass which is diseased or of any article or thing which is unwholesome or unfit for human food, drink`
  line `or medicine, as the case may be, or is adulterated or is not what it is represented to be, or of any utensil or`
  line `vessel which is of such kind or in such state as is described in clause (b) of sub-section (1), shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, and the animal, article, utensil, vessel or`
  line `other thing shall be liable to be forfeited to the Board or to be destroyed or to be so disposed of as to`
  line `prevent it being exposed for sale or used for the preparation of food, drink or medicine, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `Explanation I.--If any such article, having been exposed or stored in, or brought to, any place`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1) for sale as ghee, contains any substance not exclusively derived from milk, it`
  line `shall be deemed, for the purposes of this section, to be an article which is not what it is represented to be.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--Meat subjected to the process of blowing shall be deemed to be unfit for human`
  line food.
  line
  line `Explanation III.--The article of food or drink shall not be deemed to be other than what it is`
  line `represented to be merely by reason of the fact that there has been added to it some substance not injurious`
  line `to health:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) such substance has been added to the article because the same is required for the preparation`
  line `or production thereof as an article of commerce in a state fit for carriage or consumption and not`
  line `fraudulently to increase the bulk, weight or measure of the food or drink or conceal the inferior`
  line `quality thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the process of production, preparation or conveyance of such article of food or drink, the`
  line `extraneous substance has unavoidably become intermixed therewith; or`
  line
  line `(c) the owner or person in possession of the article has given sufficient notice by means of a label`
  line `distinctly and legibly written or printed thereon or therewith, or by other means of a public`
  line `description, that such substance has been added; or`
  line
  line `(d) such owner or person has purchased the article with a written warranty that it was of a certain`
  line `nature, substance and quality and had no reason to believe that it was not of such nature, substance`
  line `and quality, and has exposed it or hawked it about or brought it for sale in the same state and by the`
  line `same description as that in and by which he purchased it.`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (17408)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 284
  title `Import of cattle and flesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17408&sectionno=284&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without the permission in writing of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, bring into a cantonment any animal intended for human consumption, or the flesh of`
  line `any animal slaughtered outside the cantonment otherwise than in a slaughter-house maintained by the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government or the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Executive Officer shall not grant such permission unless he has considered`
  line `the recommendation of the Health Officer made this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any animal or flesh brought into a cantonment in contravention of sub-section (1) may be seized`
  line `by the Chief Executive Officer or by any official of the Board and sold or otherwise disposed of as the`
  line `President of the Board may direct, and, if it is sold, the sale proceeds may be credited to the cantonment`
  line fund.
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to two thousand five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to cured or preserved meat or to animals driven`
  line `or meat carried through a cantonment for consumption outside thereof, or to meat brought into a`
  line `cantonment by any person for his immediate domestic consumption:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, by public notice, direct that the provisions of this section shall apply to`
  line `cured or preserved meat of any specified description or brought from any specified place.`
obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (17409)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 285
  title `Unauthorised sale of spirituous liquor or intoxicating drug.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17409&sectionno=285&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line `If within a cantonment, or`
  line `within such limit sad joining a cantonment as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, define, any person not subject to Army, Navy or Air Force law, or any person subject to Army,`
  line `Navy or Air Force law, otherwise than as a military officer or a soldier knowingly barters, sells or supplies, or offers or attempts to barter, sell or supply, any spirituous liquor or intoxicating drug to or for`
  line `the use of any soldier or soldier's wife or minor child without the written permission of the Officer`
  line `Commanding the station, or of some person authorised by the Officer Commanding the station, to grant`
  line `such permission, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (17410)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 286
  title `Unauthorised possession of spirituous liquor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17410&sectionno=286&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `If within a cantonment, or within any limits`
  line `defined under section 285--`
  line
  line `(a) any person subject to, Army, Navy or Air Force law, otherwise than as a military officer or a`
  line `soldier; or`
  line
  line `(b) the wife or servant of any such person or of a soldier,`
  line
  line `has in his or her possession, except on behalf of the Central Government or for the private use of a`
  line `military officer, more than one quart of any spirituous liquor, other than fermented malt-liquor, without`
  line `the written permission of the Officer Commanding the station or of some person authorised by the Officer`
  line `Commanding the station, to grant such permission, he or she shall be punishable, in the case of a first`
  line `offence, with fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred rupees, and, in the case of a`
  line `subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (17411)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 287
  title `Arrest of persons and seizure and confiscation of things for offences against the two last foregoing sections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for section 287 (w.e.f. 2-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17411&sectionno=287&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `^1[287. Arrest of persons, seizure and confiscation of things for offences under section 285.-- (1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any police`
  line `officer or excise officer may, without an order from a Judicial Magistrate, and without a warrant, arrest`
  line `any person who commits an offence under section 285 and may seize and detain any spirituous liquor or`
  line `intoxicating drug in respect of which an offence under section 285 has been committed and any vessels or`
  line `coverings in which the liquor or drug is contained.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person accused of an offence under section 285 has been previously convicted of an`
  line `offence under that section, an officer in charge of a police station may, with the written permission of a`
  line `Judicial Magistrate, seize and detain any spirituous liquor or intoxicating drug within the cantonment or`
  line `within any limits defined under that section which, at the time of the alleged commission of the`
  line `subsequent offence, belonged to, or was in the possession of, such person.`
  line
  line `(3) The court convicting a person of an offence under section 285 may order the confiscation of the`
  line `whole or any part of anything seized under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of Chapter XXXIV of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `anything, seized under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) and not confiscated under sub-section (3) shall`
  line `be restored to the person from whom it was taken.]`
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (17412)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 288
  title `Saving of articles sold or supplied for medicinal purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17412&sectionno=288&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `The foregoing provisions of this`
  line `Chapter shall not apply to the sale or supply of any article in good faith for medicinal purposes by a`
  line `medical practitioner, chemist or druggist authorised in this behalf by a general or special order of the`
  line `Officer Commanding the station.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (17413)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 289
  title `Penalty for causing nuisances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 2-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17413&sectionno=289&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) in any street or other public place within a cantonment,`
  line
  line `(i) is drunk and disorderly or drunk and incapable of taking care of himself; or`
  line
  line `(ii) uses any threatening, abusive or insulting words, or behaves in a threatening or insulting`
  line `manner with intent to provoke a breach of the peace, or whereby a breach of the peace is likely to`
  line `be occasioned; or`
  line
  line `(iii) eases himself, or wilfully or indecently exposes his person; or`
  line
  line `(iv) loiters, or begs importunately, for alms; or`
  line
  line `(v) exposes or exhibits, with the object of exciting charity, any deformity or disease or any`
  line `offensive sore or wound; or`
  line
  line `(vi) carries meat exposed to public view; or`
  line
  line `(vii) is found gaming; or`
  line
  line `(viii) pickets animals, or collects vehicles; or`
  line
  line `(ix) being engaged in the removal of night-soil or other offensive matter or rubbish, willfully`
  line `or negligently permits any portion thereof to spill or fall, or neglects to sweep away or otherwise`
  line `effectually to remove any portion thereof which may spill or fall in such street or place; or`
  line
  line `(x) without proper authority affixes upon any building, monument, post, wall, fence, tree or`
  line `other thing, any bill, notice or other document; or`
  line
  line `(xi) without proper authority defaces or writes upon or otherwise marks any building,`
  line `monument, post, wall, fence, tree or other thing; or`
  line
  line `(xii) without proper authority removes, destroys, defaces or otherwise obliterates any notice`
  line `or other document put up or exhibited under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(xiii) without proper authority displaces, damages, or makes any alteration in, or otherwise`
  line `interferes with the pavement, gutter, storm water-drain, flags or other materials of any such street,`
  line `or any lamp, bracket, direction-post, hydrant or water-pipe maintained by the Board in any such`
  line `street or public place, or extinguishes a public light; or`
  line
  line `(xiv) carries any corpse not decently covered or without taking due precautions to prevent risk`
  line `of infection or injury to the public health or annoyance to passers-by or to persons dwelling in the`
  line `neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(xv) carries night-soil or other offensive matter or rubbish at any hour prohibited by the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer by public notice, or in any pattern of vehicle or receptacle which has not been`
  line `approved for the purpose by the Chief Executive Officer, or fails to close such vehicle or`
  line `receptacle when in use; or`
  line
  line `(b) carries night-soil or other offensive matter or rubbish along any route in contravention of any`
  line `prohibition made in this behalf by the Chief Executive Officer by public notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) deposits, or causes or permits to be deposited, earth or materials of any description, or any`
  line `offensive matter or rubbish, in any place not intended for the purpose in any street or other public`
  line `place or waste or unoccupied land under the management of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(d) having charge of a corpse fails to bury, burn or otherwise lawfully dispose of the same within`
  line `twenty-four hours after death; or`
  line
  line `(e) makes any grave or buries or burns any corpse in any place not set apart for such purpose; or`
  line
  line `(f) keeps or uses, or knowingly permits to be kept or used, any place as a common gaming house,`
  line `or assists in conducting the business of any common gaming house; or`
  line
  line `(g) at any time or place at which the same has been prohibited by the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `public or special notice, beats a drum or tom-tom, or blows a horn or trumpet, or beats any utensil, or`
  line `sounds any brass or other instrument, or plays any music; or`
  line
  line `(h) disturbs the public peace or order by singing, screaming or shouting or by using megaphone`
  line `or loud-speaker; or`
  line
  line `(i) lets loose any animal so as to cause, or negligently allows any animal to cause, injury, danger,`
  line `alarm or annoyance to any person; or`
  line
  line `(j) being the occupier of any building or land in or upon which an animal dies, neglects within`
  line `three hours of the death of the animal, or, if the death occurs at night, within three hours after sunrise,`
  line either--
  line
  line `(i) to report the occurrence to the Chief Executive Officer or to an officer, if any, appointed`
  line `by him in this behalf with a view to securing the removal and disposal of the carcass by the public`
  line `conservancy establishment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to remove and dispose of the carcass in accordance with any general directions given by`
  line `the Board by public notice or any special direction given by the Chief Executive Officer on`
  line `receipt of such report as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(k) save with the written permission of the Chief Executive Officer and in such manner as he may`
  line `authorise, stores or uses night-soil, manure, rubbish or any other substance emitting an offensive`
  line `smell; or`
  line
  line `(l) uses or permits to be used as a latrine any place not intended for the purpose; or`
  line
  line `(m) uses or permits to be used without previous permission of the Chief Executive Officer any`
  line `premises for any trade involving offensive smell or smoke,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever does not take reasonable means to prevent any child under the age of twelve years being`
  line `in his charge from easing himself in any street or other public place within the cantonment shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred-fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or keeper of any animal found picketed or staying without a keeper in a street or other`
  line `public place in a cantonment shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Any animal found picketed or straying as aforesaid may be removed by any officer or employee`
  line `of the Board to a pound.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever in a cantonment manufactures, supplies, carries or uses for packaging or any other`
  line `purposes material of non-biodegradable nature including polythene bags shall be punished with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees or imprisonment which may extend to six months.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (17414)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 290
  title `Registration and control of dogs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17414&sectionno=290&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may make bye-laws to provide for the`
  line `registration of all dogs kept within the cantonment.`
  line
  line `(2) Such bye-laws shall--`
  line
  line `(a) require the registration, by any officer authorised in this behalf of all dogs kept in the`
  line cantonment;
  line
  line `(b) require that every registered dog shall wear a collar to which shall be attached a metal token to`
  line `be issued by the registration authority, and fix the fee payable for the issue thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) require that any dog which has not been registered or which is not wearing such token shall, if`
  line `found in any public place, be detained at a place set apart for the purpose; and`
  line
  line `(d) fix the fee which shall be charged for such detention and provide that any such dog shall be`
  line `liable to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of unless it is claimed and the fee in respect thereof is`
  line `paid within one week; and may provide for such other matters as the Board thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) cause to be destroyed, or to be confined for such period as he may direct, any dog or other`
  line `animal which is, or is reasonably suspected to be, suffering from rabies, or which has been bitten by`
  line `any dog or other animal suffering or suspected to be suffering from rabies;`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice direct that, after such date as may be specified in the notice, dogs which are`
  line `without collars or without marks distinguishing them as private property and are found straying on the treets or beyond the enclosures of the houses of their owners, if any, may be destroyed, and cause`
  line `them to be destroyed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) No damages shall be payable in respect of any dog or other animal destroyed or otherwise`
  line `disposed of under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever, being the owner or person in charge of any dog, neglects to restrain it so that it shall not`
  line `be at large in any street without being muzzled and without being secured by a chain lead in any case in`
  line which--
  line
  line `(a) he knows that the dog is likely to annoy or intimidate any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Board has, by public notice during the prevalence of rabies, directed that dogs shall not be`
  line `at large without muzzles and chain leads,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever in a cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) allows any ferocious dog which belongs to him or is in his charge to be at large without being`
  line `muzzled; or`
  line
  line `(b) sets on or urges any dog or other animal to attack, worry or intimidate any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) knowing or having reason to believe that any dog or animal belonging to him or in his charge`
  line `has been bitten by an animal suffering or reasonably suspected to be suffering from rabies, neglects to`
  line `give immediate information of the fact to the Chief Executive Officer or gives information which is`
  line false,
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (17415)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 291
  title `Traffic rule of the road.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17415&sectionno=291&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in driving, leading or propelling a vehicle along a street`
  line `fails, except in a case of actual necessity,--`
  line
  line `(a) to keep to the left when passing a vehicle coming from the opposite direction; or`
  line
  line `(b) to keep to the right when passing a vehicle going in the same direction as himself, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (17416)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 292
  title `Use of inflammable materials for buildings purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17416&sectionno=292&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may,`
  line `by public notice, direct that within such limits in the cantonment as may be specified in the notice, the`
  line `roofs and external walls of huts or other buildings shall not, without the permission in writing of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer be made or renewed of grass, mats, leaves or other inflammable materials, and may, by`
  line `notice in writing, require any person who has disobeyed any such direction as aforesaid to remove or alter`
  line `the roofs or walls so made or renewed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may, by notice in writing, require the owner of any building in the`
  line `cantonment which has an external roof or wall made of any such material as aforesaid to remove such`
  line `roof or wall within such time as may be specified in the notice, notwithstanding that a public notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) has not been issued or that such roof or wall was made with the consent of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer or before the issue of such public notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of any such roof or wall in existence before the issue of such a public notice`
  line `or made with the consent of the Chief Executive Officer, it shall make compensation, not exceeding the`
  line `original cost of constructing the roof or wall, for any damage caused by the removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (17417)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 293
  title `Stacking or collecting inflammable materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17417&sectionno=293&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `A Board may, by a public notice, prohibit in`
  line `any case where such prohibition appears to it to be necessary for the prevention of danger to life or`
  line `property, the stacking or collecting of wood, dry grass, straw or other inflammable materials, or the`
  line `placing of mats or thatched huts or the lighting of fires in any place in the cantonment, or within any`
  line `limits therein, which may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that Chief Executive Officer may, in case of imminent danger to public life or property,`
  line `enforce such prohibition in consultation with the President or the Vice-President in the absence of the`
  line President.
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (17418)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 294
  title `Care of naked lights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17418&sectionno=294&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `No person shall set a naked light on or near any building in any street or`
  line `other public place in a cantonment in such manner as to cause danger of fire:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit the use of lights for purpose of`
  line `illumination on the occasion of a festival or public or private entertainment.`
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (17419)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 295
  title `Regulation of cinematographic and dramatic performances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17419&sectionno=295&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law relating to sanctioning of cinematograph films for exhibition, no exhibition of`
  line `pictures or other optical effects by means of a cinematograph or other like apparatus for the purpose of`
  line `which inflammable films are used, and no public dramatic performance, pantomime, circus, carnival,`
  line `exhibition, dance or other similar show for public recreation or amusement, shall be given in any`
  line `cantonment elsewhere than in premises for which a licence has been granted by the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If the owner of a cinematograph or other apparatus uses the apparatus or allows it to be used, or if`
  line `any person takes any part in any public dramatic performance, pantomime, circus, carnival, exhibition,`
  line `dance or other similar show for public recreation or amusement, in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `section, or if the occupier of any premises allows them to be used in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this section or of any condition of any licence granted under this section, he shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, and, in the case of continuing offence, with an additional fine`
  line `which may extend to two thousand rupees for each day after the first during which the offence continues.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit the giving of any exhibition or any dramatic`
  line `performance, pantomime, circus, carnival, exhibition, dance or other similar show for public recreation or`
  line `amusement, in any theatre or institute which is the property of Government where the exhibition,`
  line `performance, pantomime, circus, carnival, exhibition, dance or other similar show for public recreation or`
  line `amusement, is held with the permission and under the control of the military authorities.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (17420)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 296
  title `Discharging fire-works, fire-arms, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17420&sectionno=296&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in a cantonment discharges any fire-arm or`
  line `lets off fire-works or fire-balloons, or detonates or engages in any game or carries on works such as`
  line `quarries, blasts, timber cutting or building operation in such manner as to cause or to be likely to cause`
  line `danger to persons passing by or dwelling or working in the neighbourhood or risk of injury to property`
  line `shall be liable to fine which may extend to two thousand five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (17421)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 297
  title `Power to require buildings, wells, etc., to be rendered safe.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17421&sectionno=297&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `Where in a cantonment any`
  line `building, or wall, or anything affixed thereto, or any well, tank, reservoir, pool, depression, or excavation,`
  line `or any bank or tree, is in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer, in a ruinous state or, for want of`
  line `sufficient repairs, protection or enclosure, a nuisance or dangerous to persons passing by or dwelling or`
  line `working in the neighbourhood, the Chief Executive Officer, by notice in writing may, require the owner,`
  line `or part-owner or person claiming to be the owner or part-owner thereof, or, failing any of them, the`
  line `occupier, thereof, to remove the same or may require him to repair, or to protect or to enclose, the same in`
  line `such manner as the thinks necessary; and, if the danger is, in the opinion of the Chief Executive Officer,`
  line `imminent, he shall forthwith take such steps as he thinks necessary to avert the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (17422)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 298
  title `Enclosure of wasteland used for improper purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17422&sectionno=298&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Executive Officer may, by`
  line `notice in writing, require the owner or part-owner, or person claiming to be the owner or part-owner, of`
  line `any building or land in the cantonment, or the lessee or the person claiming to be the lessee of any such`
  line `land, which, by reason of disuse or disputed ownership or other cause, has remained unoccupied and has`
  line `become the resort of idle and disorderly persons or of persons who have no ostensible means of`
  line `subsistence or cannot give a satisfactory account of themselves, or is used for gaming or immoral`
  line `purposes, or otherwise occasions or is likely to occasion a nuisance, to secure and enclose the same within`
  line `such time as may be specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (17423)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 299
  title `Power to remove brothels and prostitutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17423&sectionno=299&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `The Officer Commanding the Station or the Board`
  line `may, on receiving information that any building in the cantonment is used as a brothel or for purposes of`
  line `prostitution, by order in writing setting forth the substance of information received, summon the owner,`
  line `lessee, tenant or occupier of the building to appear before him or the Board as the case may be either in`
  line `person or by an authorised agent, and, if the Officer Commanding the Station or the Board, is then`
  line `satisfied as to the truth of the information, may, by order in writing, direct the owner, lessee, tenant or`
  line `occupier, as the case may be, to discontinue such use of the building within such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (17424)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 300
  title `Penalty for loitering and importuning for purposes of prostitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17424&sectionno=300&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever in a`
  line `cantonment loiters for the purpose of prostitution or importunes any person to the commission of sexual`
  line `immorality, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five thousand rupees and in case of subsequent offence shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to one year.`
  line
  line `(2) No prosecution for an offence under this section shall be instituted except on the complaint of the`
  line `person importuned, or of a military officer in whose presence the offence was committed, or of a member`
  line `of the Military, Naval or Air Force Police, being employed in the cantonment and authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Officer Commanding the Station, in whose presence the offence was committed, or of a`
  line `police officer not below the rank of Assistant Sub-Inspector, who is deployed in the cantonment and`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Officer Commanding the Station with the concurrence of District`
  line Magistrate.
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (17425)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 301
  title `Removal of persons from cantonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17425&sectionno=301&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `If the Officer Commanding the Station or the Board`
  line `is, after such inquiry as he or it thinks necessary, satisfied that any person residing in or frequenting the`
  line `cantonment is a prostitute or has been convicted of an offence, under section 300, or of the abetment of`
  line `such an offence he or, as the case may be, the Board may cause to be served on such person an order in`
  line `writing requiring such person to remove from the cantonment within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `order, and prohibiting such person from re-entering it without the permission in writing of the Officer`
  line `Commanding the Station or the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (17426)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 302
  title `Removal and exclusion from cantonment of disorderly persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17426&sectionno=302&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the First Class, having jurisdiction in a cantonment, on receiving information that any person residing`
  line `in or frequenting the cantonment--`
  line
  line `(a) is a disorderly person who has been convicted more than once of gaming or who keeps or`
  line `frequents, a common gaming house, a disorderly drinking shop or a disorderly house of any other`
  line `description; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted more than once either within the cantonment or elsewhere, of an offence`
  line `punishable under Chapter XVII of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860); or`
  line
  line `(c) has been ordered under Chapter VIII of the Code of Criminal Procedure,1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `either within the cantonment or elsewhere to execute a bond for his good behaviour,`
  line
  line `may record in writing the substance of the information received, and may issue a summon to such person`
  line `requiring him to appear and show cause why he should not be required to remove from the cantonment`
  line `and be prohibited from re-entering it.`
  line
  line `(2) Every summons issued under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a copy of the record`
  line `aforesaid and the copy shall be served along with the summons on the person against whom the summon`
  line `is issued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate shall, when the person so summoned appears before him, proceed to inquire into`
  line `the truth of the information received and take such further evidence as he thinks fit, and if upon such`
  line `inquiry it appears to him that such person is a person of any kind described in sub-section (1) and that it is`
  line `necessary for the maintenance of good order in the cantonment that such person is required to be removed`
  line `therefrom and be prohibited from re-entering the cantonment, the Magistrate shall inform the matter to the Officer Commanding the Station and, the Officer Commanding the Station shall cause to be served on`
  line `such person an order in writing requiring him to remove from the cantonment within such time as may be`
  line `specified in the order and prohibiting him from re-entering it without the permission in writing of the`
  line `Officer Commanding the Station.`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (17427)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 303
  title `Removal and exclusion from cantonment of seditious persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17427&sectionno=303&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person in a`
  line `cantonment causes or attempts to cause or does any act which he knows is likely to cause disloyalty;`
  line `disaffection or breach of discipline amongst any portion of the forces or is a person who, the Officer`
  line `Commanding the Station has reason to believe, is likely to do any such act, the Officer Commanding the`
  line `Station may make an order in writing setting forth the reasons for making of the same and requiring such`
  line `person to remove from the cantonment within such time as may be specified in the order and prohibiting`
  line `him from re-entering it without the permission in writing of the Officer Commanding the Station:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section against any person unless he has had a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being informed of the grounds on which it is proposed to make the order and of`
  line `showing cause why the order should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be sent to the Superintendent of Police of the`
  line `District, who shall cause a copy thereof to be served on the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon the making of any order under sub-section (1), the Officer Commanding the Station shall`
  line `forthwith send a copy of the same to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may of its own motion and shall on application made to it in this behalf`
  line `within one month of the date of the order by the person against whom the order has been made, call upon`
  line `the District Magistrate to make after such inquiry as the Central Government may prescribe a report`
  line `regarding the justice of the order and the necessity therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that at every such inquiry the person against whom the order has been made shall be given`
  line `an opportunity of being heard in his own defence.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, at any time after the receipt of the copy of an order sent under`
  line `sub-section (3) or where a report has been called for under sub-section (4), on receipt of that report, if it is`
  line `of opinion that the order should be varied or rescinded, make such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person who has been excluded from a cantonment by an order made under this section may,`
  line `at any time after the expiry of one month from the date thereof, apply to the General Officer`
  line `Commanding-in-Chief, the Command for the rescission of the same and, on such application being made,`
  line `the said Officer may, after making such inquiry, if any, as he thinks necessary, either reject the`
  line `application or rescind the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (17428)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 304
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17428&sectionno=304&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) fails to comply with an order issued under this Chapter within the period specified therein or`
  line `whilst an order prohibiting him from re-entering a cantonment without permission is in force,`
  line `re-enters the cantonment without such permission; or`
  line
  line `(b) knowing that any person has, under this Chapter been required to remove from the`
  line `cantonment and has not obtained the requisite permission to re-enter it, harbours or conceals such`
  line `person in the cantonment,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and in case of continuing offence`
  line `with an additional fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after the first during which`
  line `he has persisted in the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (17429)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 305
  title `Powers of entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17429&sectionno=305&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the President or the Vice-President of a Board, or the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer, or the Health Officer or any person specially authorised by the Chief Executive Officer, or the Health Officer or for any other person authorised by general or special order of a Board in`
  line `this behalf, to enter into or upon any building or land with or without assistants or workmen in order to`
  line `make any inquiry, inspection, measurement, valuation or survey, or to execute any work, which is`
  line `authorised by or under this Act or which it is necessary to make or execute for any of the purposes or in`
  line `pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule, bye-law or order made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to confer upon any person any power such as is`
  line `referred to in section 274 or section 283 or to authorise the conferment upon any person of any such`
  line power.
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (17430)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 306
  title `Power of inspection by member of a Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17430&sectionno=306&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `A Board may by special order authorise or order`
  line `any member to inspect any work or institution constructed or maintained, in whole or part, at the expense`
  line `of the Board, and any register, book accounts or other documents belonging to, or in the possession of,`
  line `the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (17431)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 307
  title `Power of inspection, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17431&sectionno=307&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board or the Chief Executive Officer may, by general or`
  line `special order, authorise any person--`
  line
  line `(a) to inspect any drain, privy, latrine, urinal, cesspool, pipe, sewer or channel in or on any`
  line `building or land in the cantonment, and, in his discretion, to cause, the ground to be opened for the`
  line `purpose of preventing or removing any nuisance arising from the drain, privy, latrine, urinal,`
  line `cesspool, pipe, sewer or channel, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) to examine works under construction in the cantonment, to take levels or to remove, test,`
  line `examine, replace or read any meter.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on such inspection, the opening of the ground is found to be necessary for the prevention or`
  line `removal of a nuisance, the expenses thereby incurred shall be paid by the owner or occupier of the land or`
  line `building, but if it is found that no nuisance exists or but for such opening would have arisen, the ground`
  line `or portion of any building, drain or other work opened, injured or removed for the purpose of such`
  line `inspection shall be filled in, reinstated, or made good, as the case may be by the Board or the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (17432)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 308
  title `Power to enter land, adjoining land where work is in progress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17432&sectionno=308&orderno=308&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive`
  line `Officer of a cantonment may, with or without assistants or workmen, enter on any land within fifty yards`
  line `of any work authorised by or under this Act for the purpose of depositing thereon any soil, gravel, stone`
  line `or other materials, or of obtaining access to such work, or for any other purpose connected with the`
  line `carrying on of the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer shall, before entering on any land under sub-section (1), give the`
  line `occupier, or, if there is no occupier, the owner not less than three day's previous notice in writing of his`
  line `intention to make such entry, and shall state the purpose thereof, and shall, if so required by the occupier`
  line `or owner, fence off so much of the land as may be required for such purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer shall, in exercising any power conferred by this section, do as little`
  line `damage as may be, and compensation shall be payable by the Board to the owner or occupier of such`
  line `land, or to both, for any such damage whether permanent or temporary.`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (17433)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 309
  title `Breaking into premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17433&sectionno=309&orderno=309&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any person, authorised by or under this Act to`
  line `make any entry into any place, to open or cause to be opened any door, gate or other barrier--`
  line
  line `(a) if he considers the opening thereof necessary for the purpose of such entry; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the owner or occupier is absent, or being present refuses to open such door, gate or barrier.`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (17434)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 310
  title `Entry to be made in the day time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17434&sectionno=310&orderno=310&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no entry`
  line `authorised by or under this Act shall be made except between the hours of sunrise and sunset.`
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (17435)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 311
  title `Owner‟s consent ordinarily to be obtained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17435&sectionno=311&orderno=311&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act,`
  line `no building or land shall be entered without the consent of the occupier, or if there is no occupier of the`
  line `owner thereof, and no such entry shall be made without giving the said occupier or owner, as the case`
  line `may be, not less than four hours, written notice of the intention to make such entry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notice shall be necessary if the place to be inspected is a factory or workshop or`
  line `trade premises or a place used for carrying on any trade, calling or occupation specified in section 277 or`
  line `a stable for horses or a shed for cattle or a latrine, privy or urinal or a work under construction, or for the`
  line `purpose of ascertaining whether any animal intended for human food is slaughtered in that place in`
  line `contravention of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (17436)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 312
  title `Regard to be had to social and religious usages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17436&sectionno=312&orderno=312&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `When any place used as a human dwelling`
  line `is entered under this Act, due regard shall be paid to the social and religious customs and usages of the`
  line `occupants of the place entered, and no apartment in the actual occupancy of a female shall be entered or`
  line `broken open until she has been informed that she is at liberty to withdraw and every reasonable facility`
  line `has been afforded to her for withdrawing.`
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (17437)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 313
  title `Penalty for obstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17437&sectionno=313&orderno=313&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `Whoever obstructs or molests any person acting on behalf of the`
  line `Board, who is not a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)`
  line `or any person with whom the Board has lawfully contracted, in the execution of his duty or of anything`
  line `which he is empowered or required to do by virtue or in consequence of any of the provisions of this Act`
  line `or any rule, bye-law or order made thereunder, or in fulfilment of his contract, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (17438)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 314
  title `Arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 2-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17438&sectionno=314&orderno=314&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `Any member of the police force employed in a cantonment may,`
  line `without a warrant, arrest any person committing in his view a breach of any of the provisions of this Act`
  line `which are specified in Schedule IV:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) ^1*** no person shall be so arrested who consents to give his name and address, unless there is`
  line `reasonable ground for doubting the accuracy of the name or address so given, the burden of proof of`
  line `which shall lie on the arresting officer, and no person so arrested shall be detained after his name and`
  line `address have been ascertained; and`
  line
  line `(b) no person shall be so arrested for an offence under section 300 except--`
  line
  line `(i) at the request of the person importuned, or of a military officer in whose presence the`
  line `offence was committed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by or at the request of a member of the Military, Naval or Air Force Police, who is`
  line `employed in the cantonment and authorised in this behalf by the Officer Commanding the`
  line `Station, and in whose presence the offence was committed or by or at the request of any police`
  line `officer not below the rank of assistant sub-inspector who is deployed in the cantonment and`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Officer Commanding the station.`
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (17439)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 315
  title `Duties of police officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17439&sectionno=315&orderno=315&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of all police officers to give immediate`
  line `information to the Board of the commission of, or attempt to commit any offence against the provisions`
  line `of this Act or of any rule or bye-law made thereunder, and to assist all cantonment officers and employees`
  line `in the exercise of their lawful authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (17440)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 316
  title `Notices to fix reasonable time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17440&sectionno=316&orderno=316&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice, order or requisition made under this Act or`
  line `any other rule or bye-law made thereunder requires anything to be done for the doing of which no time is`
  line `fixed in this Act or in the rule or bye-law, the notice, order or requisition shall specify a reasonable time`
  line `for doing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (17441)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 317
  title `Authentication and validity of notices issued by Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17441&sectionno=317&orderno=317&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, order or`
  line `requisition issued by a Board under this Act or any rule or bye law made thereunder shall be signed--`
  line
  line `(a) either by the President of the Board or by the Chief Executive Officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the members of any committee especially authorised by the Board in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever under this Act or any rule or bye-law made thereunder the doing of, or the omission to`
  line `do, anything or the validity of anything depends upon the approval, sanction, consent, concurrence,`
  line `declaration, opinion or satisfaction of the Board, a written document signed by any officer or member`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) purporting to convey or set-forth such approval, sanction, consent,`
  line `concurrence, declaration, opinion or satisfaction shall be sufficient evidence thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Every license, written permission, notice, bill summons or other document which is required by`
  line `this Act or any rule or bye-law made thereunder to bear the signature of the President, Vice-President or`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer, or of any such member of any committee as has been specially authorised by`
  line `the Board in this behalf shall be deemed to be properly signed if it bears facsimile of the signature of any`
  line `such officer or member, as the case may be, stamped thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (17442)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 318
  title `Service of notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17442&sectionno=318&orderno=318&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, order or requisition issued under this Act or any rule`
  line `or bye-law made thereunder shall, save as otherwise expressely provided, be served or presented--`
  line
  line `(a) by giving or tendering the notice, order or requisition, or sending it by post, to the person for`
  line `whom it is intended; or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person cannot be found, by affixing the notice order or requisition on some`
  line `conspicuous part of his last known place of abode or business, if within the cantonment, or by giving`
  line `or tendering the notice, order or requisition to some adult member or servant or his family, or by`
  line `causing it to be affixed on some conspicuous part of the buildings or land, if any, to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(2) When any such notice, order or requisition is required or permitted to be served upon an owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier of any building or land, it shall not be necessary to name the owner, lessee or occupier`
  line `therein, and the service thereof shall, save as otherwise expressly provided, be effected either--`
  line
  line `(a) by giving or tendering the notice, order or requisition, or sending it by post, to the owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier, or, if there are more owners, lessees, or occupiers than one to any one of them; or`
  line
  line `(b) if no such owner, lessee or occupier can be found, by giving or tendering the notice, order or`
  line `requisition to the authorised agent, if any, of any such owner, lessee or occupier, or to an adult`
  line `member or servant of the family of any such owner, lessee, occupier, or by causing it to be affixed on`
  line `some conspicuous part of the building or land to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(3) When the person on whom a notice, order or requisition is to be served is a minor, service upon`
  line `his guardian or upon an adult member or servant of his family shall be deemed to be service upon the`
  line minor.
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (17443)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 319
  title `Method of giving notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17443&sectionno=319&orderno=319&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `Every notice which, by or under this Act, is to be given or served as`
  line `a public notice or as a notice which is not required to be given to any individual therein specified shall,`
  line `save as otherwise expressly provided, be deemed to have been sufficiently given or served if a copy`
  line `thereof is affixed in such conspicuous part of the office of the Board or in such other public place during`
  line `such period, or is published in such local newspaper or in such other manner, as the Board may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (17444)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 320
  title `Powers of Board in case of non-compliance with notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17444&sectionno=320&orderno=320&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `In the event of non-compliance`
  line `with the terms of any notice, order or requisition issued to any person under this Act or any rule or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, requiring such person to execute any work or to do any act, it shall be lawful`
  line `for the Board, or the civil area committee or the Chief Executive Officer at whose instance the notice,`
  line `order or requisition has been issued whether or not the person in default is liable to punishment for such`
  line `default or has been prosecuted or sentenced to any punishment therefor, after giving notice in writing to`
  line `such person, to take such action or such steps as may be necessary for the completion of the act or work`
  line `required to be done or executed by him, and all the expenses incurred on such account shall be`
  line `recoverable by the Chief Executive Officer on demand, and if not paid within ten days after such demand,`
  line `shall be recoverable in the same manner as moneys recoverable by the Board under section 324:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the action or step relates to the demolition of any erection or re-erection under`
  line `section 248 or the removal of any projection or encroachment under section 252, the Board or the civil`
  line `area committee or the Chief Executive Officer may request any police officer to render such assistance as considered necessary for the lawful exercise of any power in this regard and it shall be the duty of such`
  line `police officer to render forthwith such assistance on such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (17445)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 321
  title `Occupier not to obstruct owner when complying with notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17445&sectionno=321&orderno=321&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of any property`
  line `in respect of which a notice as is referred to in section 320 has been given is prevented by the occupier`
  line `from complying with such notice, the Board or civil area committee or the Chief Executive Officer at`
  line `whose instance such notice has been given, may, by order, require the said occupier to permit the owner`
  line `within eight days from the date of service of such notice to take all such actions as may be necessary to`
  line `comply with the said notice and such owner shall, for the period during which he is prevented as`
  line `aforesaid, be exempt from any fine or penalty to which he might otherwise have become liable by reason`
  line `of non-compliance with such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (17446)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 322
  title `Liability of occupier to play in default of owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17446&sectionno=322&orderno=322&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any such notice as is referred to in`
  line `section 320 has been given to any person in respect of property of which he is the owner, and he fails to`
  line `comply with the notice so given, the Board or the civil area committee or the Chief Executive Officer at`
  line `whose instance such notice has been issued may require any occupier of such property or of any part`
  line `thereof to pay to it or him instead of to the owner any rent payable by him in respect of such property, as`
  line `it falls due, up to the amount recoverable from the owner under section 320:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the occupier, on application made to him by the Board or the civil area committee or`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer at whose instance such notice has been issued, refuses to truly disclose the`
  line `amount of his rent or the name or address of the person to whom it is payable, the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `may recover from the occupier the whole amount recoverable under section 320 in the same manner as`
  line `money is recoverable by the Board under section 324.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount recovered from an occupier instead of from an owner under sub-section (1) shall, in`
  line `the absence of any contract between the owner and the occupier to the contrary, be deemed to have been`
  line `paid to the owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (17447)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 323
  title `Relief to Agents and Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17447&sectionno=323&orderno=323&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person, by reason of his receiving the rent of`
  line `immovable property as an agent or trustee, or of his being as an agent or trustee the person who would`
  line `receive the rent if the property were let to a tenant, would under this Act be bound to discharge any`
  line `obligation imposed on the owner of the property for the discharge of which money is required, he shall`
  line `not be bound to discharge the obligation unless he has or but for his own improper act or default might`
  line `have had funds in his hands belonging to the owner sufficient for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving any fact entitling an agent or trustee to relief under sub-section (1) shall lie`
  line `upon him.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any agent or trustee has claimed and established his right to relief under this section, the`
  line `Board may, by notice in writing, require him to apply to the discharge of such obligation as aforesaid the`
  line `first monies which may come to his hands on behalf, or for the use, of the owner and on failure to comply`
  line `with the notice, he shall be deemed to be personally liable to discharge the obligation.`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (17448)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 324
  title `Method of recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17448&sectionno=324&orderno=324&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything elsewhere contained in this Act arrears of`
  line `any tax, and any other money recoverable, including rent on land and buildings due or damages and fine`
  line `due under leases or licences executed by or in favour of a Board or the Defence Estates Officer under this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder may be recovered together with the cost of recovery either by suit or on`
  line `application to a Judicial Magistrate having jurisdiction in the cantonment or in any place where the person`
  line `from whom such tax, rent or money is recoverable may for the time being be residing, either by the`
  line `distress and sale of movable property of such person, or by the attachment and sale of immovable`
  line `property of that person, which is within the limits of the jurisdiction of such Judicial Magistrate, or by`
  line `both these methods, and shall, if payable by the owner of any property as such, be a charge on the`
  line `property until paid :`
  line
  line `Provided that the tools of artisans, growing crops up to the value of five thousand rupees and`
  line `implements and cattle used for the purposes of agriculture shall be exempt from such distress or sale.`
  line
  line `(2) An application to a Judicial Magistrate under sub-section (1) shall be in writing and shall be`
  line `signed by the President or Vice-President of the Board or by the Chief Executive Officer or the Defence`
  line `Estates Officer or the Officer Commanding the Station or any other officer authorised by any of these`
  line `officers, but shall not require to be personally presented.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon receiving the application, the Judicial Magistrate referred to in sub-section (1) may take`
  line `action for the recovery of the amount of tax, rent or money from the person specified in the application as`
  line `if such amount were a fine recoverable under a sentence passed by him and the provisions of`
  line `sections 421 and 422 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to the recovery of such amount:`
  line
  line `Provided that the recovery of no such amount shall be made by the arrest or detention in prison of the`
  line `said person.`
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (17449)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 325
  title `Application for a Committee of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_325_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17449&sectionno=325&orderno=325&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `In the event of any disagreement as to the`
  line `liability of a Board to pay any compensation under this Act, or as to the amount of any compensation so`
  line `payable, the person claiming such compensation may apply to the Board shall for the reference of the`
  line `matter to a Committee of Arbitration, and the Board shall forthwith proceed to convene a Committee of`
  line `Arbitration to determine the matter in dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (17450)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 326
  title `Procedure for convening Committee of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17450&sectionno=326&orderno=326&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `When a Committee of Arbitration is to`
  line `be convened, the Board shall cause a public notice to be published stating the matter to be determined,`
  line `and shall forthwith send copies of the order to the District Magistrate, and to the other party concerned,`
  line `and shall, as soon as may be, nominate such members of the Committee as it is entitled to nominate under`
  line `section 327, and by notice in writing call upon the other persons who are entitled to nominate a member`
  line `or members of the Committee to nominate such member or members in accordance with provisions of`
  line `that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (17451)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 327
  title `Constitution of the Committee of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17451&sectionno=327&orderno=327&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Committee of Arbitration shall`
  line `consist of five members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman who shall be a person not in the service of the Government or the Board, and who`
  line `shall be nominated by the Officer Commanding the Station;`
  line
  line `(b) two persons nominated by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons nominated by the other party concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Board or the other party concerned or the Officer Commanding the Station fails within`
  line `seven days of the date of issue of the notice referred to in section 326 to make any nomination which it or`
  line `he is entitled to make or if any member who has been so nominated neglects or refuses to act and the`
  line `Board or other person by whom such member was nominated fails to nominate another member in his`
  line `place within seven days from the date on which it or he may be called upon to do so by the District`
  line `Magistrate, the District Magistrate shall forthwith appoint a member or members, as the case may be, to`
  line `fill the vacancy or vacancies.`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (17452)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 328
  title `No person to be nominated who has direct interest or whose services are not immediately available.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17452&sectionno=328&orderno=328&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who has a direct interest in the matter under reference, or whose services are`
  line `not immediately available for the purposes of the Committee shall be nominated a member of the`
  line `Committee of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the opinion of the District Magistrate any person who has been nominated has a direct`
  line `interest in the matter under reference or is otherwise disqualified for nomination or if the services of any`
  line `such person are not immediately available as aforesaid and if the Board or the other person by whom any`
  line `such person was nominated fails to nominate another member within seven days from the date on which it`
  line `or he may be called upon to do so by the District Magistrate, such failure shall be deemed to constitute a`
  line `failure to make a nomination within the meaning of section 327.`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (17453)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 329
  title `Meetings and powers of Committee or Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17453&sectionno=329&orderno=329&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Committee of Arbitration`
  line `has been duly constituted, the Board shall, by notice in writing inform each of the members of the fact,`
  line `and the Committee shall meet as soon as may be thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the Committee shall fix the time and place of the meetings and shall have power`
  line `to adjourn any meeting from time to time as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall receive and record evidence, and shall have power to administer oaths to`
  line `witnesses, and on requisition in writing signed by the Chairman of the Committee, the District Magistrate`
  line `shall issue the necessary processes for the attendance of witnesses and the production of documents`
  line `required by the Committee and may, enforce the said processes as if they were processes for attendance or`
  line `production before himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (17454)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 330
  title `Decisions of Committee of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17454&sectionno=330&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `(1) The decisions of every Committee of Arbitration`
  line `shall be in accordance with the majority of votes taken at a meeting at which the Chairman and at least`
  line `three of the other members are present.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is not a majority of votes in favour of any proposed decision, the opinion of the Chairman`
  line `shall prevail.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of a Committee of Arbitration shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (17455)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 331
  title Prosecutions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17455&sectionno=331&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no court shall proceed to the`
  line `trial of any offence made punishable by or under this Act, other than an offence specified in Schedule IV,`
  line `except on the complaint of or upon information received from the Board concerned or a person authorised`
  line `by the Board by a general or special order in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (17456)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 332
  title `Composition of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17456&sectionno=332&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Chief Executive Officer or any person authorised by him, by`
  line `general or special order in this behalf, may, before or after the institution of the proceedings, compound`
  line `an offence, made punishable by or under this Act other than an offence under Chapter XIV:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence shall be compoundable which is committed by failure to comply with a`
  line `notice, order or requisition issued by or on behalf of the Chief Executive Officer, unless and until the`
  line `same has been complied with in so far as compliance is possible.`
  line
  line `(2)Where an offence has been compounded, the offender, if in custody, shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of the offence so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (17457)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 333
  title `General penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17457&sectionno=333&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in any case in which a penalty is not expressly provided by this`
  line `Act, fails to comply with any notice, order or requisition issued under any provision thereof, or otherwise`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees, and, in the case of a continuing failure or contravention, with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees for everyday after the first during which he has persisted in the failure`
  line `or contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (17458)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 334
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17458&sectionno=334&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (17459)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 335
  title `Cancellation or suspension of licences, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17459&sectionno=335&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `Where any person to whom a licence or written`
  line `permission has been granted under this Act or any agent or servant of such person commits a breach of`
  line `any of the conditions thereof, or of any bye-law made under this Act for the purpose of regulating the`
  line `manner or circumstances in, or the conditions subject to, which anything permitted by such licence or`
  line `written permission is to be or may be done, or where the Board or the civil area committee, as the case`
  line `may be, is satisfied that such licence or written permission has been secured by the holder through`
  line `misrepresentation or fraud, the Board or the civil area committee, as the case may be, may, without`
  line `prejudice to any other penalty which may have been incurred under this Act, by order in writing, cancel`
  line `the licence or written permission or suspend it for such period as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless an opportunity has been given to the holder of the`
  line `licence or written permission to show cause why it should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (17460)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 336
  title `Recovery of amount payable in respect of damage to cantonment property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17460&sectionno=336&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `person has incurred a penalty by reason of having caused any damage to the property of a Board, he shall`
  line `be liable to make good such damage, and the amount payable in respect of the damage shall, in case of`
  line `dispute, be determined by the Judicial Magistrate by whom the person incurring such penalty is`
  line `convicted, and, on non-payment of such amount on demand, the same shall be recovered either by the`
  line `distress and sale of the movable property of such person, or by the attachment and sale of the immovable`
  line `property of that person, or by both these methods and the Judicial Magistrate shall recover the amount in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sections 421 and 422 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) as if it were a fine recoverable under a sentence passed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (17461)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 337
  title `Limitation for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17461&sectionno=337&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `No court shall try any person for an offence made punishable by`
  line `or under this Act, after the expiry of six months from the date of the commission of the offence, unless`
  line `complaint in respect of the offence has been made to a Judicial Magistrate within the six months`
  line aforesaid.
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (17462)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 338
  title `Protection of action of Board, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17462&sectionno=338&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `No suit or prosecution shall be entertained in any court`
  line `against a Board or against the Chief Executive Officer, the Officer Commanding a station, Defence`
  line `Estates Officer, Principal Director, General Officer Commanding in Chief, the Command, Director`
  line `General Defence Estates, or against any member of a Board, or against any officer or employee of a`
  line `Board, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done, under this Act or any rule or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (17463)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 339
  title `Notice to be given of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17463&sectionno=339&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit shall be instituted against any Board or against any`
  line `member of a Board, or against any officer or employee of a Board, in respect of any act done, or`
  line `purporting to have been done, in pursuance of this Act or of any rule or bye-law made thereunder, until`
  line `the expiration of two months after notice in writing has been left at the office of the Board, and, in the`
  line `case of such member, officer or employee, unless notice in writing has also been delivered to him or left`
  line `at his office or place of abode, and unless such notice states explicitly the cause of action, the nature of`
  line `the relief sought, the amount of compensation claimed, and the name and place of abode of the intending`
  line `plaintiff, and unless the plaint contains a statement that such notice has been so delivered or left.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Board or member, officer or employee has, before the suit is instituted, tendered sufficient`
  line `amounts to the plaintiff, the plaintiff shall not recover any sum in excess of the amount so tendered, and`
  line `shall also pay all costs incurred by the defendant after such tender.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit, such as is described in sub-section (1), shall, unless it is an action for the recovery of`
  line `immovable property or for a declaration of title thereto, be instituted after the expiry of six months from`
  line `the date on which the cause of action arises.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a suit in which the only relief claimed is an`
  line `injunction of which the object would be defeated by the giving of the notice or the postponement of the`
  line `institution of the suit or proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (17464)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 340
  title `Appeals from executive orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17464&sectionno=340&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any order described in the third`
  line `column of Schedule V may appeal to the appellate authority specified in that behalf in the fourth column`
  line `of the said Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, for the purposes of expeditious disposal of the pending appeals, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, amend Schedule V so as to designate additional appellate authority in`
  line `the fourth column of the said Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) No such appeal shall be admitted if it is made after the expiry of the period specified in that`
  line `behalf in the fifth column of the said Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) The period specified as aforesaid shall be computed in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), with respect to the computation of periods of limitation thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (17465)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 341
  title `Petition of Appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17465&sectionno=341&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every appeal under section 340 shall be made by petition in writing`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such petition may be presented to the authority which made the order against which the`
  line `appeal is made, and that authority shall be bound to forward it to the appellate authority, and may attach`
  line `thereto any report which it may desire to make by way of explanation.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (17466)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 342
  title `Suspension of Action Pending Appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17466&sectionno=342&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `On the admission of an appeal from an order, other`
  line `than an order contained in a notice issued under section 144, section 183, section 238, section 273 or`
  line `section 302, where the appellate authority so directs, all proceedings to enforce the order and all`
  line `prosecutions for any contravention thereof shall be held in abeyance pending the decision of the appeal,`
  line `and, if the order is set aside on appeal, disobedience thereto shall not be deemed to be an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (17467)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 343
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17467&sectionno=343&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an appeal from an order made by the Board has been disposed of by the`
  line `District Magistrate, either party to the proceedings may, within thirty days from the date thereof, apply`
  line `through the General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, the Command to the Central Government, or to such`
  line `authority as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf, for revision of the decision.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Chapter with respect to appeals shall apply, as far as may be, to the`
  line `applications for revision made under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The appellate authority shall make endeavours to dispose of the appeal made under section 340 of`
  line `this Act within a period of ninety days.`
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (17468)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 344
  title `Finality of the Appellate Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17468&sectionno=344&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in section 343, every order of`
  line `appellate authority shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (17469)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 345
  title `Right of appellant to be heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17469&sectionno=345&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `No appeal shall be decided under this Chapter unless the`
  line `appellant has been heard, or has had a reasonable opportunity of being heard in person or through a legal`
  line practitioner.
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (17470)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 346
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17470&sectionno=346&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after previous publication, make`
  line `rules to carry out the purposes and objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which, and the authority to which, application for permission to occupy and`
  line `belonging to the Government in a cantonment is to be made;`
  line
  line `(b) the authority by which such permission may be granted and the conditions to be annexed to`
  line `the grant of any such permission;`
  line
  line `(c) the allotment to a Board of a share of the rents and profits accruing from property entrusted to`
  line `its management under the provisions of section 63;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment, promotion, transfer, tenure of office, salaries and allowances, provident`
  line `funds, pensions, gratuities, leave of absence, discipline and other condition of service of employees of`
  line Boards;
  line
  line `(e) the circumstances in which security shall be demanded from employees of Boards and the`
  line `amount and nature of such security;`
  line
  line `(f) the keeping of accounts by Boards and the manner in which such accounts shall be audited and`
  line published;
  line
  line `(g) the definition of the persons by whom, and the manner in which, money may be paid out of a`
  line `cantonment fund or cantonment development fund;`
  line
  line `(h) the preparation of estimates of income and expenditure by Boards and the definition of the`
  line `persons by whom, and the conditions subject to which, such estimates may be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(i) the regulation of the procedure of Committees of Arbitration;`
  line
  line `(j) the prescribing of registers, statements and forms to be used and maintained by any authority`
  line `for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) the grant of leave to the members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(l) the form of notices, required to be sent under this Act and the manner of their service; and`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (17471)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 347
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17471&sectionno=347&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `(1) A rule under section 346 may be made either`
  line `generally for all cantonments or for the whole or any part of any one or more cantonments.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 346 shall include power to`
  line `give retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of the Cantonments Act,`
  line `2006, to the rules or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any rule so as to`
  line `prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such rule may be applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any rule has to be given retrospective operation, the reasons therefor and the`
  line `effect of giving such retrospective operation shall be published along with the draft of the rules when such`
  line `draft is published for eliciting public opinion under sub-section (1) of section 346.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner,`
  line `if any, as the Central Government may direct and, on such publication, shall have effect as if enacted in`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (17472)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 348
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17472&sectionno=348&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and of the rules made`
  line `thereunder, a Board may, in addition to any bye-laws which it is empowered to make by any other`
  line `provision of this Act, make bye-laws to provide for all or any of the following matters in the cantonment,`
  line `namely :--`
  line
  line `(1) the registration of births, deaths and marriages, and the taking of a census;`
  line
  line `(2) the enforcement of compulsory vaccination and inoculation and levy of fees where such`
  line `vaccination or inoculation is carried out at the houses of residents;`
  line
  line `(3) the regulation of the collection and recovery of taxes, tolls and fees under this Act and the`
  line `refund of taxes;`
  line
  line `(4) the regulation of any description of traffic in the streets and the enforcement of measures for`
  line `the reduction of noise caused thereby or the prohibition of any description of such traffic;`
  line
  line `(5) the manner in which vehicles standing, driven, led or propelled in the streets between sunset`
  line `and sunrise shall be lighted;`
  line
  line `(6) the seizure and confiscation of ownerless animals straying within the limits of the`
  line `cantonments and regulation and control of cattle pounds;`
  line
  line `(7) the prevention and extinction of fire;`
  line
  line `(8) the construction of scaffolding for building operations to secure the safety of the general`
  line `public and of persons working thereon;`
  line
  line `(9) the regulation in any manner not specifically provided for in this Act of the construction,`
  line `alteration, maintenance, preservation, cleaning and repairs of drains, ventilation-shafts, pipes,`
  line `water-closets, privies, latrines, urinals, cesspools and other drainage works;`
  line
  line `(10) the regulation or prohibition of the discharge into, or deposit in, drains of sewage, polluted`
  line `water and other offensive or obstructive matter;`
  line
  line `(11) the regulation or prohibition of the stabling or herding of animals, or of any class of animals,`
  line `so as to prevent danger to public health;`
  line
  line `(12) the proper disposal of corpses, the regulation and management of burial and burning places`
  line `and other places for the disposal of corpses, and the fees chargeable for the use of such places where`
  line `the same are provided or maintained by Government or at the expense of the cantonment fund;`
  line
  line `(13) the permission, regulation or prohibition of the use or occupation of any street or place by`
  line `itinerant vendors or by any person for the sale of articles or the exercise of any calling or the setting`
  line `up of any booth or stall, and the fees chargeable for such use or occupation;`
  line
  line `(14) the regulation and control of encamping grounds, sarais, hotels, dak-bangalows, lodginghouses,`
  line `boarding-houses, buildings let intenements, residential clubs, restaurants, eating-houses,`
  line `cafes, refreshment-rooms, guest houses, holiday resorts, cinemas and places of public recreation,`
  line `entertainment or resort;`
  line
  line `(15) the regulation of the ventilation, lighting, cleansing, drainage and water-supply of the`
  line `buildings used for the manufacture or sale of aerated or other potable waters and of butter, milk,`
  line `sweetmeats and other articles of food or drink for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(16) the matters regarding which conditions may be imposed by licences granted under`
  line `section 295 or section 277;`
  line
  line `(17) the control and supervision of places where dangerous or offensive trades are carried on so`
  line `as to secure cleanliness therein or to minimise any injurious, offensive or dangerous effects arising or`
  line `likely to arise there from;`
  line
  line `(18) the regulation of the erection of any enclosure, fence, tent, awning or other temporary`
  line `structure of whatsoever material or nature on any land situated within the cantonment and the fees`
  line `chargeable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(19) the laying out of streets, and the regulation and prohibition of the erection of buildings`
  line `without adequate provision being made for the laying out and location of streets;`
  line
  line `(20) the form of and the particulars which shall be contained in a development scheme or an`
  line `improvement scheme and the manner in which such scheme shall be framed or altered and levy of`
  line `development charges;`
  line
  line `(21) the regulation of the use of public parks and gardens and other public places, and the`
  line `protection of avenues, trees, grass and other appurtenances of streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(22) the regulation of the grazing of animals and the fees chargeable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(23) the fixing and regulation of the use of public bathing and washing places;`
  line
  line `(24) the regulation of the posting of bills and advertisment, and of the position, size, shape or`
  line `style or name boards, sign-boards and sign-posts;`
  line
  line `(25) the fixation of a method for the sale of articles whether by measure, weight, piece or any`
  line `other method;`
  line
  line `(26) the rendering necessary of licences within the cantonment for--`
  line
  line `(a) persons working as job porters for the conveyance of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) animals or vehicles let out on hire or used for hawking articles;`
  line
  line `(c) the proprietors or drivers of vehicles, boats or other conveyances, or of animals kept or`
  line `plying for hire or used for hawking articles;`
  line
  line `(d) persons impelling or carrying such vehicles or other conveyances; or`
  line
  line `(e) persons practising as nurses, midwives or dais;`
  line
  line `(27) the prescribing of the fee payable for any licence required under clause (26), and of the`
  line `conditions subject to which such licences may be granted, revised, suspended or withdrawn;`
  line
  line `(28) the regulation of the charges to be made for the services of such job porters and of the hire of`
  line `such animals, vehicles or other conveyances, and for the remuneration of persons impelling or`
  line `carrying such vehicles or conveyances as are referred to in clause (26);`
  line
  line `(29) the prescribing of fee payable for any licence except as otherwise specifically provided in the`
  line `Act, sanction or for any written permission granted by the Chief Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(30) the regulation or prohibition, for purposes of sanitation or the prevention of disease or the`
  line `promotion of public safety or convenience, of any act which occasions or is likely to occasion a`
  line `nuisance, and for the regulation or prohibition of which no provision is made elsewhere by or under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(31) the circumstances and the manner in which owners of buildings or land in the cantonment,`
  line `who are temporarily absent from, or are not resident in, the cantonment, may be required to appoint as`
  line `their agents, for all or any of the purposes of this Act of any rule or bye-law made thereunder, persons`
  line `residing within or near the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(32) the prevention of the spread of infectious or contagious diseases within the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(33) the segregation in, or the removal and exclusion from, the cantonment, or the destruction, of`
  line `animals suffering from or reasonably suspected to be suffering from any infectious or contagious`
  line disease;
  line
  line `(34) the supervision, regulation, conservation and protection from injury, contamination or`
  line `trespass of sources and means of public water-supply and of appliances for the distribution of water`
  line `whether within or without the limits of the cantonment;`
  line
  line `(35) the manner in which connections with water-works may be constructed or maintained, and`
  line `the agency which shall or may be employed for such construction and maintenance;`
  line
  line `(36) the regulation of all matters and things relating to the supply and use of water including the`
  line `collection and recovery of charges there for and the prevention of evasion of the same;`
  line
  line `(37) the maintenance of schools, and the furtherance of education generally;`
  line
  line `(38) the regulation or prohibition of the cutting or destruction of trees or shrubs, or of the making`
  line `of excavations, or of the removal of soil or quarrying, where such regulation or prohibition appears to`
  line `the Board to be not prejudicial to the maintenance of ecological balance and to be necessary for the`
  line `maintenance of a water-supply, the preservation of the soil, the prevention of landscape or of the`
  line `formation of ravines or torrents, or the protection of land against erosion, or against the deposit`
  line `thereon of sand, gravel or stones;`
  line
  line `(39) the rendering necessary of licences for the use of premises within the cantonment as stables,`
  line `kennels, sites or cow houses or as accommodation for sheep, goats or fowls;`
  line
  line `(40) the control of the use in the cantonment of mechanical whistles, sirens or trumpets;`
  line
  line `(41) the regulation of supply of copies of official document and prescribing the fee payable in`
  line `respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(42) the regulation of permission for granting licence for use of loud-speakers and prescribing the`
  line `fee payable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(43) the conservation and maintenance of ancient and historical monuments, archaeological sites`
  line `and remains or place of public importance in the cantonment; and`
  line
  line `44) generally for the regulation of the administration of the cantonment under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (17473)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 349
  title `Penalty for breach of bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17473&sectionno=349&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any bye-law made by a Board under this Act may`
  line `provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees; or`
  line
  line `(b) with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and, in the case of a continuing`
  line `contravention, with an additional fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every day during`
  line `which such contravention continues after conviction for the first such contravention; or`
  line
  line `(c) with fine which may extend to one hundred fifty rupees for every day during which the`
  line `contravention continues after the receipt of a notice from the Board or Chief Executive Officer by the`
  line `person contravening the bye-law requiring such person to discontinue such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such bye-law may also provide that a person contravening the same shall be required to`
  line `remedy, so far as lies in his power, the damage or mischief, if any, caused by such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (17474)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 350
  title `Supplemental provisions regarding bye-laws and regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17474&sectionno=350&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any power to make`
  line `bye-laws conferred by this Act is conferred subject to the conditions of bye-laws being made after`
  line `previous publication and of their not taking effect until they have been approved and confirmed by the`
  line `Central Government and published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government in confirming a bye-law may make any change therein which appears to`
  line `it to be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, after previous publication of its intention, cancel any bye-law`
  line `which it has confirmed, and thereupon the bye-law shall cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `(4) Every bye-law and Regulation made under this Act and every order made under sub-section (3)`
  line `shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for`
  line `a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the bye-law and Regulation, or order or both`
  line `Houses agree that the bye-law and Regulation, or order should not be made, the bye-law and Regulation,`
  line `or order shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that bye-law and Regulation or order.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (17475)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 351
  title `Rules and bye-laws to be available for inspection and purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17475&sectionno=351&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of all rules and`
  line `bye-laws made under this Act shall be kept at the office of the Board and shall, during office hours, be`
  line `open free of charge to inspection by any inhabitant of the cantonment.`
  line
  line `(2) Copies of all such rules and bye-laws shall be kept at the office of the Board and shall be sold to`
  line `the public at cost price singly, or in collection at the option of the purchaser.`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (17476)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 352
  title `Extension of certain provisions of the Act and rules to place beyond cantonments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17476&sectionno=352&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, and subject to any conditions as to`
  line `compensation or otherwise which thinks fit to impose, extend to any area beyond a cantonment and in the`
  line `vicinity thereof, with or without restriction or modification, any of the provisions of Chapters VIII to XV`
  line `or of any rule or bye-law made under this Act for the cantonment which relates to the subject-matter of`
  line `any of those Chapters, and every enactment, rule or bye-law so extended shall thereupon apply to that`
  line `area as if the area were included in the cantonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (17477)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 353
  title `Power to delegate functions to the President, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17477&sectionno=353&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by a resolution passed`
  line `in this behalf, delegate to the President, Vice-President, Chief Executive Officer or Health Officer, subject`
  line `to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the resolution, all or any of its functions under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (5) of section 290, section 168, section170, section 175, section 167, section 263 and`
  line `section 264.`
  line
  line `(2) The civil area committee may, by passing a similar resolution, delegate subject to such conditions,`
  line `if any, as may be specified in such resolution, all or any of its functions to the Vice-President, Chief`
  line `Executive Officer or Health Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (17478)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 354
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17478&sectionno=354&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `(1) Paragraphs 2 and 3 of section 54, and section 59, 107 and 123 of the Transfer`
  line `of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), with respect to the transfer of property by registered instrument, shall,`
  line `on and from the commencement of this Act, extend to every cantonment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar or Sub-Registrar of the district or sub-district formed for the purposes of the`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) in which any cantonment is situated, shall, when any document`
  line `relating to immovable property within the cantonment is registered, send information of the registration`
  line `forthwith to the Chief Executive Officer and the Defence Estates Officer and such other authority as the`
  line `Central Government may prescribe in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (17479)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 355
  title `Validity of notices and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17479&sectionno=355&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `No notice, order, requisition, licence, permission in`
  line `writing or other such document issued under this Act shall be invalid merely by reason of any defect of`
  line form.
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (17480)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 356
  title `Admissibility of document or entry as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17480&sectionno=356&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, plan,`
  line `notice, order or other document or of any entry in a register, in the possession of a Board shall, if duly`
  line `certified by the legal keeper thereof or other person authorised by the Chief Executive Officer in this`
  line `behalf, be admissible in evidence of the existence of the document or entry, and shall be admitted as`
  line `evidence of the matters and transactions there in recorded in every case where, and to the same extent to`
  line `which, the original documents or entry would, if produced, have been admissible to prove such matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (17481)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 357
  title `Evidence by officer or employee of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17481&sectionno=357&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `No officer or employee of a Board shall, in`
  line `any legal proceeding to which the Board is not party, be required to produce any register or document the`
  line `contents of which can be proved under section 356 by a certified copy, or to appear as a witness to prove`
  line `any matter or transaction recorded therein save by order of the court made for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (17482)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 358
  title `Application of Act 4 of 1899.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17482&sectionno=358&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Government Buildings Act, 1899,`
  line `cantonments and Boards shall be deemed to be municipalities and municipal authorities respectively and`
  line `the references to the State Government in section 4 of that Act shall be construed as references to the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (17483)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 359
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17483&sectionno=359&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (17484)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 360
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015&sectionId=17484&sectionno=360&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00011_200641_1517807323015
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Cantonments Act, 1924 (2 of 1924) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Cantonments Act, 1924 (2 of 1924)--`
  line
  line `(a) any appointment, notification, order, scheme, rule, form, notice or bye-law made or issued,`
  line `and any licence or permission granted under the Act shall, in so far as it is not in consistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act continue in force and be deemed to have been made, issued or granted, under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, unless and until it is superseded by any appointment, notification, order,`
  line `scheme, rule, form, notice or bye-law made or issued or any licence or permission granted under the`
  line `said provisions;`
  line
  line `(b) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and`
  line `things engaged to be done by, with or for the Board shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered`
  line `into or engaged to be done by, with or for the Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all budget estimates, assessments, valuations, measurements or divisions made by the Board`
  line `shall in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force and be`
  line `deemed to have been made under the provisions of this Act unless and until they are superseded by`
  line `any budget estimate, assessment, valuation, measurement or division made by the Board constituted`
  line `under the said provisions;`
  line
  line `(d) all properties, movable and immovable and all interests of whatsoever nature and kind therein,`
  line `vested in the Board shall with all rights of whatsoever description, use, enjoyed or possessed by the`
  line `said Board vest in the Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) all rates, taxes, fees, rents and other sums of money due to the Board shall be deemed to be`
  line `due to the Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) all rates, taxes, fees, rents, fares and other charges shall, until and unless they are varied by the`
  line `Board constituted under this Act, continue to be levied at the same rate at which they were being`
  line `levied by the Board immediately before the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) all suits, prosecutions and other legal proceedings instituted or which might have been`
  line `instituted by or against the Board may be continued or instituted by or against the Board constituted`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
